title: taco salad dip
directions: Cream together first 6 ingredients and salt.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan. Chill.
Make sure it is set.
Place each of the following layers one at a time in order listed, taco sauce, onion, tomato, lettuce and Cheddar.
Serve with any taco chips.

title: spanish rice
directions: Brown rice in oil in skillet.
Pour tomato sauce and water in skillet after rice has browned.
Add onion, salt and pepper.
Cook at medium heat for approximately 40 minutes.
Stir occasionally. If rice starts sticking, add more water.

title: buttermilk pralines
directions: Bring soda, sugar and buttermilk to a rolling boil.
Boil 5 minutes (soft ball stage).
Add butter, vanilla and pecans and beat until it gets creamy (a long time).
Drop by tablespoon on buttered pan or wax paper.
Use a 5-quart heavy pan.

title: savory spread
directions: Combine ingredients until smooth.
Spread on hot bread.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake 60 minutes at 350°.

title: fudge frosting
directions: Place margarine, cocoa and milk in saucepan; bring to a boil. Add sugar, vanilla and nuts; mix well.
Spread on cake or cupcakes while hot.

title: fiesta bread
directions: Cut bread in half.
Spread each half with cheese mixture.
Add the other ingredients.
Put loaf together.
Wrap in foil.
Heat over medium setting on gas grill, turning frequently.
Cut in slices and serve.

title: broccoli turkey salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 2 tablespoons of the juice and set aside.

title: swedish apple pie
directions: Place apples in a pie plate. Sprinkle with 1 tablespoon sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
In a saucepan, melt the stick of butter. Remove from heat. Stir in the flour and sugar. Add egg last and mix well.
Put chopped nuts over apples, if desired.
Pour cooked mixture over apples. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sweet sausage in sauce
directions: Saute cut-up pepper and cut up onion in oil. Drain oil.
Add tomatoes (cut up), tomato sauce, tomato paste plus water, salt and pepper.
Boil sausage for 5 minutes; remove from pot.
Cut sausage into pieces; simmer for 1 1/2 to 2 hours in sauce.
If desired, add 2 small cans of mushroom pieces and stems.

title: granola bars
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Line a 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan with foil; grease.
In a large bowl, stir together all ingredients. Press evenly into pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool slightly.
Remove from pan and peel off foil.
Cut into bars.
Store, loosely covered, at room temperature.
Yields 48 bars.

title: raspberry punch
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; add sugar, cold water and juices.
Cool, but don't chill or gelatin will congeal.
(If this happens, heat just enough to bring back to liquid.)
When time to serve, pour into punch bowl.
Add ginger ale and frozen raspberries.
Stir until raspberries break apart.
Makes 4 quarts.

title: easy green pea dumplings
directions: Drop peas and onion into boiling salted water; cover and simmer 8 minutes.
Add the beef bouillon cubes and 2 tablespoons butter.
Add pepper to taste.
Cut each biscuit into quarters or strips and pinch off into boiling peas and water.
Drop one piece at a time, stirring frequently, as dough cooks.
Allow enough water, because dough will absorb some while cooking.

title: orange chiffon cake
directions: Measure the first 4 ingredients together into mixing bowl. Make a well and add remaining ingredients in order.
Beat until smooth with electric mixer.

title: jew bread
directions: Mix in top of double boiler over hot water.
Melt sugar and eggs in boiler until syrupy.
Add rest of ingredients.
Pour into greased pan or spray with Pam.
Bake in 300° oven for 20 minutes or until done.
Cool, then cut in squares.

title: four (4) layer dessert
directions: Mix oleo and flour; mix well.
Add nuts.
Press into 10-inch pie pan and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Remove from oven and let cool completely.

title: crab - mushroom - cheese quiche
directions: Bake pastry shell at 450 degrees for 10 minutes.
Drain mushrooms.
Save liquid.
Saute mushrooms in butter for 2 minutes. Scatter in pie shell.
Scatter crab meat and cheese over mushrooms. Mix sour cream and mayonnaise with mushroom liquid, salt and flour. Add enough light cream to make 2 cups.
Blend in eggs and pepper sauce and pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 350 degrees for 55 minutes or until set.
Let stand 15 minutes before cutting.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: beef barley soup
directions: In a large kettle or Dutch oven, brown short ribs in hot oil over low heat; drain well.
Stir in water, undrained tomatoes, onion, bouillon, salt, basil and Worcestershire sauce.
Cover; simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Stir in carrot, celery, barley, green pepper and parsley.
Cover; simmer for 45 minutes.
Remove ribs; when cool enough to handle, cut off meat and coarsely chop.
Discard bones.
Skim fat from soup.
Return meat to soup; heat through. Season to taste with salt and pepper.

title: crabmeat spread
directions: Mix cream cheese with mayonnaise, onion and Worcestershire sauce.
Flatten on a plate and put crabmeat on top.
Spread cocktail sauce over and serve with crackers.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place peeled and sliced apples in a greased square pan.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 2 quart casserole.
Layer with 1/3 of the sliced potatoes; sprinkle with salt and pepper and dot with Velveeta chunks.
Continue layering 2 more layers.
Beat the eggs and milk together in a small bowl; pour over the layers. Bake, covered, about 1 hour or until potatoes are cooked and tender.

title: carrot raisin salad
directions: In a medium size bowl, stir together honey, mayonnaise and vinegar until blended.
Stir in cinnamon.
Add carrots, pineapple chunks and raisins.
Toss with dressing.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving.
(Can be made night before.)
Yields 2 cups with 80 calories per 1/2 cup.

title: grape jelly meatballs
directions: Prepare meatballs and begin baking.
Combine chili sauce and jelly in pan.
Heat over medium heat until jelly is melted.
Pour over meatballs and finish baking.

title: liz's microwave rice
directions: Soak rice in 2 cups of hot water for 30 minutes.
Dissolve chicken bouillon cubes in 1 3/4 cups of hot water.
Drain and rinse rice.
Place rice in casserole and stir in butter.
Season to taste with garlic salt.
Pour chicken bouillon over rice, but do not stir.
Cover and microwave for 15 minutes.
Let stand, covered, for 4 minutes.
Stir and serve.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Combine
hot
water, Crisco, salt and sugar.
Add yeast mixture
(yeast,
teaspoon
sugar
and warm water) and egg. Then
add 3 cups flour.
Beat slowly real good, then add other cup of
flour and beat until smooth.
Put in a bowl.
Put oil over top.
Refrigerate.	Must sit at least 4 hours.
Will keep up to 3 or 4 days.	Take out amount you need.
Form into rolls and let rise for about 30 minutes.	Bake at 425° until done.

title: rod's soft pretzels
directions: Make up bread dough enough for two loaves.
Knead dough.
Cut off dough in strips and roll into ropes.
Form into pretzel shapes. Let rise 1/2 hour or so.
Bake at 400° until brown, around 1/2 hour or so.
Beat egg and water together.
Brush over pretzels before baking.

title: pink snow
directions: Mix all ingredients together except Jell-O.
Sprinkle Jell-O in mixture.

title: blender coconut pie
directions: Blend all above ingredients in blender for 2 minutes.
Pour in greased 9-inch pie pan.
Let it set for 5 minutes.
Sprinkle 1 cup of coconut.
Bake 40 minutes at 350.

title: turtle cheesecake
directions: Mix and press into a spring-form pan.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Have potatoes drained and cooled.
Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain.
Mix all ingredients, adding enough mayonnaise to mix well.

title: chocolate butterscotch brownies
directions: Mix well and press into well greased 9 inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 30-35 minutes.
Cool for 45 minutes and cut in squares.

title: taco fiesta
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet; drain off excess grease after adding salt, onions and black pepper.
Cook thoroughly.
Add tomato sauce and paste, then water and hot sauce; simmer.
Cook shells for 5 to 7 minutes at 375°.
Spoon ground beef mixture into shells.
Top with lettuce, cheese and tomatoes.

title: herbal tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in an airtight container.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cut cucumbers, tomatoes and peppers into small pieces.
Mix with spaghetti, Italian dressing and Salad Delight.
Mix through and through very well.
Cover and let it chill.

title: million dollar fudge
directions: Combine milk, butter and sugar in a large pan.
Bring to a boil gently 4 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into two buttered pans.
Refrigerate until firm.
Yields 5 pounds.

title: cheesy ham and potato casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter in large saucepan until tender.
Add flour and seasonings.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly. Gradually add milk; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add 1 1/2 cups cheese; stir until cheese melts. Add ham and potatoes.

title: sausage quiche
directions: Crumble sausage and cook until brown.
Remove sausage and add butter and onions to drippings and cook for 5 minutes.
Cover bottom of pie crust with sausage, onions and 1/4 cup of cheese.

title: okra and rice
directions: Cook bacon in Dutch oven until crisp; remove bacon to a paper towel. Cook okra, water, tomato, corn, onion and seasonings in bacon drippings over medium heat for 5 minutes. Reduce to low. Cover and simmer 15 minutes or until vegetables are tender. Serve over rice and top with crumbled bacon.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Do not use chicken wings.
Remove skin from remaining pieces.
Salt chicken.
Coat chicken with a mixture of flour, 2 teaspoons salt, pepper and paprika.
Combine eggs and milk.
Dip chicken in egg mixture.
Roll in mixture of cheese and bread crumbs.
In oven, melt 2 tablespoons butter and shortening in pan.
Place chicken, bone side down, in pan.
Drizzle with melted butter.
Bake 1 hour.
Makes 6 servings.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mince onion, peppers and garlic; saute onion, jalapeno pepper, garlic green pepper, onion powder and garlic powder in butter.
Add vinegar and water, then simmer.
Stir in brown sugar, ketchup (as much as needed), tomato paste, tomato sauce and Worcestershire sauce or hot sauce.
Add paprika, mustard, lemon juice and smoke flavoring to taste.
Cook on low heat for 20 minutes.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Dissolve jello in water; set aside to cool.
Tear cake into small pieces and press into an 8 1/2 x 11 1/2-inch cake pan.
Mix Dream Whip as the package directions say.
Pour jello and strawberries over cake.
Chill.
Top with Cool Whip before serving.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Put 1/2 in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Cover with green beans and Tater Tots.
Add rest of hamburger. Heat cream of chicken soup, cream of mushroom soup and milk.
Pour over meat and cover with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: deviled tuna dip
directions: *Optional:
Use plain yogurt instead of sour cream.

title: mandarin dessert
directions: Melt the oleo.
Add the sugar.
Pour over the crackers.
Mix and press in big Pyrex pan.
Mix Cool Whip, milk, orange juice, mandarin oranges, crushed pineapple and marshmallows all together. Spread over the cracker crust.
Refrigerate.

title: hashed brown casserole
directions: Rinse and drain potatoes.
Heat soup in pan with butter.
Stir in sour cream and pour over potatoes.
Mix in cheese and onions. Season with salt and pepper.
Dot top with butter and crushed corn flakes.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: hawaiian baked onion
directions: Cut onions in half and put in buttered pan.
Mix tomato juice, pineapple juice and honey and pour over onions.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until soft.
A little grated fresh ginger over top is a nice touch.

title: chili-egg on triscuits
directions: Put 2 cans of green chilies (chopped) in 8-inch square pan. Cover with grated cheese.
Beat eggs with Worcestershire sauce and salt.
Pour over all.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve on Triscuits.

title: pinch bread
directions: Thaw bread and cut into one inch slices.
Roll into balls. Dip each ball into melted butter and then into cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Place balls in ungreased Bundt pan.
Let rise about an hour.
Bake at 315° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: peanut butter gems
directions: Melt chocolate in microwave or double boiler. Mix together remaining ingredients and pat into bottom of 9 x 13 pan. Spread melted chocolate over this mixture. Chill and cut into small squares.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add ketchup, Worcestershire sauce, mustard, vinegar, sugar, celery seed, salt, pepper and hot water. Simmer at least 1 hour or until desired thickness.
Serve on hamburger buns.

title: crab bisque
directions: About 20 minutes before serving, mix soups, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce together.
Simmer over low heat for 10 minutes.
Then add the crabmeat and simmer for 10 more minutes. Just before serving, stir in the sherry.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: pork chop 'n potato bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown chops in vegetable oil.
Salt the chops.
Combine soup, milk, sour cream and pepper.
Stir in potatoes, 1/2 the cheese and 1/2 can onions.
Spoon mixture into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Arrange pork chops over mix.
Bake covered for 90 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onions.
Bake uncovered 5 minutes more.

title: choco-date squares
directions: Melt 1/2 cup butter with 1/2 cup chocolate chips in saucepan. Blend in flour and sugar.
Press firmly on bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.

title: baked onion potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes.
Cut, unpeeled, into chunks.
Mix oil and soup together.
Place in bowl or plastic bag.
Add potatoes.
Shake until well coated.
Place potatoes on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 450° for 40 minutes or until browned.

title: butter pecan sauce
directions: In a heavy saucepan, combine the sugars and cornstarch. Gradually stir in cream until smooth; bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly. Cook and stir for 2 to 3 minutes or until slightly thickened. Remove from heat; stir in butter until melted. Add pecans. Serve warm over ice cream or pound cake.

title: old-fashioned cracker stuffing(a moist, delicately herbed dressing for chicken)
directions: Cook celery and onion in butter until tender.
Add 3/4 cup milk to cracker crumbs.
Stir in onion mixture, egg, parsley, sage, thyme, salt and a dash of pepper.
Makes 2 1/2 cups stuffing, enough for a 3 to 4 pound chicken.

title: ginger and rum roasted cornish game hens
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Season Cornish hens well with salt and pepper, inside and out.
Combine remaining ingredients in bowl. Spoon 2 tablespoons of the mixture into each hen cavity.
Tie the legs together and fold the wings back.
Place the hens in a roasting pan.
Brush each hen with the sauce.
Roast for 55 minutes or until tender.
Baste the hens twice during the cooking time with the sauce.

title: mochi chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients, except chicken. Add chicken to mixture; let stand for 2 hours or refrigerate overnight.
Fry or grill until done.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spoon one inch apart on greased baking sheet.
Bake 8 minutes at 350°.
Remove at once.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: randy's secret sauce for halibut
directions: Mince garlic.
Saute in butter in pan.
Lightly brown steaks on both sides.
In a separate bowl, mix soy sauce, brown sugar, spices and wine.
Stir until the sugar dissolves (it should taste salty and sweet if the mixture is right).
Pour over fish.
Turn heat down to medium-low.
Let sauce thicken and fish cook.
The fish flakes when it is done.

title: hawaiian cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on package.
Cool.
Mix pudding and milk.
Add Cool Whip and cream cheese.
Spread on cake.
Sprinkle on coconut, pineapple, cherries and nuts on top, if desired.

title: molded broccoli
directions: Dissolve gelatin in undiluted warm consomme to broccoli.
Add finely mashed eggs and remaining ingredients to consomme.
Turn food in eggs and broccoli; blend well.
Put in mold which has been greased with mayonnaise.
Chill.
Serves 14 to 16.

title: carol sparks' sausage bread
directions: Mix hot roll mix according to package instructions.
Cover and set aside for use later.
Brown sausage on low heat for 5 minutes. Drain well; chunk sausage into very small pieces and add chopped onion.
Continue to cook on low heat until sausage is almost done. Drain again and add cheeses, parsley flakes, salt and Tabasco sauce.
Cook for one minute; add beaten eggs and cook for another minute.
Turn off heat and set aside.
Roll dough mixture (on floured surface) into a large round thin circle.
Place sausage mixture in center of circle.
Fold dough over sausage mixture to form a crescent shape.
Brush with melted butter and bake for 25 to 30 minutes in a preheated 350° oven.
Brush bread with melted butter when removed from oven.

title: raisin-nut sandwiches
directions: In saucepan, put sugar and lemon juice; mix well.
Add raisins, pecans and egg yolk.
Mix well and cook 3 minutes. While still hot, add mayonnaise and stir. Spread on bread.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Place the first 4 ingredients in 4-cup microsafe bowl. Microwave on High 2 minutes.
Stir really well and add 1 teaspoon vanilla and 1/2 cup chopped pecans.
Pour in buttered platter.

title: almond cake(fyrstekake)
directions: Crumble butter into flour.
Add baking powder, beaten egg and sugar.
Roll out to line a 9-inch cake tin.
Cover bottom and sides of pan.
Add filling.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: pancakes
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Combine egg, milk and butter. Add to dry ingredients.
Stir until flour is moistened.
(Batter will be lumpy.)
Bake on ungreased griddle.

title: dump cake
directions: Pour 1/2 cup margarine over top of ingredients (add as listed).
Bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Serve warm with vanilla ice cream or whipped cream.

title: baked ham
directions: Place ham in large baking dish.
Sprinkle well with brown sugar.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Then place pineapple slices around sides and on top.
Bake for another hour.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage and onion; drain.
Cook macaroni until tender; drain.
Combine soup, milk, salt and pepper in casserole.
Stir in sausage mixture, macaroni and peas.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: spicy mexican skillet chicken
directions: Mix chili powder, salt and pepper.
Sprinkle evenly over both sides of chicken.
Heat oil in 10-inch skillet over medium heat until hot.
Cook chicken in oil 10 minutes, until brown on both sides.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink when centers of thickest pieces are cut.

title: do nothing cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: crispy doodles
directions: Boil Karo and brown sugar until bubbly. Add 1 cup of peanut butter. Add Special K and stir well. Press mixture into a buttered 13 x 9 x 2 pan.

title: coffee coffee cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening with pastry blender or fork until coarse crumbs.
Reserve 3/4 cup of this mix for top.
To rest, add well beaten eggs and coffee.

title: red cucumbers
directions: Peel and slice cucumbers.
Soak cucumbers in pickling lime and 8 1/2 quarts water for 24 hours.
Rinse well and soak in cold water for 3 hours.

title: salami
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cover and refrigerate for 24 hours stirring occasionally.
Makes 2 (12-inch) rolls and wrap in foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Punch holes in bottom of foil rolls and place directly on the oven rack.
Use an oblong cake pan to catch the drips.

title: mr. mom's turkey pot pie
directions: Heat turkey/chicken, Veg-All, soup and thyme in large pot over medium heat until it begins to bubble.
Place 1 crust in bottom of pie pan.
Fill with meat/veggie mixture.
Cover with second crust. Seal edges and cut slits in the top crust.
Sprinkle with more thyme.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes until crust is brown.

title: egg custard(2 pies)
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar.
Melt butter and add to mixture.
Add vanilla and evaporated milk.
Mix well and pour into 2 unbaked crusts.
Bake at 300° for about an hour.

title: nitey-nite cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line a baking sheet with parchment paper or foil.
Beat egg whites until frothy.
Gradually add sugar while beating, until mixture can hold stiff peaks.
Fold in chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart onto a prepared baking sheet.
Place into oven and quickly close the door.
Turn the oven off.
Let cookies remain at least 5 hours, undisturbed.
Makes about 25 to 30 cookies.

title: chili con carne
directions: Brown ground beef in heavy skillet.
Place ground beef and all other ingredients in pot with a tight fitting cover.
Cook over low heat for about 2 hours.

title: strawberry chicken salad
directions: Sprinkle the chicken breast halves lightly with salt and pepper.
Pour chicken broth into a large saucepan or skillet.
Add chicken to broth.
Bring broth to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer chicken for 15 to 20 minutes or until chicken is tender and no longer pink.
Remove chicken from broth with a slotted spoon and cool slightly.
Thinly slice chicken breasts.

title: ida's pecan pie
directions: Combine dry ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Add eggs, syrup, vanilla and margarine.
Beat with electric mixer until blended.
Stir in pecans.
Pour mixture in pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: bean salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except sweet and sour dressing in large bowl.
Add sweet and sour dressing; cover and chill for 3 to 4 hours or overnight.
Toss well.
When ready to serve, add more dressing if desired.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: watermelon rind preserves
directions: Soak rind in sugar overnight.
Bring to a slow boil and cook about 3 hours.
Add alum and cook 15 minutes longer.

title: microwave hot german potato salad
directions: Pierce potatoes with fork.
Microwave on High 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool slightly, peel potatoes and cut into 1/8-inch slices to make about 4 cups.
Cut bacon into small pieces, place in 2-quart casserole dish, cover with paper towel.
Microwave on High 6 minutes, stirring after 3 minutes, until crisp.
Set aside and drain.
Stir flour, sugar and seasonings into bacon fat until smooth.
Microwave on High 1 to 2 minutes, until bubbly, stirring after 1 minute.
Add water and vinegar to flour mixture. Microwave on High 4 minutes, until mixture boils and thickens, stirring after 1 minute.
Remove from oven and stir smooth.
Add potatoes and bacon, stir gently.
Cover and let stand until served.

title: shrimp gumbo
directions: Mix the oil and flour together in a 4-cup measure to make a roux.
Cook on High for 6 to 7 minutes until dark brown.
Stir and cook 30 seconds to 1 minute longer to give good dark color.
Add onion, celery and bell pepper to roux in measuring cup.
Stir and return to microwave.
Saute on High 3 minutes.
Add garlic, parsley and green onion to roux.
Stir and return to microwave. Saute on High 2 minutes.
At this time, if oil has risen to the top, pour off.
Slowly add enough hot tap water to bring roux to the 4-cup mark.
Stir and you will have a smooth, dark roux. Transfer roux to a 4-quart casserole.
Cooking time:
12 minutes.

title: baptist punch
directions: Mix Minute Maid lemonade per directions on can.
Mix 3 cups sugar with 3 cups warm water.
Pour sugar mixture in with lemonade and add grape juice.
Let chill.
Add 1 quart of ginger ale to 3/4 gallon punch.
Makes one gallon.

title: cleve's chili beans
directions: Cook beans until tender.
Salt to taste.
Brown ground beef, onion, bell pepper, salt and chorizo in skillet.
Add tomato sauce, El Pato, dried pepper and chili powder.
Simmer 5 minutes. Add beef mixture to beans.
Simmer 10 additional minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine cornbread mix, milk and oil. Mix well. Stir in onion, corn, sugar, salt and chilies. Beat eggs and stir into mixture. Stir in 1 1/2 cups cheese. Pour into greased 13 x 9 pan. Bake at 400° for 25 minutes. Sprinkle remaining cheese on top and continue baking 15 to 20 minutes longer.

title: mom thomson's shilalay
directions: Chop first 3 ingredients.
Boil until soft, about 20 minutes. Mix flour, butter and milk.
Break up cream cheese and add to milk mixture.
Put this mixture in a double boiler, stir until smooth, then add tomato mixture.
Heat until warm.
Serve on crackers. Serves 4 to 6.
Something like Welsh Rabbit.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and margarine well.
Add milk alternately with flour and baking powder.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix well.
Add vanilla and fold in coconut.
Bake in tube cake pan at 350° for 1 hour 10 minutes.

title: penny wise casserole
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling water 15 minutes.
Drain.
Chop pepper and onion and boil slowly in small amount of water until tender and water disappears.
Add meat and cook slowly, stirring constantly until it is crumbly.
Combine mixture, macaroni, corn and soup. Mix well.
Pour into casserole.
Cover with buttered bread crumbs. Bake 15 minutes at 375° or until crumbs are brown and crisp.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Whip shortening and hot water until like whipped cream.
Add salt and vinegar slowly.
Add flour slowly; the last flour will have to be hand mixed.
Makes about 4 to 5 double crusts.
May be refrigerated.

title: cavatini pasta casserole
directions: Cook pasta and drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, then put cheese on top last 15 minutes.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Remove seed section from cut green peppers.
Place pepper halves on a paper towel and cook 6 minutes with microwave energy. Cook onions and beef in an 8-inch round glass cake dish about 4 minutes or until all pink has left the meat.
Stir several times during cooking.
Cook rice according to the directions.
Mix the tomato sauce with water.
Combine onion, beef mixture with cooked rice, half of tomato mixture, egg, salt and pepper.
Stuff pepper halves and place in a 2-quart glass utility dish.
Pour remaining tomato sauce over top and place wax paper over the dish.
Cook with microwave 10 minutes.
Recipe yields 6.

title: tortilla soup
directions: Add all ingredients along with 1 cup of chopped chicken to the skimmed broth and simmer about 30 minutes until the vegetables are tender. Serve over tortilla chips and shredded Monterey Jack cheese.
Garnish with a slice of avocado and a dollop of sour cream.

title: peanut butter chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix the sugars and shortening. Add the egg and vanilla. Mix in the peanut butter. Sift flour, salt,
and soda together add this to other mixture. Add chocolate chips last. Bake at 300 to 325 for 12 - 15 minutes.

title: country-braised pork chops
directions: Coat pork chops with flour.
Brown onion in oil in skillet until tender.
Add pork chops and brown on both sides.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Heat to boiling point.
Reduce heat. Simmer, covered, for 1 hour or until pork chops are tender, stirring occasionally.
Yields 4 servings, about 573 calories each.

title: slush punch
directions: Freeze for 16 to 20 hours. If using soon, stir every few hours or freeze and when ready to use, thaw out overnight.
Keep stirred to give it the slush texture.
Will keep frozen for several months.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Place onions and potatoes in a baking dish.
Place pork chops on top.
Pour soup and water over all.
Bake, covered, at 375° until chops are tender.
Turn chops over 1/2 way through (20 minutes).

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream first 4 ingredients.
Beat, adding eggs one at a time. Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with buttermilk.
Add bananas.
Beat until all are combined.
Stir in pecans.
Bake in 3 bread loaf pans (greased and floured) for one hour and thirty minutes at 325°.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and eggs. Blend well. Add bananas.
Beat well. Add flour and soda.
Beat well after each addition.
Add nuts and mix well.
Bake in greased loaf pan at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: mama's fig cake
directions: Beat sugar, oil and egg well. Slowly add dry ingredients. Add vanilla, preserves and pecans. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes in a greased and floured 7 x 11 pan.

title: sugar drop cookies
directions: Stir flour, baking powder and salt.
Cream butter and sugar. Add egg; beat until fluffy.
Alternately mix flour and milk and egg mixture.
Add vanilla.
Drop by teaspoonful on cookie sheet 2 inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Remove from cookie sheet while hot.

title: grilled chicken salad platter
directions: Combine dressing mix and oil.
Pour over chicken breasts in a shallow pan.
Toss to coat well.
Cover.
Refrigerate 1 hour. Place chicken on greased grill and grill, uncovered, 15 to 20 minutes or until tender, brushing with marinade.
Remove and place vegetables on grill; turn frequently until just crisp, about 3 minutes.

title: thai broccoli salad(low calorie)
directions: Combine peanut butter, Equal, hot water, lime juice, soy sauce, sesame oil and red pepper flakes until well blended. Set aside.

title: potato soup
directions: Boil the potatoes in enough water to cover.
Microwave celery and carrots until tender. Add to the potatoes. Add white sauce and corn. Simmer.

title: stuffed salmon
directions: Pre-heat oven to 450°F.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and cheese as directed on box.
Add remaining ingredients and bake until hot at 375°.

title: low calorie brownie bars
directions: Coat 9 x 12 x 2-inch baking pan with nonstick cooking spray.

title: pumpkin cake delight
directions: Set aside 1 cup cake mix.
Stir the remaining ingredients with a wooden spoon and pat up to all sides of a 9 x 12-inch pan.

title: sand tarts
directions: Bake at 400° for approximately 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chocolate dessert
directions: Cream 1 stick butter, 1 cup flour and 1 3/4 cups crushed nuts. Mix well.
Press out into 8 x 10-inch pan or baking dish.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Cream the cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread over cooled crust.
Mix chocolate pudding and milk.
Spread over top of other 2 layers in pan.
Top with remaining Cool Whip and nuts.

title: beef tacos
directions: Season beef with monosodium glutamate, salt, chili powder and garlic powder.
Heat the skillet.
Put raw beef mixture in center of tortillas, and fold over, drop into hot oil and fry for 1 minute and 30 seconds on each side.
Remove from oil and drain on paper towel.
Stuff remaining open space with shredded lettuce and chopped tomato.
Yields 12 to 14 servings.

title: chicken paprikash(hungarian dish)
directions: This recipe comes from a very dear friend.
When I told him about this cookbook, he was very excited to share this special, old favorite family recipe.
He told me this is the most requested meal by his family.
Thanks Les....Forever Plaid!

title: indian pudding
directions: Scald the milk with the cornmeal added, then mix in oleo, molasses, salt, spices and eggs.
Pour into well-greased dish. Add the evaporated milk, but do not stir.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except butter, almonds and crackers. Place in 2 1/2-quart greased casserole. Mix butter, almonds and crackers and place evenly over top.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Remove foil on top the last 10 minutes.

title: pecan nut patties
directions: Combine all ingredients, except soup.
Drop by spoonfuls into hot oil.
Brown on both sides.
Place in casserole, cover with mushroom sauce.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
(May serve plain without sauce or baking.)

title: kraut salad
directions: Use oil from pimentos as part of oil.
Mix and let stand several hours.

title: spicy corn dip
directions: Chill; serve with tortilla chips.

title: apple salad
directions: Mix apples, celery, nuts, bacon, cheese and mayonnaise.
Place on lettuce leaves and sprinkle with salt and pepper or paprika.

title: mashed peas and potatoes
directions: Scrub the potatoes and slice (leave skins on).
Add onion slices, salt, pepper and part of stick of butter.
Place it
all on a double thickness of aluminum foil (large piece) and fold over; seal tightly.
Place on grill. Turn over after 8 to 10 minutes for another 8 to 10 minutes.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and pepper.
Drain fat.
Add the pepper, garlic salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Add bouillon cubes, wine and bread crumbs.
Turn to low heat and add sour cream. Simmer until ready to stuff washed and stemmed mushroom buttons. Stuff and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: welsh cakes
directions: Rub margarine (mix) into flour.
Add caster sugar.
Add currants.
Beat eggs and mix into dry ingredients.
The mixture should be easy to roll out to approximately 1/4-inch thick.
Add another egg or a little milk if mixture is too dry.
Cut into rounds and bake on a griddle or frying pan.
When slightly browned, turn and bake on the other side.

title: vegetable fish chowder(low-fat and cholesterol)
directions: Heat oil in 4-quart saucepan and saute onion about 5 minutes. Add carrots, celery, potatoes, water and herbs.
Cover and gently simmer until vegetables are just tender, about 15 minutes.
Add fish and simmer another 10 to 15 minutes more until fish is just cooked.
Stir in evaporated skim milk and heat to serving temperature.
Do not boil.
Add pepper to taste.
Makes about 10 cups.

title: easy candy cookies
directions: Bring Karo syrup, margarine, sugar, and brown sugar to a boil.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter, Rice Krispies, Corn Flakes, and nuts.
Blend well and spoon onto wax paper.
Makes 5 doz.

title: ambrosia salad
directions: Drain pineapple and mandarin oranges.
Combine fruit with pecans.
Add marshmallows.
Add sugar to yogurt and add to fruit and marshmallow mixture.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Serve chilled. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Bring to boil the oleo, water and cocoa.
In large mixing bowl, combine flour, white sugar and salt.
Add to flour the eggs beaten with buttermilk, baking soda and vanilla.
Pour hot mixture in with flour and egg mixture.
Mix well.
Pour on ungreased sheet pan, 11 x 17-inches with 1-inch sides.
Batter will be hot.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: chicken breast casserole
directions: Mix soup, sour cream and broth in small bowl; set aside.
Toss crackers into melted butter.
Layer into 8 x 11-inch casserole dish, beginning with 1/2 the crackers, then breast chunks, then creamy mixture with crackers on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cranberry gelatin salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot cranberry sauce. Cool. Add pineapple and ginger ale. Chill until slightly thickened. Stir in remaining ingredients and pour into a ring mold or any dish. Chill until firm.

title: gooey dessert
directions: Mix together and bake until lightly brown (burns easily).

title: cranberry-orange relish
directions: Mix all ingredients and simmer until all berries pop, 15 to 20 minutes over medium heat.
Put in sterilized jars and seal. Will keep indefinitely in refrigerator.
Makes 1 1/2-quarts.

title: pizza
directions: Stir together the warm water and yeast to dissolve.
Stir in the sugar, salt and olive oil.
Add 2 cups flour.
Blend in, then add about 1 1/2 cups more flour.
Knead dough, enough for 2 pizzas, until smooth and elastic.
Let rise 45 minutes until double.

title: dirt cake
directions: Make in a clean plastic flowerpot and put an artificial flower in the center.
Serve with a plastic gardening tool.

title: pumpkin cheesecake
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, sugar and butter in a medium bowl.
Press onto the bottom and 1-inch up sides of a spring-form pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 6 to 8 minutes.
Do not allow to brown.
Remove from oven; cool.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli; arrange on tray or in
11 1/2 x 7 1/2-inch pan.

title: cheesecake
directions: Crush graham crackers.
Add 3 tablespoons sugar and oleo. Press mixture in bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Beat cream cheese and 2 cups sugar well.
Add eggs, one at a time, blending well after each.
Add vanilla.
Pour over graham mixture.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Chocolate chips or fresh blueberries can be added before baking.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Pour into three small or two large greased loaf pans.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Bread will slice better if served the following day.
Freezes well.

title: corn griddle cakes
directions: Melt butter or margarine and set aside to cool.
Sift together and set aside the flour, baking powder, sugar, salt, celery salt and monosodium glutamate.
Drain contents of corn.
Put into a large bowl with well-beaten egg and milk.

Add melted shortening, mix until corn is evenly distributed throughout mixture. Gradually add dry ingredients, blending well after each addition. Test griddle, it is hot enough for baking, when drops of water sprinkled on surface dance in small beads.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown onion and sausage well. Stir in soups and milk.
Cook noodles.
Mix all and bake in casserole dish at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: sand tarts
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add flour, pecans and vanilla.
Mix together.
Roll in balls and bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Roll balls in powdered sugar.

title: sauce provencale for broiled steak or roast prime rib
directions: Sprinkle tomatoes with sugar and set aside.
Melt 2 tablespoons of butter.
Add onion and heat through.
Add wine; cook and stir until liquid is slightly reduced.
Add tomatoes; heat through.
Add remaining ingredients; heat, stirring gently until butter melts.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: giblet gravy
directions: Cook heart, gizzard, neck, celery and onion until tender; drain.
When cool enough to handle, chop giblets rather fine. Blend drippings and flour; add broth and cook, stirring constantly until gravy thickens.
Add salt and stir in giblets.
Heat and serve.

title: sour cream chicken breasts
directions: Salt, pepper and paprika each piece of chicken.
Place bone side down in baking dish and spoon sour cream over each piece. Sprinkle cracker crumbs over this and pour melted margarine over all.
Bake uncovered in a 350° oven for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: johnnycake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Stir until blended.
Bake at 350° until firm and slightly brown.
Serve as a bread or with milk and sugar.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Freeze in a Tupperware container.
Will keep in freezer for 2 to 3 months.

title: cheese round
directions: Mix together first five ingredients.
Stir in 1/2 cup pecans. Spread remaining pecans in the bottom of greased Bundt pan. Spread in cheese mixture and then refrigerate.
When ready to serve, turn onto platter and spoon preserves in center.
Serve with your favorite crackers to serve.
It is better to let set overnight before serving to let the flavors blend together.

title: dill cheese bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in a large bowl.
Heat cheese to warm.
Stir into yeast mixture.
Stir in rest of ingredients except flour and butter.
Mix well.
Beat in flour gradually until completely blended.
Beat vigorously about 20 strokes.
(Dough will be sticky and heavy.) Cover; let rise until doubled in bulk. Stir down dough.
Spoon into 6-cup baking bowl.
Cover and let rise 45 minutes.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for about 50 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding mix, regular milk, Eagle Brand milk and Cool Whip until smooth (best if use electric mixer).
In large container (13 x 9 x 3 1/2-inch cake pan is okay), add in layers (2 or 3) crushed vanilla wafers or graham crackers, sliced bananas and pudding. Sprinkle wafers on top.
Takes 10 minutes tops!

title: caramel corn
directions: Place popped corn in a large roasting pan.
In heavy 1-1/2 qt. sauce pan stir sugar, margarine, and corn syrup together. Stirring constantly, bring to a boil over medium heat.
Without stirring, boil 5 minutes.
Remove from heat, stir in vanilla and soda.
Pour over corn stirring to coat well.
Bake at 250 for 1 hour stirring every 15 minutes.

title: homemade brown sugar
directions: Take some morning sunshine.
Add a smile, some kind words, too.
Sprinkle in some happy hours.
It's not very hard to do...

title: a nutty cake for nutty people
directions: Drain fruit cocktail juice in a cup and save. Mix cake mix according to directions, but omitting the water and using the cocktail juice. The mix calls for 1 cup of water but my juice was about 2/3 cup and was fine. After mixing the batter thoroughly, fold in the fruit cocktail and 1 cup of chopped pecans. Pour into a 9 x 13 pan or dish and cook per directions, about 40 minutes. When you remove from the oven, spread about 4 ounces of Cool Whip on top of hot cake and let melt and soak in. After it is cooled, spread 12 ounces of Cool Whip on top of cake and then cover with the other cup of chopped pecans.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Combine sugar and flour in mixing bowl.
Heat oleo, Coke and cocoa to boiling.
Pour over flour and sugar.
Mix thoroughly. Add eggs, buttermilk, soda and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add marshmallows and mix well.
This is thin batter and marshmallows will float over top.
Bake in large oblong pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Ice while hot.

title: italian spaghetti salad
directions: Cut into small pieces cucumbers, tomatoes and onions. Bring water to a boil and add spaghetti; boil for 5 minutes. Do not let spaghetti get soft; drain and rinse off with cold water. Add cucumbers, tomatoes and scallions (green onions). Then sprinkle McCormick Salad Supreme seasoning until spaghetti starts to get a little red. Mix all through spaghetti. Add Seven Seas Italian Viva dressing. This will take the whole bottle.

title: cheese salad
directions: Mix orange jello and hot water until completely dissolved. Cool to lukewarm.
Add pineapple to jello mixture and let it jell slightly.
Add Dream Whip to jello mixture, then add cheese.
Let set until solid.

title: health bread
directions: Mix ingredients.
Add well beaten egg, milk and molasses and then oil.
Bake in slow oven in bread loaf mold for about 45 minutes.

title: o.t. appetizer
directions: In a small bowl, mix mayonnaise, egg yolk, mustard, Tabasco sauce, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
In a medium bowl, mix together the olives, onion and cheese.
Pour sauce on top; mix until blended.
(Mixture can be made a day ahead and refrigerated. Just stir before spreading.)
Put squares of rye bread on a cookie sheet and run under the broiler of your oven until lightly toasted.
Remove from oven; turn them over.
Spread vegetable-cheese mixture on top of bread to the edge so bread won't burn.
Return to broiler (about 3 minutes) until cheese is somewhat melted and bubbly.
Serve.
Let me know if you like them!!

title: baked squash
directions: Cook squash and onion in a small amount of salted water; drain and mash.
Mix with egg, butter, cheese and 1/2 cracker crumbs. Place in a casserole dish.
Top with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: cream of broccoli and potato soup
directions: Cook vegetables until tender.
Drain off all but 1 cup of broth.
Mash vegetables slightly.
Add milk, cheese, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat until cheese is melted and soup is heated through.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender. Drain and arrange in greased baking dish. Cook and dice chicken.
Put on top of broccoli.
Mix and heat mushroom soup, Miracle Whip, cheese soup and curry powder. Spread half of this mixture over the chicken.
Prepare stuffing according to directions on box and put over soup mixture. Put rest of soup mixture over top and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: buttermilk oatmeal muffins
directions: In a bowl, soak oats in buttermilk for 15 minutes.
Stir in egg, sugar and oil.
Combine flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt; stir into oat mixture just until moistened.
Fill greased muffin cups 3/4 full.
Bake at 400° for 16 to 18 minutes or until muffins test done.
Yields about 8 muffins.

title: country corn bread sausage stuffing
directions: Bake corn bread as directed on package.
Cool and crumble into large bowl.
Add bread cubes and set aside.
Cook sausage with sage until meat is done.
Drain and discard grease.
Saute celery and onions and add to sausage mixture.
Add eggs and chicken broth to combined breads.
Toss lightly.
For more moist stuffing, add 1/4 cup water.
Lightly spoon stuffing into turkey.
Bake as directed.
Place remaining stuffing in a 1 to 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes.
Makes 12 cups.

title: candied walnut halves
directions: Place the walnut halves in a shallow pan; heat in oven at 325° for about 10 minutes.
Cook the sugar, water, cinnamon and salt to soft ball stage (236°) without stirring.
Remove from heat.
Add the vanilla.
Add nuts; stir gently until all nuts are covered and mixture is creamy.
Turn out onto a buttered platter.
Separate nut halves as they cool.

title: cheesy oven potatoes
directions: Melt butter in bottom of baking dish.
Place potatoes in dish. Toss in butter to coat.
Then sprinkle season salt over potatoes. Sprinkle Cheddar cheese over potatoes.
Bake at 450° until done.

title: lee's jambalaya
directions: Saute green pepper, onion, and garlic.	 Add all ingredients except shrimp and parsley.	Simmer 60 to 75 minutes
(might need more water) 30 minutes if using Minute Rice.
Add parsley and shrimp, simmer till done.	Remove bay leaf before serving. Serves 6.

title: beef roast
directions: Place roast in crock pot.
In a mixing bowl, combine all remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour mixture over roast and cook in crock pot on low heat for 8 to 10 hours.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix Italian dressing into plain yogurt and chill.
Serve with raw vegetables.
Best if you make a day ahead.

title: christmas 3-in-1 salad
directions: Chop cranberries in blender.
In large bowl, add apples and pears that have been chopped.
Put marshmallows, pecans and coconut.
Stir in Cool Whip.
Keep salad in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: beef dip
directions: Blend together cream cheese and milk.
Add minced onion, pepper and dried beef.
Stir in sour cream.
Place in small casserole dish.
Bake at 350° until heated through, 15 to 30 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: squash supreme
directions: Grease 9 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Line with crushed saltines. Mix above ingredients and spoon on top of saltines.
Top with more saltines.
Pat butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour (approximately).

title: red devils food cake
directions: Combine flour, sugars, cocoa, salt and baking soda in large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and beat at low speed with mixer until flour is mixed in.
Scrape down sides of bowl as needed. Beat at high speed for about 3 minutes, scraping bowl once or twice.
Prepare two 8 or 9 inch round pans or one 13 x 9 inch with cocoa pan coat, covering sides and bottom generously. Pans may be coated with shortening and dusted with flour.
Pour batter into pans.
Bake in a 350 degree oven for 30 to 35 minutes for round pans or 35 to 40 minutes for rectangle pan.
Cool cake completely. Frost with Snowy Range Icing.

title: apple crisp
directions: Cut
flour, salt and shortening together.
Roll out 1/2 of the dough
on a floured surface.
Spread on the bottom of a cookie sheet.
Sprinkle the corn flakes over the dough and add the chopped
apples
and
sugar.
Roll out the remaining dough and place
on
top of the bottom layer.
Seal the edges.
Beat the egg white
and
brush over the dough.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes
until
brown.
Glaze with powdered sugar icing while hot.

title: lemon baked fish
directions: Thaw fish if frozen.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Divide fish into 6 servings.
Place in single layer in baking dish.
Mix butter, lemon juice, rind and seasonings.
Pour over fish and bake 25 minutes.

title: old fashioned chocolate cake
directions: Beat sugar, eggs and shortening.
Dissolve cocoa and soda in hot water.
Beat in sugar mixture.
Add flour, buttermilk, soda and vanilla; mix well.
Put in well-greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan or 3 (8-inch) round pans.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Spread one can of Crescent rolls onto bottom of 9x13 dish. Bake by directions or until golden brown.

title: chocolate-amaretto cheesecake
directions: Sprinkle chocolate wafer crumbs in bottom of 7-inch spring-form pan.
Set aside.
In food processor, put cream cheese and remaining ingredients, except egg and mini chips, processing until smooth.
Add egg and process until well blended.
Fold in mini chips.
Pour slowly over crumbs.
Bake at 300° for 65 to 70 minutes or until set.
Cool on rack in pan.
Cover and chill at least 8 hours.
Remove from pan.
Garnish with chocolate curls.

title: sweet-sour italian dressing
directions: Blend in electric blender.
Serve at room temperature.

title: creamy tacos
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain.
Mix soup, tomato sauce, tomatoes and beans in a bowl.
Melt Velveeta cheese in Pet milk and mix with other ingredients.
Heat and serve over corn chips.

title: apple pancakes
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients.
Slowly add the water and gently blend in the apples.
FOR FLUFFY PANCAKES DO NOT OVERMIX. Pour onto heated griddle and flip when side is covered in bubbles. Turn only once.
Makes 12 to 14 pancakes.

title: summer melon bowl
directions: Slice watermelon lengthwise 1/3 from top.
Cut the edge with a sharp knife.
Scoop the watermelon out in balls* removing all visible seeds.
Scoop out the scraps inside the watermelon and chill the "bowl".
Cut balls* from other melons.
Prepare grapes. Combine juices and sugar.
Pour over fruit in a large bowl.
Stir occasionally.
Just before serving, fill the melon bowl with fruit.

title: hershey bar pie
directions: Melt marshmallows and milk in double boiler.
Add 6 of the candy bars.
Stir until melted.
Cool.
Mix in the whipped cream. Break up remaining candy bar and mix in.
Pour into pie shell. Garnish with whipped cream.
(I sometimes use a chocolate crust instead of a graham cracker crust.)

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add season mix and water.
Simmer, then cool.
Mix kidney beans, onion, cheese, olives and tomatoes.
Add ground beef mixture and toss.
Refrigerate until serving time. Before serving, add chopped up lettuce and package of Ranch dressing, made as directed on package.
Place chips on plate. Add mixture and serve.

title: no-fuss swiss steak
directions: In a large skillet, brown beef in oil over medium-high heat; drain. Transfer to a 5-quart slow cooker. Add carrots and celery. Combine the remaining ingredients; pour over meat and vegetables. Cover and cook on low for 6 to 8 hours or until meat is tender. Discard the bay leaf before serving. Thicken cooking juices, if desired. Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: blender pimiento cheese
directions: Combine milk, mayonnaise, salt and Tabasco in blender.
Cover and mix on low speed for about 1 minute.
While blender is running, add cheese, one cube at a time, until all are blended. Pour into a bowl, drain and stir in pimientos.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Mix and bake 25 to 30 minutes at 400°.

title: sausage & beans
directions: Combine sausage, beans and salsa in large skillet. Bring to a boil over medium heat. Cover and simmer for 10 minutes or until hot, stirring occasionally. Serve over rice.

title: chocolate walnut frosting
directions: In large bowl, combine sugar and walnuts.
In small saucepan, bring butter, cocoa and milk to a boil.
Stir into sugar mixture. Blend thoroughly.
Spread on warm cake.

title: caroliner corn bread
directions: Mix all the ingredients together and pour in lightly greased Corningware dish.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: chili kahlua
directions: In a 4-quart pot, heat oil. Add onions and garlic.
Saute until soft. Add meat and brown. Add next 10 ingredients and mix well. Add Kahlua.
Increase heat until mixture simmers.
Add beans. Simmer partially covered for 45 minutes.

title: dorothy's yellow cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add eggs and milk.
Beat at medium speed until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients and beat again until smooth.
Bake at 350° in a greased cake pan.
Frost with desired frosting.

title: dutch oven white bean and sausage soup(serves 4)
directions: In
Dutch oven, bring water to a boil.	Add beans; boil briskly for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat; let beans soak for 1 hour.
Add
ham,
salt
pork
and	onion.	Simmer,
partially covered,
for
1 1/2 hours.
Add chorizo, greens and potatoes; simmer for 30 minutes.
Remove sausage and salt pork.
Discard pork.
Slice
chorizo
into
1/4-inch thick rounds.
Return to soup and serve.

title: refrigerator bran muffins
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Add eggs, oil and buttermilk.
This will keep one week in refrigerator or batter can be frozen.
Bake in greased muffin tins at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: lee's stuffing
directions: (Watkins Spices are recommended.)

title: depression cake(making the best of it coffee cake)
directions: Put shortening, sugar, raisins, spices, salt and liquid into boiler and boil 10 minutes.
(Let it stand until cool.)

title: sweet raisin and onion
directions: Chop onion into moon shapes.
Put 1 Tbsp. olive oil into skillet and add onion.
Cover and cook until clear.
Add black pepper, cinnamon, saffron and salt.
Cook uncovered; add raisin and simmer for 10 minutes.
Add sugar and simmer until begins to thicken and sauce is golden.

title: kiss cookies
directions: Mix butter and peanut butter for 30 seconds.
Add 1/2 cup of the flour, sugar, egg, brown sugar or honey, baking soda and powder and vanilla.
Beat until combined.
Mix in rest of flour. If necessary, cover dough and chill until easy to handle.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Roll balls in sugar and put on ungreased cookie sheet 2 inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 9 minutes. Remove from oven and press uncovered kiss into center of cookie. Let cool.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: family style white bread
directions: Blend together yeast, 2 cups flour, sugar, salt and oil into large bowl.
Stir in hot water and beat with spoon until mixture is smooth and satiny.

title: butter thin pancakes(shared by "mom" blakeman)
directions: Mix cream and eggs together.
Mix dry ingredients together. Then, combine wets and drys.
Melt butter until hot.
Add while hot.
Will keep in refrigerator for weeks.
Cook on griddle.

title: jam cake filling
directions: Cook the milk, flour, sugar and eggs until thick, then add remaining ingredients.

title: marjoram corn muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. With cooking spray, coat 12 standard-size muffin pan cups. In large bowl, mix flour, cornmeal, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt.

title: apple butter cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 325° in greased tube pan for 1 1/2 hours.
Glaze, if desired.

title: rave review coconut cake
directions: Blend cake mix, pudding mix, water, eggs and oil in a large mixing bowl. Beat at medium speed for 4 minutes. Stir in coconut and walnuts. Pour into 3 greased and floured 9-inch layer pans or 1 oblong pan. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Cool and frost with Coconut Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: pig stomach
directions: Mix all together and stuff into cleaned pig stomach.
Sew hole closed.
Put into roast pan and bake at 350° for 3 1/4 to 4 hours. Remove lid the last 1/2 hour to brown skin.

title: plum good bread
directions: Sift flour with sugar, salt, baking soda and spices.
Add egg, oil and plums to flour and spices.
Beat about 2 minutes at medium speed (by hand 150 strokes).
Stir in nuts.
Bake in an 8-inch square baking pan about 3 minutes, or until done.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: ham and zucchini quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Combine Parmesan, Cheddar/Jack, zucchini, and ham.
Pour into crust.
Combine eggs, milk, salt, black pepper and melted butter.
Beat until well mixed.
Pour over zucchini mixture. Bake for about 1 hour or until set.
Allow to cool slightly before slicing. Makes 8 servings.

title: yogurt pie treasure
directions: Mix Cool Whip and yogurt together.
Spoon into prepared pie crust and refrigerate.

title: marlean's easy vegetable squares
directions: *That includes chopped broccoli, cauliflower, green pepper, ripe olives, celery, carrots, green onion, seeded tomatoes.

title: orange julius salad
directions: Mix pineapple, water, vanilla, sugar and jello; bring to a boil and cool until thick.
Add Cool Whip, cheese and nuts; refrigerate until set.
Makes a nice mold.

title: chicken salad italian
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients, toss.
Cover and chill.
Serve on lettuce leaves.
Yields 6 servings.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Cook sausage.
Mix with cooked vegetables and partially cook. Add rice and 2 cans cream soup (mushroom, chicken or celery).
Mix all together and bake about 1 hour at 350°.

title: butterscotch cookies
directions: Cream ingredients.
Make in rolls and bake after they have been in icebox overnight, or 3 or 4 days.

title: kahlua pecan pie
directions: Purchase a frozen, unbaked pie shell or prepare pie shell: Combine flour with salt.
Cut in shortening until particles are size of peas.
Sprinkle with cold milk or water, adding just enough to make a stiff dough.
Shape into a ball.
Roll out on a floured surface to a 10 1/2-inch circle and fit into an 8-inch pie pan. Trim edges about 1/2-inch wider than rim of pan; fold under and flute, building up a low fluted rim on the crust.
Cream butter and sugar together well.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Stir in salt, corn syrup and Kahlua.
Arrange pecans in pie shell and carefully and slowly pour Kahlua mixture over them.
Bake on rack placed below the center of the oven at 375° for 30 minutes.
Remove and cool thoroughly.
Serve with Kahlua Cream.

title: pie crust
directions: Cream shortening, flour and salt; add milk.
Roll out and place in a pie plate.
Bake at 400 degrees for 10 minutes.

title: pizzaburger loaf
directions: Combine the onion, tomato paste and water in saucepan; simmer 20 minutes.
Mix together the ground beef, egg, bread crumbs, salt, oregano and basil.
Add 1/2 cup prepared sauce and blend well.
Form into loaf.
Place in a 10 x 6 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 50 minutes.
Pour sauce over, arrange cheese on top. Bake 15 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: old-fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla to sour cream. Sift together dry ingredients and add alternately with the liquid to Crisco and sugar mixture.
Chill thoroughly.
Roll out 1 1/4-inches thick.
Cut with a large cutter.
Sprinkle with sugar and press lightly.
Bake in a moderate 375° oven for 15 minutes. Makes 100 cookies.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook
broccoli	as
directed on package and drain.
Mix together
with soup, onion, mayonnaise, beaten egg and cheese. Put dressing mix on top and bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: potatoes with cheese and apple slices
directions: Bring the water to a boil with the potatoes.
Add the macaroni and cook until done.
Drain.
Arrange in layers in au gratin form, adding cheese to each layer.
Place in a preheated 240° C oven until cheese has melted.
Melt the butter in frying pan.
Add onion and garlic until light brown.
Pour over the potato-macaroni dish. Using the same frying pan, bring the milk, heavy cream and salt to taste to a boil.
Pour over mixture.

title: shredded beet salad with orange-cranberry dressing
directions: Mince orange zest with cranberries and sugar in blender or food processor fitted with metal blade.
Transfer to mixing bowl. Add orange juice, oil, water, mustard, salt, cayenne and beets. Mix well.
Salad is best made 2 days ahead and refrigerated.
To serve, toss well and adjust seasoning to taste.

title: chicken gumbo meat loaf
directions: In a large mixing bowl, mix thoroughly together.
Press into loaf pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Makes about 8 to 10 servings.

title: sherried beef
directions: Marinate beef with sherry, garlic powder and soy sauce several hours.
Drain, reserving liquid.
Brown meat in deep heavy skillet; add reserved liquid and simmer 2 hours, covered.
Add mushrooms, cooking 5 to 10 minutes, according to taste.
Mix in gravy mix to thicken and serve over rice or noodles.

title: crab cheese ball
directions: Stir until creamed all the ingredients, except the crab meat. Mound the creamed mixture on a plate.
Make a hole in the center. Fill with crab meat.
Pour cocktail sauce over top.
Serve with rice crackers.

title: border enchiladas
directions: Stew and debone chicken.
Cool and cut into bite size pieces. Saute onions in margarine.
Drain both cans of tomatoes and reserve the liquid.
Add drained tomatoes to onions and simmer until liquid is reduced, about 10 minutes.
Add cheese, stirring until melted.
Add chicken; mixture should be thick.
Fry tortillas in oil over medium heat to soften.
Drain.
Place a heaping tablespoonful of chicken mixture on each tortilla and roll up.
Place in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Thin remaining chicken mixture with some of the reserved tomato juice from both cans of tomatoes and pour over the enchiladas.
Spread with sour cream. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Salt and pepper pork chops.
Roll in flour and brown on both sides.
Mix together other ingredients and pour over chops.
Cover and cook on low heat for 45 minutes.

title: mondale meat loaf
directions: Combine ingredients; mix well.	Bake in 375° oven for 1 hour.

title: goldie's pie meringue
directions: Cook cornstarch, 2 tablespoons of sugar and 1/2 cup of water until clear.
Cool and add vanilla.
Beat 3 egg whites and add 6 tablespoons sugar, small amount at a time, until forms a peak. Add cornstarch mixture.
Beat to firm peak.
Yields 1 pie.

title: pecan pralines
directions: Cook first 5 ingredients over medium heat until soft ball stage.
Add vanilla and pecans.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: green beans
directions: Defrost
beans,
mix
with remaining ingredients.
Bake covered in 2 quart casserole for 50 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Roll into 1-inch balls. Store in refrigerator or freezer.

title: sauteed chicken
directions: Then pour over chicken in casserole dish. Cook 1 hour at 350°. Cook rice and use sauce over rice.

title: frozen pickles
directions: Mix together sugar, vinegar, celery seed and salt.

title: chex honey roast mix
directions: In large microwave-safe bowl, melt the butter on High for 45 seconds; stir in the honey.
Gradually add the cereal, nuts, apricots and raisins.
Stir until all pieces are evenly coated. Microwave on High for 4 minutes; stir every minute.
Spread on waxed paper to cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: chicken-broccoli-cheese soup
directions: Melt 1 1/4 sticks butter or margarine in a Dutch oven.
Mix in flour and stir.
Mix in half and half and chicken broth.
Stir constantly over medium heat just to the boiling point.
Do not let it come to a full boil.
Add more chicken broth or milk to get the desired consistency.
Add to soup mixture the broccoli, which has been microwaved to desired degree of doneness with 3/4 stick of butter and a little water.
Mix in Velveeta cheese until melted. (You may also add Cheddar cheese.)
Add desired amount of chopped chicken.
(I boil chicken breast in water and use the broth.)
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: meat loaf (quick)
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except hamburger and ketchup. Add hamburger last.
Make a loaf about 10 1/2 inches thick.
Top with ketchup.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix peanut butter, shortening, sugars and egg thoroughly. Measure flour by sifting.
Blend all dry ingredients; stir into shortening mixture.
Chill dough.
Heat oven to 375°.
Roll dough in 1 1/4-inch balls.
Place 3 inches apart on lightly greased baking sheet.
Flatten crisscross style with a fork dipped in flour.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen 2 1/2-inch cookies.

title: quick cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients and form into 1 inch balls.
Place on cookie sheet and bake for 10 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: piki(indian bread)
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls on a hot griddle or lightly greased electric skillet.
Good served with butter.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Invent your own combination:
Start with 1 item from each group 1-4, then add other items as listed.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in a mixing bowl.
Let set 15 to 20 minutes to blend flavors.
Yield:
1 1/2 cups.

title: parmesan fried chicken
directions: Mix flour, parmesan cheese and pepper together.
Dip each chicken breast into egg white then dredge in flour mixture.
Heat oil in skillet and cook chicken on each side for 5 to 6 minutes, or until done.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Mix all well. Make into small balls. Flatten with a fork. Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: honey-mustard salad dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender.
Process for
2 minutes. Pour into quart jar and chill for 1 hour before serving.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Cut broccoli and cauliflower into individual sized pieces. Mix remaining ingredients thoroughly and pour over vegetables. Let stand for 24 hours.

title: spring pea salad
directions: Rinse peas in hot water or steam if fresh.
Drain.
Combine vegetables, nuts and bacon with sour cream; mix dressing, mustard and garlic together.
Pour over salad mixture.
Toss gently. Chill.
Macadamia nuts or salted sunflower seeds are a good alternative.
Serves 4.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix Cool Whip, condensed milk and frozen lemonade. Pour in prepared pie shells. Refrigerate 30 minutes. Overnight is good too. Eat and enjoy. Wonderful dessert for unexpected guests.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown bacon, mushrooms and onion in olive oil until brown.
Do not let it get black.
Blend tomatoes, tomato paste, garlic, bay leaf, tomato juice, sugar and seasonings in a 2-quart saucepan. Stir in water.
Use very low heat until all things are blended. Add browned base to sauce mixture.
Slowly break ground beef into mixture (raw).
Bring to a boil; reduce heat to very low and simmer for 2 to 6 hours, depending on time limit.

title: old-fashion dumplings
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add 1/2 cup broth and oil, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened.
Turn dough out on floured surface and form into a ball.

title: texas caviar
directions: Combine ingredients.
Cover and chill.
Serve with blue corn chips.

title: grilled flank steak
directions: Trim excess fat from steak.
Score on both sides in 1 1/2-inch squares. Place in large shallow dish.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Stir well.
Pour over steak and marinate 8 hours, turning occasionally.
Drain steak, reserving marinade.
Grill over medium coals 7 to 9 minutes on each side, basting twice with marinade.
To serve, slice across grain into thin slices.
Makes approximately 6 servings.

title: sugar cake
directions: Cream sugar, egg and butter, then add the rest of the ingredients and beat until well blended.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chicken pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Place chicken in pan.
Mix together chicken soup and broth; pour over chicken.
Arrange carrots and peas over top.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Combine the cucumbers, onion, and green pepper in a large bowl. Add the sugar, vinegar, salt, and celery seed; mix well. Cover and refrigerate for at least 24 hours before serving.

title: rhubarb bread
directions: Mix together and pour into two greased and floured loaf pans. Sprinkle with mixture of 1/4 cup sugar, 1/2 tablespoon butter and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Mix the cornbread by directions.
Cool, then crumble.
If you make your own cornbread, fix a 10-inch cast-iron skillet with a thick pone.
Add 2 tablespoons sugar, if not using mix.

title: spinach salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add cold water.
Stir in vinegar and mayonnaise.
Stir well.
Cool.
Add well drained spinach.
Fold in celery, onion and cottage cheese.
Pour into square pan.
Chill.
Double the recipe for a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: fudge pie(super easy and great)
directions: Melt margarine and chocolate in a double boiler; pour into a mixing bowl.

title: maw maw's ambrosia
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: quick supper rice
directions: Peel and finely chop the onion.
Heat oil in a frying pan and saute onion for 5 minutes.
Stir in salt, paprika and pepper, then add the diced ham and lunch meat.
Fry for 1 minute.
Add rice and mix thoroughly.
Continue to cook for 4 to 5 minutes to reheat the rice.
Add a spoonful of water if the mixture is too dry.
Stir in cheese and cook another 1 to 2 minutes until cheese begins to melt.
Sprinkle over the chives and serve hot with green beans. Serves 2.

title: meatballs
directions: Combine and make meat balls 3/4-inch in diameter and brown.

title: homemade kahlua
directions: In a large, metal bowl, combine sugar, instant coffee, boiling water and vodka; mix well and pour into glass 1/2 gallon jar.
Cut vanilla bean in half and place in jar (this bean can be recycled after it's ready.)
Let mixture stand in jar on counter for 10 days.
Shake every other day or so.

title: microwave cake
directions: Mix all ingredients
together.
Coat pan.
Cook on High for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Boil pineapple, sugar and lemon juice 5 minutes. Soak gelatin in 3/4 cup cold water; add to hot mixture. Let cool. Add other ingredients.

title: eight can casserole
directions: In a 2-quart casserole dish, combine all ingredients, saving enough noodles to sprinkle on top.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: For each serving, place one chicken breast in casserole. Cover each breast with cream of chicken soup.
Add slice of Swiss cheese and cover cheese with dressing.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake an additional 15 minutes.

title: puppy chow
directions: In a bowl, melt together margarine, peanut butter and chocolate chips.
Let cool 5 minutes.
Add the Corn or Rice Chex to mixture.
Put the powdered sugar in a large bag.
Add cereal and shake.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Mix 1 cup firmly packed light brown sugar and 3 teaspoons cinnamon.
Spread over batter in pan and swirl through with knife.

title: diabetic fruit salad
directions: Slice strawberries and bananas.
Drain canned fruits.
Use reserved juice to prepare instant pudding.
Stir all fruits into pudding.
Chill.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in a medium bowl.
Do this by hand with large spoon.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle a tablespoon of sifted flour over top.
Cover with top crust.
Bake in 425° oven for 10 minutes.
Lower heat to 325° and continue to bake for 30 minutes.

title: quick pate
directions: Mash liverwurst with fork.
Blend in the remaining ingredients.
Press pate into small bowl or 10-ounce custard cups. Chill several hours until firm.
Unmold pate onto a serving dish and spread with cream cheese mixture.

title: buttermilk chicken dinner(microwave)
directions: Whites of hard-boiled eggs, finely chopped, and mixed with the crumbled yolks and mayonnaise.

title: peach ice cream
directions: Mash peaches with fork until soft.
Add sugar, condensed milk, evaporated milk, vanilla and peaches.
Blend together and put into freezer container.
Add milk to full line.
Mix well before freezing.

title: dad's quick and easy hot cocoa
directions: In a microwave-safe cup, mix the cocoa, sugar, dry milk and water, mixing well.
Heat in microwave about 75 seconds, on full power should do it.
Add optional items.

title: cavatina
directions: Brown sausage.
Drain.
Cook pasta and drain.
Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts, about 30 minutes. Use a 2 1/2-quart dish.
Serves 8.

title: no bake fudge cookies
directions: Put all ingredients in saucepan and bring to a full boil. Boil for 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add 1/2 cup peanut butter and 2 1/2 cups Quick Quaker oats.
Stir until well mixed. Spoon onto waxed paper or greased dish.

title: horseradish salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water; cool.
When Jell-O starts to set, add whipping cream, mayonnaise and horseradish.
Blend thoroughly and chill; cover with regular mixture of lemon or pineapple Jell-O.

title: pot roast
directions: In 6-quart pan brown roast on all sides.
Spoon off fat.
Stir in mushroom soup, onion soup mix and 1 cup water.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and cook 2 hours.
Add vegetables.
Cover and cook for 45 minutes.
Remove roast and veggies and stir together flour and remaining 1/4 cup water until smooth.
Gradually stir into the soup mixture.
Cook until mixture thickens.
Pour over sliced roast on platter.
Serves 8.

title: cornwallis yams
directions: Mix all ingredients except coconut and pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Serves 12 to 14.

title: veal chops with tarragon
directions: In small saucepan, melt butter over very low heat.
Turn off heat and skim off foam.
Carefully pour off golden clarified butter and reserve.
Discard residue.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Roll chicken in onion soup mix.
Place rice in casserole dish. Add soup, water and salt.
Add chicken on top.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: grandpa reda's italian spaghetti sauce
directions: Simmer onion in oil (can use olive oil) until tender, then add garlic.
Empty contents of tomato sauce and tomato paste.
After you empty the tomato paste fill each can with water and add to sauce.
Stir to dissolve and then if it is too thick, add another 3/4 can of water.
After sauce (sugo) is mixed, add remaining ingredients, basil, parsley, bay leaf, sugar and pepper.
Simmer approximately 2 hours.

title: barbecue shrimp
directions: Cook all ingredients, except shrimp, until well blended, over medium heat, 5 minutes.
Turn off heat.
Add shrimp.
Mix well. Place pan in oven at 375° for 20 minutes.
Serve.

title: cherry fruit salad
directions: Mix milk and Cool Whip with cherry pie filling.
Add remaining ingredients and mix together.
Refrigerate.

title: shakertown chess pie
directions: Combine sugar and melted butter; then add eggs and remaining ingredients. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Preheat oven to 450°. Put pie in oven and immediately turn heat to 400° about 15 minutes, then at 300° about 25 to 30 minutes.
Filling of pie will puff up full.
Give a little jiggle to be sure center is firm before removing.
Pie may be browned before serving.

title: slow cooker spaghetti sauce
directions: Place ground beef in a large, deep skillet. Cook over medium-high heat until evenly brown. Stir in onion and garlic; cook 1 to 2 minutes. In a slow cooker, combine ground beef mixture, tomato puree, tomato paste, sugar, Italian seasoning and salt. Cook on low for 4 hours.

title: bambi's spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach and squeeze out as much moisture as possible. Mix all ingredients together thoroughly and chill 24 hours.
Serve with chips, vegetables or crackers.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix all together.
Bake in slow oven (325°) for 1 hour.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli 5 minutes.
Place a layer of broccoli and a layer of cooked chicken pieces in a casserole dish.
Sprinkle all over with garlic salt to taste.
Dot with butter.
Cover lightly with grated Cheddar cheese and sprinkle with almonds.
Mix soup, sour cream, milk, cup of grated cheese and sherry together and heat.
Pour over chicken and broccoli.
Sprinkle with paprika. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: barbecued beef sandwiches
directions: Cut away fat from meat and put in roaster.
Mix other ingredients and spoon over beef.
Bake in 300° oven for 5 hours or until meat is tender enough to shred.
Prepare and allow to set overnight.
Remove fat when ready to reheat and serve.
Serve on large buns.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Cream together sugar and softened margarine.
Add eggs, vanilla and salt.
Beat until smooth and creamy.
Spread mixture in baked pie shell and chill.

title: aunt sue's blueberry muffins
directions: Mix together flour, sugar, salt baking powder, and soda, Mix all liquid ingredients with eggs and pour over flour mixture. Stir only enough to mix.
Bake in muffin pans 350° until done.

title: date nut bread
directions: Put dates in bowl; sprinkle soda over dates.
Pour water over and let cool.
Mix all well together.
Bake at 350° in loaf pan for about 1 hour.
Double recipe for Bundt pan.

title: custard pie
directions: Combine eggs, sugar and salt.
Gradually stir in hot milk; add flavoring.
Strain before you put in crust.
Last, sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake the pastry about 3 minutes in oven before adding the filling.
Heat oven at 450° and bake pie for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° and bake around 25 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Do not overbake.

title: blueberry crunch cake
directions: Layer the ingredients in a large baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Sift together the soda, salt, flour and sugar. Add eggs and buttermilk, then add bananas. Stir in nuts.
Mix thoroughly. Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans. Bake at 325° about 40 minutes.
Makes 2 (1 pound) loaves.

title: broccoli puffs
directions: *If frozen, thaw and use without cooking.
If fresh, cook about 5 minutes.

title: hot spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach and drain.
Squeeze out liquid while draining. Mix all ingredients.
Chill 2 hours or more.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Freeze or refrigerate.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes, until golden brown.
If desired, roll in additional cheese.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Stir soda in applesauce.
Cream shortening and brown sugar. Add applesauce and flour, alternately.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: salmon with toast topping
directions: Melt butter or margarine in pan over medium heat.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Add salmon liquid and milk and cook until thick, stirring frequently.
When mixture has thickened, remove from heat; add salmon and cheese.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Place bread (cut in pieces) on top.
Bake at 400°
for 20 to 25 minutes until bubbly and browned.

title: creamy chicken tacos
directions: Saute green chiles and onion in butter.
Add flour and tomato juice; simmer several minutes and allow to cool.
Melt cheese with half and half in top of double boiler over hot water.
Dice chicken and add to tomato mixture.
Gradually add cream mixture.
Soften tortillas in small amount of hot oil.
Arrange alternating layers of chicken mixture in large casserole.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°, until thoroughly heated.
