Serves 4 to 6.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Drop from spoon onto greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: stuffed pumpkin
directions: Clean out pumpkin.
Brown hamburg; drain.
Make stuffing.
Add to hamburg; mix well.
Spoon stuffing into pumpkin; put cover back on top.
Place pumpkin in casserole dish or cake pan; add 2 cups of water to pan.
Bake at 350° for 3 to 4 hours or when fork sticks through pumpkin.
Serve with green salad and French bread.

title: orange-cranberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add cranberry sauce; stir to mix.
Add applesauce; stir.
Refrigerate to set.

title: chocolate truffle cake
directions: Melt butter and pour over chocolate to melt. Mix until chocolate is completely melted. Add eggs and mix well until all combined. Pour into 2 round, well-greased cake pans. Bake at 350° for 5 minutes. Place in the refrigerator overnight. Turn out onto cake plate. Serve with fresh berries and whipped cream.

title: boloney
directions: Mix ingredients well; let set 4 days, then grind again and stuff in cloth bags.
Cook real slow, just simmer, for 30 minutes. You can smoke it or paint it with liquid smoke.
Or, can it in wide mouth cans.
Put in 1/2 teaspoon liquid smoke.
Pressure cook for 1 1/2 hours at 10 pounds pressure.

title: fluffy rice
directions: Melt margarine in dish, add rice and all other ingredients. Stir well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, covered.

title: coffee cake
directions: Combine mix and sugar.
Beat milk and egg together. Stir into mix.
Turn over into 2 greased 9-inch layer pans.
Combine brown sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over batter.
Bake in a preheated 400° oven for 25 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Cream margarine and liquid sweetener, vanilla and egg; blending well.
Add flour mixture and beat well.
Stir in chocolate morsels.
Drop from spoon on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: never fail divinity(microwave)
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup, 3/4 cup water and salt in a 2-quart glass casserole.
Microwave on High for 19 minutes, stirring every 5 minutes or to 260° on candy thermometer.

title: cauliflower and broccoli salad
directions: Cut cauliflower and broccoli into pieces.
Add bacon pieces, cheese and onion.
Mix mayonnaise, sour cream and sugar.
Pour over veggies, mix and refrigerate overnight.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Combine everything but mushrooms.
Bring to a boil.
Add mushrooms and simmer 5 minutes.
Pour into bowl and refrigerate overnight.
Drain and serve.

title: peach-pineapple champagne punch
directions: Stir together pineapple juice and nectar with 2 cups water. Add champagne slowly and stir gently.
May garnish with orange and lemon slices.
Serves about 50 (4 ounce) cups.

title: sugar cookies(light, crispy and easy to make)
directions: Cream margarine and the sugars.
Add egg, beating well.
Add oil and beat until light and fluffy.
Sift together flour, salt, soda and cream of tartar.
Add to the first mixture and blend well.
Stir in vanilla extract.
Chill dough for several hours (overnight is best) until very firm.

Shape chilled dough into walnut size balls and place 2 inches apart on a greased cookie sheet or dip top of ball in a little water and then in granulated sugar and place on greased cookie sheet, sugared side up.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or as brown as you like.
Yields 3 1/2 to 4 dozen.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water and set aside.
Mix dry ingredients, in order given, cutting shortening as you do
for pie dough.
Stir in buttermilk, also the water yeast mix.
Blend thoroughly and dough is ready to be refrigerated in a large, covered bowl or made into biscuits.

title: houghton holiday punch
directions: Mix cranberry juice cocktail, frozen orange juice and ginger ale.
Mix spices together and add to liquids.
Mix well and chill.

title: artichoke balls
directions: Drain and mash artichokes.
Add all ingredients except cheese. Mix well.
Chill 4 hours or overnight.
Make into small balls and roll in grated cheese.
Heat until light brown in a 400° oven. Freeze well cooked or uncooked.

title: marinated vidalia onions
directions: Slice onions in thin, round slices.
Separate into rings; place in a shallow, covered container.
Combine water, sugar and vinegar; stir to dissolve sugar.
Pour hot vinegar mixture over onions.
Let stand, covered, overnight.
Drain well, squeezing out excess marinade.
Add mayonnaise and celery seed, tossing onions to coat well.
Chill.
Keeps in refrigerator, covered, for several weeks.

title: punch
directions: Combine sugar and water.
Boil 3 minutes and cool.
Mix bananas and lemon juice in blender.
Add pineapple juice; mix with syrup mixture.
Pour in milk cartons and freeze.
Pour ginger ale over frozen punch.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Combine sugar, water and spices.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and add butter.
Mix together the dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening.
Add milk and stir until flour is moist.
Roll small amount of dough in a big enough circle to cover an apple.
Place 4 slices of apple in middle of dough.
Sprinkle with sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg and dot with butter.
Wrap dough over apples.
Place in pan.
Pour cooked syrup over dough and apples.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: quick hot dish
directions: Mix all in a lightly greased 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 350° or until thoroughly heated.

title: no-roll pastry
directions: Sift directly into a 9-inch pie pan the flour, salt and sugar. Mix in a cup the vegetable oil and milk.
Pour over the flour and mix with a fork until no flour shows.
Press with your fingers to line the pan and sides as evenly as possible.
Fill and bake for any one crust pie.

title: banana breakfast cookies
directions: Melt oleo, stir in brown sugar, dry milk, and banana.
Mix thoroughly.
Quickly mix in soda, cream of tartar, and cereal. Drop on cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 12 minutes.

title: irish potato casserole
directions: Boil the potatoes. Refrigerate overnight or cool completely. Grate with coarse grater. Mix other ingredients with potatoes. Place in buttered casserole dish.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 300°.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: In saucepan combine sugar, cornstarch, salt, cocoa; gradually stir in milk, add oil. Cook and stir over medium heat until bubbly. Cook and stir 2 minutes. Remove from heat. Stir small amount of hot mixture into yolks, immediately return to hot mixture in pan. Cook 2 minutes stirring constantly. Remove from heat. Add butter and vanilla. Pour into cooled baked pastry shell (or baked cooled tart shells). Spread meringue
on top of pie and bake at 350° for 12-15 minutes.

title: toad in the hole(irish breakfast; sausage in batter)
directions: Fry sausage until lightly brown and all the fat has been rendered.
Place sausage in a 9-inch baking dish (glass dish). Place milk, eggs, flour, salt, pepper and melted butter into blender.
Blend for 1 minute until smooth.
Pour batter over sausage and bake, uncovered, in a 400° oven for 30 minutes. Batter will become puffed, golden brown and crisp. Serves 4.

title: crispy baked fillets
directions: Preheat oven to 500°.
Wash and dry fillets.
Cut into serving pieces.
Season.
Dip in egg whites and coat with corn flake crumbs.
Arrange in a single layer in a lightly sprayed shallow baking dish.
Bake for 10 minutes without turning.
Makes 4 servings.

title: scandia sardine spread
directions: In mixing bowl, mash sardines lightly with a fork.
Mix remaining ingredients in thoroughly.
Serve with crackers or snack bread.
Garnish with parsley and lemon slices.
Makes 2 servings.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients, except margarine (add it last). Pour into 2 (9-inch) unbaked pie crusts. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: punch
directions: Mix all together. Add ginger ale/lemon-lime, shortly before serving.

title: apple dapple cake
directions: Grease 9-inch tube pan with solid shortening and flour lightly. Set aside.
Sift flour and measure.
Resift twice with soda and salt.
Set aside.
Prepare apples and nuts.
Beat eggs, sugar and oil until thoroughly blended.
Add vanilla, apples and nuts to flour mixture and to egg, sugar and oil.
Stir good to make sure all ingredients are blended evenly into batter.
Bake in prepared tube pan at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Cool a few minutes in pan but while still warm, pour hot topping over cake.
Let cake remain in pan until almost cold.
Remove from pan.
Cut with sharp knife for neat slices.

title: lemon broccoli
directions: Prepare broccoli, wash and drain.
Split stalks.
Place in a large saucepan
with boiling water and salt.
Cover and cook until tender (10 minutes).
Drain.

title: tailgate baked beans
directions: Cook and drain meat.
Cook veggies in butter.
Add everything together and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: bean dip
directions: Heat in pan until the cheese is melted.
Serve hot with taco chips.

title: overnight casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in a covered casserole. Refrigerate overnight. Bake in 350° oven for 60 minutes.

title: one hour cinnamon rolls
directions: Put 1/3 cup of margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan and place in 200° oven.
Put hot water in a blender and add remaining 1/3 stick of margarine, sugar and salt.
Float 1 cup flour on liquid in blender.
Put another 4 cups of flour in a large mixing bowl.

title: egg custard
directions: Mix and pour into a buttered pie dish.
Bake about 30 minutes at 350°.
This pie will make a crust.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Boil first 4 ingredients for 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Spoon onto paper.

title: black bean salad(best if made 2 hours prior to serving)
directions: Combine cilantro leaves, sour cream, mayonnaise, lime juice and garlic in blender.
Blend until smooth.
Stir in lime peel, salt and pepper.
Pour dressing over salad and mix.

title: pineapple bars
directions: Beat together yellow cake mix, egg yolks and butter.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat together egg whites and sugar until stiff.
Spread over cake mixture.
Top with pineapple and coconut. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: special chicken and rice
directions: Prepare rice; keep warm.
Cook green pepper and onions in heated oil in covered skillet over low heat until tender, but not browned.
Blend cornstarch with a small amount of chicken stock. Add remaining stock and soy sauce.
Gently stir chicken and stock into vegetables.
Cook and stir until sauce is clear and thickened.
Serve on rice.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chicken stock(soup)
directions: Put all the ingredients in a large saucepan.
Bring to a boil and skim off any scum.
Cover and simmer over very low heat for 2 hours.

title: sounds bad, tastes good "scalloped potatoes"
directions: Wash, peel and slice potatoes very thin.
Slice Spam longways. Spray casserole with Pam or other cooking spray.
Start with a layer of white sauce, potatoes, then Spam, white sauce, potatoes and Spam until all is used.
Season to taste.
Bake in a preheated oven at 375° for 1 1/2 hours or until potatoes are done and Spam is crunchy.
Cover for first 1/2 hour.

title: strawberry soda pop cake
directions: When cake is cool, mix the following for the topping:

title: apple pancakes
directions: Put all ingredients, except apple, into blender.
Cover and process at low until blended.
Stop and add apple; cover and process at high only until apple is finely grated.
Pour into a hot, well-greased griddle.
Yields 10 to 12 pancakes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Mix applesauce and cream cheese together.
Add to jello.
Put in refrigerator until chilled (not set).
Add celery or nuts.
Fold in cranberry sauce gently. Refrigerate.

title: chicken with asparagus
directions: Saute green onions in 2 tablespoons margarine.
Add flour and stir until smooth.
Add milk and asparagus liquid.
Boil 1 minute. Add chopped asparagus.
Set aside.
Pound chicken until about 1/4-inch thin.
Season with salt and pepper.
Flour.
Saute in butter until done.
Place chicken in casserole dish.
Spoon asparagus mixture over chicken.
Sprinkle with Parmesan.
Brown lightly under broiler.

title: alabama pecan pie
directions: Put all together and mix well with rotary beater. Put in unbaked (homemade) pie shell and cook slowly, about 1 hour at 325°.

title: microwave brownies
directions: Grease 9-inch square baking dish.
Mix sugar, flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Cut in oleo until coarse crumbs.
Whisk eggs, oil and vanilla; stir in cocoa mix.
Beat 50 strokes. Spread in pan.
Microwave
on Medium (50%) power 5 minutes, turning halfway through.
Rotate dish.
Microwave on High for 2 1/2 to 3 minutes until center is just firm to touch.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: pancakes
directions: In large bowl, mix first 4 ingredients.
In small bowl, beat egg slightly.
Stir in milk and oil.
Add to flour mixture and stir just until flour is moistened.

title: corned beef brisket
directions: Rinse spices from vacuum-packed meat.
Trim excess fat from meat.
Place in crock-pot (slow cooker).
Cover with onions and garlic.
Mix other ingredients together and pour over meat.
Cook 8 or more hours.
Goes great with potato pancakes.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Add next 4 ingredients.
Mix these ingredients well by hand.
Grease and flour a 15 x 10-inch cookie sheet with sides.
Pour batter into pan and bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.
Take from oven and put a layer of miniature marshmallows on top; broil one minute.
Cool completely and frost.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook
broccoli. Combine first 5 ingredients in saucepan or bowl.
Add	cooked broccoli. Put into greased baking dish. Dot with
butter.
Sprinkle with Ritz crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pie meringue
directions: Combine last 3 ingredients until thick; add pinch of salt and 1/2 teaspoon of vanilla.
Cool this mixture.

title: pudding-chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugars and pudding mix.
Add eggs; beat well. Beat in vanilla.
Combine flour and baking soda.
Add gradually to creamed mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove to wire racks to cool.

title: gala punch
directions: Combine fruit juices and sugar; stir until sugar is dissolved. Add mint leaves; chill.
When ready to serve, pour in chilled juices, ginger ale and ice water in punch bowl.
Float lemon and lime slices on top.
Serves 30.

title: pecan tarts
directions: Cream together margarine and cream cheese.
Add flour, a little at a time.
Put in small muffin pans.

title: irish tipsy cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box; cool.
Prepare pudding as directed on box and add rum.
Use a small punch bowl and crumble enough cake to cover the bottom; cover with a thin layer of pudding and rum mixture, then a layer of Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Repeat these layers until all ingredients have been used, being sure the top layer is Cool Whip.
Cover with nuts and dot with maraschino cherries.
Do not serve for 4 days.
Keep refrigerated.
The cake will stay delicious up to 10 days.
I put cherries around the sides of the cake to make it look pretty.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Grease and flour three 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Cream sugar and oil together with electric mixer.
Add eggs; beat well.
Add pumpkin, water and nuts.
Mix well.
Sift together dry ingredients and mix into liquid ingredients only until moistened.
Add raisins. Spoon into pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.

title: electric skillet spicy roast
directions: Brown a 3 pound roast in an electric skillet.
Mix the remaining ingredients and pour over browned roast.
Simmer 3 hours in electric skillet.
Thicken with cornstarch, if needed.

title: tropical waldorf salad
directions: Combine bananas, apples, celery, dates and walnuts.
For dressing, blend together mayo, sour cream, lemon juice and ginger. Pour over fruit and toss.
Serve on crisp salad greens.
Sprinkle with coconut, if desired.
Serves 6.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together and press in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 7 minutes at 375°.

title: reuben sandwiches
directions: Mix mayonnaise and chili sauce. Spread on 6 slices of bread. Arrange cheese, corned beef and sauerkraut on bread slices. Top with remaining bread slices.
Grill in skillet with oleo.

title: chocolate pizza
directions: Melt Candi-Quik and chocolate chips.
Add Rice Krispies and peanuts.
Add marshmallows.
Spread in pizza pan greased with 1 teaspoon oil.
Place red cherries, cut in halves on top.
Then spread green cherries, cut in fourths on top.
Sprinkle with coconut.

title: cheese dreams
directions: Slice muffins in half, then toast and butter.
Place a tomato slice on each muffin.
Add 2 half slices of bacon, crisscrossed over the tomatoes, then place 2 pieces of cheese crisscrossed over the bacon.
Place muffins under broiler for about one minute or until cheese is melted.
Serve at once.

title: tuna cheese spread
directions: In a small bowl, combine all ingredients.
Mix well. Cover and refrigerate. If desired, garnish with chopped parsley.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: feed-an-army beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together and simmer on top of stove for 1 hour.
Very good served with hot biscuits.

title: broccoli and chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken and debone.
Cook broccoli in a little chicken broth.
Butter a casserole dish.
Put broccoli in first, cut-up boiled chicken on top of broccoli and then spread mayonnaise on chicken.
Mix chicken soup with a small amount of chicken broth and spread on mayonnaise.
Put cheese on top, then add herb stuffing on top and dot with butter.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: hardee's biscuits
directions: Measure a good 2 cups flour, baking powder, sugar and shortening.
Cut shortening into the flour mixture with a pastry blender until flour mixture resembles coarse cornmeal .
Add a scant 1 cup buttermilk to the flour mixture and mix well.
Turn dough onto floured surface.
Knead slightly and roll out with rolling pin. Cut with biscuit cutter.
Makes about 10 large biscuits. Bake at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven at 375°.
Pour can of peaches into long baking dish.
You may dice peaches or leave them in large slices.
Pour entire bag of plain cake mix over top of peaches.
Slice butter into think slices and completely cover top of cake mix.
Use extra butter if one stick is not enough.
Bake for 35 minutes, or until golden brown.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with brown sugar and bake for 5 minutes more (optional).

title: spam sandwiches spread
directions: Grate all together and serve for sandwiches.

title: preacher cookies
directions: Combine margarine, sugar and milk in a medium sized pot. Bring to a boil and boil for 3 minutes more.
Remove from heat and add oats, cocoa, vanilla and nuts.
Mix very quickly and drop on wax paper with a teaspoon.
Let set until firm.

title: tabbuli
directions: Rinse burghul with water; drain, then squeeze the water out. Place in a large mixing bowl, first finely chop the parsley, mint, green onions and tomatoes.
Place vegetables in layers on top of burghul in the order given, leaving dried onions on one half of the top layer and diced tomatoes on the other.
Add seasonings to the dried onions and mix thoroughly.
Add lemon juice and toss with spoon.
Just before serving, add oil and toss thoroughly.

title: fruit slushy salad
directions: Boil water and sugar for 3 minutes.
Allow to cool.
When completely cool, add fruit.
Freeze.
Usually ready to serve in 2 to 3 hours.
(Best if slushy rather than hard frozen.)
May be frozen in mold and floated in punch.

title: make ahead mashed potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes in salted water until tender.
Drain and mash. Add cream cheese, sour cream, salt and pepper, mixing well.
Put in greased 2-quart casserole or baking dish.
Top with pats of butter and sprinkle with paprika.
Potatoes may be kept in refrigerator for several days.
Before serving, bake uncovered for 30 to 35 minutes at 350° until heated through.
Serves 8.

title: peanut butter thumbprints
directions: Mix shortening, peanut butter, sugar and egg.
Blend in flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Cover and chill.

title: libby's d-lite
directions: Pour ginger ale in large punch bowl, add sherbet to your desired consistency.

title: coconut bread
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together.
Add eggs, almond essence, coconut, flour, baking powder, water and raisins.
Put this mixture into a greased and floured loaf pans (divide between 2 or 3 loaf pans, too much for one).
Make a little indentation in loaf, put reserved coconut and cinnamon and sugar into this indentation on top of the loaf.
Bake at 325° until toothpick inserted into loaf comes out clean.

title: italian cheese spread
directions: Beat cream cheese at medium speed until fluffy; add sour cream and dressing mix, beating until blended. Reserve 1 tablespoon Cheddar cheese; stir remaining cheese into cream cheese mixture. Spoon into a bowl. Cover and chill 2 hours. Sprinkle with 1 tablespoon reserved cheese; serve with crackers or party rye bread.

title: colonial lima bake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine ingredients in a heavy casserole or bean pot and bake 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: beef ravioli casserole
directions: Place oil in skillet.
Add ground beef and onion.
Place one can of ravioli in casserole dish.
Add half the beef mixture and 1/2 cup of cheese.
Repeat.
Place dish on a baking sheet and cook in a 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: delicious soup
directions: Chop all vegetables into bite-size pieces.
Add all ingredients into a large pot and bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer until vegetables are soft.

title: quick shrimp curry
directions: Cook onion in butter until tender but not brown.
Add soup; heat and stir until smooth.
Stir in sour cream and curry powder. Add shrimp and heat.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Add a sprig of parsley.
Serve over hot rice.
Offer curry condiments:
salted peanuts, chopped hard-cooked eggs, chutney and kumquat preserves. Makes 4 servings.

title: nacho dip
directions: Mix taco seasoning and refried beans together.
Add a little water to the mixture.
Layer in order listed in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Serve with chips for dipping.

title: eclair cake
directions: Mix pudding and milk.
Add Cool Whip and beat until thick and creamy.
Layer graham crackers and 1/2 pudding mix,
graham crackers and remaining pudding.
Top with graham crackers.
Cover graham crackers with chocolate frosting.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: baked deviled eggs
directions: Preheat
oven
to
Cut
eggs in half lengthwise. Remove yolks
and
mash.	Combine
yolks,
3 tablespoons sour cream, mustard and salt; mix well.
Refill egg whites.
Saute green pepper and onion in butter 5 minutes.
Stir in pimiento, soup and 1
cup
sour cream.
Pour sour cream mixture into 11 3/4
x
7 1/2-inch
baking
dish.
Place deviled eggs on top. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 20 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: after school shake(yield: 2 shakes)
directions: 1. Scoop ice cream into blender pitcher.

title: onion casserole
directions: Saute onions in butter and pour into buttered casserole.
Pour over this, soup and Pet milk, sprinkling in between with cheese. Top with buttered crackers and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: mary b's supreme chicken casserole
directions: Butter a 2-quart casserole with two tablespoons melted margarine or butter.
Blend remaining margarine or butter with cracker crumbs; set aside.
Combine in a separate bowl, chicken, sour cream, soup, chestnuts, mushrooms, onion powder, 1/2 cup chicken broth and all cooked celery.
(You may add more chicken broth for a thinner consistency if you prefer, however, this is optional.)
Taste the mixture; if more salt is desired, add a dash of seasoned salt to taste.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Place peaches in long Pyrex dish.
Add sugar, butter, cinnamon and water.
Cook 1 hour in oven at 350°.
Mix flour and milk and stir until lumps are out.
Pour over peaches; cook until brown. (Can cook for 15 minutes in microwave, then pour batter on it and bake in oven for 30 to 45 minutes).
Serve with vanilla ice cream.

title: chocolate peanut butter balls
directions: Mix
peanut
butter, margarine, sugar and Rice Krispies. Mix it with hands.
Then roll into small balls.
Heat chocolate chips and
paraffin
wax.
Dip
the
peanut butter balls in the chocolate mix.
Put on wax paper.

title: potato chip-tuna casserole
directions: Blend mushroom soup and milk, add onion.
Bring slowly to boiling point, stirring constantly.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Arrange half of crushed potato chips in bottom of casserole dish, (2 or 2 1/2-quart).
Top with half of tuna. Repeat layers.
Pour mushroom soup mixture over all and garnish top with whole potato chips.
Bake at 350° about 25 minutes or until thoroughly heated and lightly browned.
Yields 5 to 6 servings.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Pour in unbaked pie shell. Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: easy scalloped potatoes
directions: Mix together soups, sour cream and dry onion; stir in 2 pounds frozen hash browns and mix well.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: pumpkin float punch
directions: Four to 5 hours before serving, combine ice cream and 1 1/2 cups pumpkin.
Stir until well blended.
Freeze 2 hours.
Beat with mixer until smooth.
Tightly cover and freeze for 2 hours or until firm.

title: cheesy mashed potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes until tender and drain.
Mash potatoes and add remaining ingredients.
Put into a greased casserole and cover. Bake at 350 degrees for 40-45 minutes.

title: oyster stew
directions: Melt butter and saute leeks over medium heat, about 5 minutes. Add potatoes, water, salt and pepper.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Puree the mixture in a food processor.
Return to saucepan and bring to a boil.
Add cream, oysters and reserved liquid.
Cook several minutes.

title: icebox carrots
directions: Cook carrots until tender.
Make sauce, adding all other ingredients.
Chopped green peppers or onions can be added. Chill before serving.
Can be kept in refrigerator for 1 week.

title: nut puffs
directions: Mix together butter, sugar and vanilla.
Stir flour and nuts into mixture and form dough into small balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet and bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Mix all together.
Put into casserole dish.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mexican pork chops and beans
directions: You will need 1 Reynolds oven cooking bag, large (14 x 20-inches).

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger and add taco seasoning as directed on taco seasoning package.
Drain off liquid and chill for one hour or more.
Toss lettuce, tomatoes, olives and Cheddar cheese in a large salad bowl.
Crunch up taco Doritos and combine with the rest of the salad.
Pour dressing over the entire mixture and combine well using a spoon.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix and let set overnight.

title: candied yams
directions: Remove skin from baked potatoes.
Slice as desired.
Pour crushed pineapple with juice over potatoes.
Sprinkle sugar over. Place sliced butter over or on top.
Add vanilla.
Add grated orange peel, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Place in 350° oven 1 or 1 1/2 hours, until candied and brown.
Yields 4 servings.

title: diabetic cookies
directions: Crush crackers and mix with peanut butter.
Add sweetener, baking powder and egg yolk.
Mix well and stir in milk.
Form 6 balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Press with fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Yields 6 cookies.

title: new york cheese cake
directions: Mix and press into a 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Let cool.

title: cheese ball
directions: In one bowl, whip all ingredients with electric mixer.
This mixture will be soft.
Separate mixture to desired serving size and place in Saran Wrap in cups or bowl, depending on the size cheese ball(s) wanted.
Place in the freezer until firm, but not completely frozen.
You want the ball(s) to be soft enough to roll in chopped walnuts.
This recipe will make enough to get you through the holiday season because it freezes well.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Bake in uncooked pie shell for 45 minutes at 350°. Let cool before serving.

title: candy cane cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix thoroughly, butter, shortening, confectioners sugar, egg and flavorings.
Blend in flour and salt. Divide dough in half; blend food coloring into one half.
Shape 1 teaspoon dough from each half into 4 inch rope.
For smooth even ropes roll them back and forth on lightly floured board.
Place ropes side by side; press together lightly and twist.
Complete cookies one at a time.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Curve top down to form handle of cane.
Bake about 9 minutes or until set and very light brown.
Mix candy and granulated sugar.
Immediately sprinkle cookies with candy mixture; remove from baking sheet. Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: hush puppies
directions: Sift together first 5 ingredients.
Add egg, buttermilk and finely chopped onion.
When all ingredients are well mixed, drop by spoonful in deep hot fat.
Cook until well browned.
Proceed to eat your head off.

title: butterfingers(pecan sandies)
directions: Mix all ingredients except nuts.
After mixing thoroughly, add nuts.
Pinch off dough and roll out between your palms until the dough is about the size of your finger.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake in a slow oven (325°) until lightly browned. Remove and roll cookie in sifted powdered sugar.

title: chocolate nut clusters
directions: Melt chocolate chips and butterscotch pieces in top of double boiler over hot water.
Remove from heat, add noodles and nuts, stirring until evenly coated.
Drop by teaspoonful onto waxed paper.
Chill.
Store in refrigerator until ready to serve.
May be stored frozen also.

title: pumpkin nut roll
directions: Beat eggs on high for 3 minutes.
Gradually add sugar.
Stir in pumpkin.
In another bowl, mix rest of dry ingredients (not nuts).
Gradually fold in pumpkin mixture.
Spread into greased and floured cookie sheet.
Top with chopped nuts.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Turn out on dish towel; sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Roll up in towel.
Let set for 1 hour.
Unroll; fill with Cream Cheese Filling.
Re-roll and refrigerate.

title: vince's death by chocolate
directions: Make a chocolate cake in a rectangular pan.
After the cake cools, poke holes in it with a fork and pour Kahlua over the cake. Refrigerate the soaked cake overnight.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into 9 x 13-inch greased pan. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Store leftovers in the refrigerator and reheat to serve.
Serves approximately 12.

title: graham crackers and peanut butter
directions: Spread peanut butter on cracker and make a sandwich.

title: rhubarb crumble(has oatmeal crust)
directions: Save tablespoon of flour for rhubarb filling.
Sift flour, salt and 1/2 cup sugar.
Stir in oats.
Stir in melted butter or margarine until mixture is crumbly.
Press 1/2 of the oats mixture evenly over bottom and sides of 9-inch pie pan.
Combine rhubarb, 1/2 cup sugar, 1 tablespoon flour, cinnamon and water.
Turn into crust.
Sprinkle remaining oat mixture over fruit.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° until rhubarb is tender and crust is lightly browned, about 45 minutes.

title: picnic beans
directions: Brown and drain the first 3 ingredients.
Mix together all of the rest and place in baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, for first 1 1/2 hours; cover the last 1/2 hour (at 300° for 2 hours).

title: diet salad
directions: First, cook cauliflower according to directions.
Drain well.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Cream together eggs, oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix well; add nuts.
Pour into greased, floured loaf pan.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325°.

title: pasta with shrimp and peas
directions: Bring large pot of water to boil over high heat.
Heat butter in large skillet over medium-high heat.
Add garlic and shrimp; sprinkle with 1/4 teaspoon salt and cook, stirring, until shrimp are pink, 2 minutes.
With slotted spoon, transfer shrimp to small bowl.
Add clam juice to skillet; bring to boil.
Boil for 3 minutes.
Stir in cream, peas, 1/2 teaspoon salt and pepper; return to boil for 2 minutes.

title: "lite" banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding as directed. Stir in 1 cup of Cool Whip lite and set aside.
In a medium bowl layer vanilla wafers, bananas and Cool Whip mixture until all of the mixture is used. Top with remaining Cool Whip.
Serve after chilling, about 1 hour.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cut chicken into small pieces after baking.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Put into oblong baking dish.
Add topping.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown hamburger in skillet with seasoning (to taste).
In saucepan, put hamburger and add chili sauce and onion.
Simmer for 1 hour or more.

title: kolachi(nut rolls)
directions: Mix well.
Knead for 5 minutes.
Let rest for 30 minutes.
Cut into 4 portions.
Fill and let rise for 30 minutes.
Egg wash and prick with fork.
Bake at 350°
for 30 minutes.

title: green tomato pickle
directions: Slice tomatoes and onions.
Pour salt over both.
Mix thoroughly and leave overnight.
Pour off liquid in the morning and discard it.
Mix water and 1 quart vinegar.
Boil 20 minutes, drain and throw liquor away.
Take 3 quarts vinegar, sugar, cloves, allspice, cinnamon, ginger, mustard and green peppers.
Boil from 1 to 2 hours.
Put away in stone crock.

title: honey milk balls
directions: Mix honey, peanut butter and dry milk.
Form into balls with greased hands.
Roll in wheat flakes.
Chill until firm.
(You may use crushed cornflakes or wheat germ.) This candy is high in protein.

title: stir-fry sauce
directions: Blend on high in blender.
Lasts 3 weeks in refrigerator.
Use as sauce for stir-fry, as a steak marinade and in spaghetti sauce. Use wherever a little extra color and flavor is needed.
Great!

title: stuffed clams
directions: Chop the clams and add sauteed onion, crumbled bacon, bread crumbs, salt and pepper and heavy cream until creamy consistency. Bake at 375°
for 15 minutes.

title: shrimp creole and rice
directions: Dice onion, bell pepper and celery; saute in 3/4 stick of oleo.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce and cook for 30 minutes.
Add okra, cooked rice, shrimp and simmer for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: heavenly cheese salad
directions: Bring pineapple juice to a boil and pour over jello.
Cool. Add cream cheese, pineapple and nuts.
Fold in whipped cream. Chill and serve.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Lay chicken flat between 2 sheets of waxed paper.
Using a heavy cleaver or meat mallet, flatten each breast half to about 1/4-inch thickness.
Wrap one slice of ham and one slice of cheese around each breast half and place in baking dish sprayed with Pam. Mix soup and sour cream.
Pour over chicken.
Serve with rice. Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: cran-raspberry punch
directions: Mix all juices together.
Add sherbet.
Good for church receptions.

title: quick chicken and pasta
directions: Combine water and salt in a large saucepan; bring to a boil. Add vermicelli and peas.
Return to a boil; reduce heat and cook 10 minutes.
Drain and set aside.
Heat salad dressing in saucepan.
Add chicken and red pepper flakes; cook 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add pasta mixture and cook until thoroughly heated.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese, tossing well.
Yield:
2 servings.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put into buttered baking dish. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: pear honey
directions: Peel pears, core and grind up.
Place in large pan on stove. Add Jell-O (I use strawberry or peach).
Add sugar.
Cook until thick.
Have jars and lids ready.
After filling jars, turn them over for 5 minutes on the tops.
This will help seal them.
This is great with biscuits.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken breasts until tender.
Remove all bones and skin. Break into small pieces.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a casserole dish and bake at 350° for about 35 minutes.

title: jiffy chicken pie
directions: Place chicken in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Spread vegetables over chicken.
Combine soup and broth; pour over vegetables.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar.
Add egg and mix well.
Sift dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla.
Stir in apples.
If mixture is dry, add small amount of water.
Pour in greased oblong baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: cole slaw dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients. Store in container that can be shaken.
Oil and vinegar will separate.
This is also good for 3 bean salad or vegetable marinade, cucumbers, tomatoes, etc.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Debone and cut meat into bite-size pieces.
Melt margarine in skillet.
Add remaining ingredients, except chicken.
Pour into oblong baking pan.
Place pieces of chicken over entire top. Press down into liquid.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until rice is done.

title: carrot apple salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except salad greens.
Chill thoroughly.
Serve over salad greens.
Calories:
per serving, about 135.

title: mini white castles
directions: Mix ground chuck, onion soup, pepper, water, bread crumbs and egg.
Pack tightly on a large cookie sheet or 2 small ones, so that meat is about 1/2 inch thick.
Poke holes in meat with a fork.
Cook for 10 minutes at 400°; let cool.
Cut into squares the size of buns.
Put meat and pickles on buns.
Sprinkle top and bottom of bun with a few drops of water.
Place in pan.
Seal tightly with foil and heat at 350° for 15 minutes.
Serve.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Melt butter in large pot.
Stir in flour and cook over medium heat.
Gradually add chicken broth, stirring constantly.
Stir and simmer until it is gravy-thick.
Add seasonings.
Add chicken and vegetables and simmer until heated through.
Stir in sherry.
Pour into 2-quart casserole.
Stir together Bisquick and milk to make manageable dough.
Turn onto floured board and knead lightly until smooth.
Roll out to a circle large enough to cover the top of casserole.
Set dough on top of chicken mixture.
Bake at 450° until golden brown, about 10 minutes.

title: pineapple-lemon salad
directions: Boil together pineapple and sugar for 2 minutes.
Cream together Cool Whip and cream cheese.
Add pineapple mixture to cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Add jello, nuts, apple and celery (all chopped fine).
Chill until set.

title: shrimp roll
directions: Combine softened cream cheese, ground fine shrimp, eggs, sauces and salt.
Shape into roll about 2-inches in diameter. Combine chopped parsley and pecans and place in tray.
Roll shrimp mixture in parsley and pecans until well covered.
Chill.

title: baked ham
directions: In a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan, put the ham in and stick cloves in the ham. Next add the water, Karo syrup, brown syrup and then your vinegar.
Bake at 350° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: fried potato cakes(doughnuts)
directions: Blend potatoes and eggs.
Sift in sugar gradually, beating constantly.
Add buttermilk and melted butter.
Sift dry ingredients together and sift into potato mixture.
Chill dough 20 minutes.
Roll out on floured board to 1/2-inch thickness.
Dip doughnut cutter in flour before cutting out each doughnut.
Fry in deep fat or vegetable oil at 375° for about 2 minutes per side, flipping over when golden brown.
Makes 3 dozen.
A real old-time treat.

title: enchilada sauce(chili)
directions: Saute garlic in bacon drippings.
Add flour; cook 1 minute. Add bouillon to water, then add all seasonings and add to sauteed flour and bacon drippings.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
If your enchilada sauce needs thickening, add in small amounts at a time up to 1 tablespoon of corn meal.
Salt to taste.

title: taco casserole
directions: In a skillet, cook the ground beef and onion until meat is browned.
Drain off excess fat.
Add the taco seasoning mix to the meat and
cook
according to directions on the package. Combine the refried beans
and
cup
of
taco sauce.
Mix well. Layer the refried
beans
in
the
bottom
of a greased casserole dish.
Top with the seasoned meat, 3/4 of the cheese and tortilla chips.
Sprinkle
the
remaining
cheese
on top. Bake for 20 to 25	minutes
Remove from oven and top with lettuce and tomatoes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix mushroom soup, eggs, mayonnaise and cheese. Pour over broccoli in baking dish.

title: macaroons
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Drop from spoon on well-greased tin.
Bake in oven at 325° for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: crazy cake
directions: Combine ingredients. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mandarin chicken(use meat, poultry or seafood)
directions: Cut wings at first joint and discard the tips.
Wash and dry on paper towel and sprinkle lightly with garlic salt.
Mix cornstarch, eggs and water, stirring to form a smooth batter.
Dip wings in batter and deep fry in oil.
Let sit while making the sauce.

title: haystacks
directions: Melt chocolate in double boiler.
Add coconut, stirring until coconut is completely covered.
Spoon onto wax paper or greased cookie sheet.
Cool completely.

title: martha pafford's backbone and rice
directions: Cook backbones until tender, 1 1/2 hours.
Add rice and cook 20 minutes on medium heat.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: meatball subs
directions: Combine all of the ingredients and mix thoroughly. Roll into golf ball sizes. Bake at 425° for 20 minutes. Yields about 20 balls. Put in sub buns and top with cheese.

title: scalloped corn and broccoli
directions: Mix 1/2 stick butter, broccoli, corn, eggs and bread. Place in casserole dish. Crush crackers and add remaining butter. Crumble over top. Bake 350 degrees uncovered 30-45 minutes.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Mix macaroni, soup and diced cheese.
Put into greased baking dish.
Place cheese slices on top.
Bake at 325° until cheese on top is lightly browned.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease and flour 10-inch pan.

title: chocolate doodle cookies
directions: Microwave 1 cup of chocolate chips; stir until smooth.
Cool. Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat granulated sugar, butter and vanilla until crumbly.
Beat in melted chocolate.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well.
Gradually beat in flour mixture.
Stir in remaining chips.
Cover.
Chill until firm. Make 1 1/2-inch balls; roll in powdered sugar.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes on an ungreased baking sheet at 350°.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in refrigerator overnight.

title: mud pie
directions: Mix sugar, margarine, vanilla, salt, eggs, flour and cocoa in a medium bowl with wooden spoon.
Stir in nuts.
Pour in pan. Bake at 325° about 25 minutes.

title: heath bar cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on package in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. While hot, poke holes in cake and pour Eagle Brand milk over the top.
Let cool.
Ice cake with Cool Whip.
Crumble Heath bars on top of Cool Whip. Refrigerate.

title: microwave fantasy fudge
directions: Microwave margarine in 4-quart bowl on High until melted.
Add sugar and evaporated milk; mix well.
Microwave on High for 5 minutes or until the mixture comes to a boil, stirring after 3 minutes.
Add chocolate chips; stir until melted.
Add Marshmallow Creme and vanilla; blend well.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Let stand until completely cool.
Cut into squares.
Yields 3 pounds.

title: beef fried rice
directions: Brown meat; drain and set aside.
In a separate skillet, saute rice with seasoning packet and soy sauce, celery, onion and butter.
Stir in ground meat, water and tomatoes; simmer in a covered skillet 25 minutes and serve.

title: cranberry mold
directions: Make gelatin according to package directions.
Add cranberry sauce and sour cream.
Mix well with beater.
Let rest.
Pour in mold.
Chill to set.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: potato dumplings(repne halusky)
directions: Grate potatoes; add salt, egg and flour.
Mix well.
If dough is too stiff, add a little water (1/4 cup more or less).
Drop small portions from tip of spoon into boiling water.
Cook from 7 to 10 minutes.
Drain; rinse with cold water.
Serve with cottage cheese or cabbage.

title: creamy spinach dip
directions: Combine cream cheese and whipping cream in a little crock-pot. Cover and heat until cheese is melted (approximately 30 to 60 minutes). Add remaining ingredients. Cover and heat for 30 minutes. Serve with raw vegetables, crackers or bread pieces.

title: biscuits
directions: Sift flour; stir in oil.
Stir in milk (add more flour or milk for desired texture).
Knead dough; turn dough out on floured surface.
Roll to 1-inch thickness.
Cut out biscuits and place in greased bread pan.
Bake at 500° for about 20 minutes.

title: cream cheese roll-ups
directions: Melt butter and set aside.
Mix 1 cup sugar and cinnamon and set aside.
Cut edges from bread.
With rolling pin roll slices of bread until flat and thin.
Mix first four ingredients.
Put 1 teaspoon cream cheese mixture on each slice of bread and spread out.
Roll corner to corner.
Dip in melted butter, then sugar mixture.
Bake on cookie sheet 10 minutes at 350°.

title: sister lucy's cheese ball or loaf
directions: Take the Cheddar cheese (cut in small pieces) and put in blender.
Take the cream cheese. Knead together with hands.
Roll into ball or loaf. Can season with garlic powder or hot pepper. Chop chipped beef or shred. Roll cheese in chipped beef.
Wrap and refrigerate.
Slice and serve with dip and chip cracker, etc.

title: menudo
directions: Combine first four ingredients in a pot, with approximately 12 to 15 cups water, on low to medium heat, until meat and hominy (if using fresh) are done (approximately 4 hours).
Add chili and stir well.
Serve onions and lemon wedges (for juice) in separate bowls as an option.
Serve with crackers on side.
Yields approximately 3 to 4 servings.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add oil; mix well.
Add milk and yeast.
Work with hands or large spoon until all flour is mixed well.
Cover and refrigerate until ready to use or cook now. This keeps for several weeks.
I just make as I eat.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch cake pan with Pam.
Mix coconut and pecans. Put on bottom of pan.
Mix cake mix as on box.
Put on top of coconut and pecan mixture.
Mix cream cheese, butter and powdered sugar.
Put on top of cake.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix sugar and vinegar until sugar is dissolved.
Add Eagle Brand milk and mayonnaise.
Add macaroni, onions, carrots, celery and sweet pickles; mix well.

title: punch
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Add ginger ale just before serving. This can be doubled or tripled.

title: broiled venison chops
directions: Combine oil, Worcestershire sauce and onion in 9-inch square pan.
Place chops flat over top.
Spoon small amount of mixture over chops.
Marinate overnight, turning chops occasionally.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt 1 stick margarine.
Mix with graham cracker crumbs and pat into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat together eggs, 2 sticks softened margarine, vanilla and powdered sugar.
Beat on high speed for 15 minutes.
Spread over crumbs.
Layer pineapple and bananas and top with Cool Whip.
Decorate with cherries or nuts.

title: banana split pie
directions: Beat butter until creamy.
Add sugar; beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time.
Beat 3 minutes after each egg. Blend in vanilla.
Peel 2 bananas.
Fold bananas and chocolate into sugar mixture.
Turn into cooled baked pie shell.
Sprinkle with walnuts.
Chill 2 to 3 hours before serving.

title: spinach cheese puffs
directions: Cook spinach with onion according to package directions. Drain well.
Press out excess liquid.
In a medium mixing bowl stir together eggs, cheeses, salad dressing, margarine and garlic powder.
Stir in spinach and muffin mix.
Shape into 1-inch balls. Arrange on baking sheet.
Cover and chill until serving time. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.
Puffs can be served with Dijon mustard or sour cream as a dip.
Puffs will freeze and can be baked as needed.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Put popped corn in a large bowl.
Combine all remaining ingredients, except butter, in a saucepan.
Heat to boiling over medium-high heat, stirring often.
Cook, stirring constantly, to 250° on candy thermometer.
Remove from heat; stir in butter until melted and slowly pour over popcorn, stirring to coat.
Cool slightly.
Butter hands; shape into 3-inch balls and place on waxed paper.
Makes 8 balls.

title: oreo blizzard
directions: Soften ice cream; crunch up Oreo cookies and add the ice cream.
Stir well, then fold in Cool Whip.
Put in pan and freeze. Best if made the night before serving.

title: refrigerator rolls(no cholesterol)
directions: Put yeast and sugar in lukewarm water and set aside.
Put margarine in the hot water and stir until melted.
Add cold water to make it lukewarm.
Put the water with margarine in it in a large bowl with the sugar and salt.
Stir well.
Add yeast mixture and mix well.
Add flour and mix into dough.
Put some corn oil in a large bowl and put the dough into the bowl; turn it over to coat with oil to keep it from getting a crust on it.
Place in the refrigerator overnight.
When you want rolls, punch dough down. Pinch off small pieces and place in greased pan.
Place in warm place to rise.
Bake in a preheated 375° oven.

title: oatmeal pudding cookies
directions: Mix flour with soda. Combine butter, the sugars and pudding mix in a large mixing bowl.
Beat until smooth and creamy.
Beat in eggs. Gradually add flour mixture.
Then stir in oats and raisins (batter will be stiff).
Drop from teaspoon onto ungreased baking sheets, about 2-inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 7 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and dry jello together.
Add cheese and pineapple.
Stir well and chill in refrigerator.

title: rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a 2-quart casserole. Bake, covered, at 375° for 30 minutes, then bake, uncovered, for 15 minutes.

title: scrumptious chicken
directions: Cook noodles; drain.
Place in large mixing bowl.
Mix in soups, sour cream, chicken, mushrooms, broccoli, 1/3 stuffing and 1/2 chicken broth.
Turn into 3-quart greased casserole.
Combine remaining stuffing, butter and broth.
Place over top of casserole. Cover with foil and bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: impossible ham and swiss pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease a 10 x 1 1/2-inch pie pan. Sprinkle ham, cheese and onion in plate.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth, 15 seconds in blender or 1 minute by hand beater.
Pour into plate.
Bake until golden brown and knife inserted comes out clean.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: hello dolly squares
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch pan, melt butter, then remove from heat. Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs over butter.
Pour Eagle Brand milk evenly over crumbs.
Then sprinkle chocolate chips, coconut and nuts.
Press down gently.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: butterscotch candy
directions: Boil all ingredients until brittle when tested in cold water (290°, crack).
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: parmesan cheese potatoes
directions: Place potatoes in an ungreased 8-inch square baking dish. Pour butter over potatoes.
Sprinkle with seasoned salt, cheese and parsley.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 minutes.
Yield:
4 to 6 servings.

title: curried chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken breasts in salt water until tender.
Drain.
Cut chicken into bite-size pieces and place in bottom of a 1-quart casserole.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions until tender-crisp.
Drain.
Layer broccoli and chicken in greased, shallow 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Mix soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice in bowl.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with mixture of melted butter and bread crumbs.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until light brown.

title: tuna patties
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Divide into patties and fry in a small amount of vegetable oil.

title: baked chicken breast
directions: In large bowl combine first seven ingredients.
Place chicken in mixture and turn to coat.
Cover and marinate overnight in refrigerator.
Remove chicken from marinade; coat each piece with crumbs.
Place in shallow pan.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: won't last long cake
directions: Measure and sift dry ingredients together.
Add other ingredients.
Stir until mixed.
Do not beat.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Cool in pan. Sprinkle with powdered sugar (optional).
Cake will be very moist.

title: chicken chowder(microwave)
directions: In 5-quart casserole, cook chicken with 5 cups water for 25 minutes on High.
Remove chicken from bones and return to broth. Add next 6 ingredients and cook 30 minutes on High.
Add corn and cook on Medium-Low 10 to 15 minutes.
Broth may be thickened with 1/4 cup flour mixed with a small amount of liquid or Wondra flour.

title: granny's apple dip
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate for 2 hours.
Serve with Granny Smith apples, sliced medium thin.

title: quick apple cream loaf
directions: Combine applesauce, jam and lemon rind in a small saucepan. Simmer 30 minutes.
Chill.

title: cheese and fruit salad
directions: Mixer blend the cheese and topping together.
Put in Jell-O (dry) and beat.
Fold in the fruit.
Set 24 hours.
Serves 12.

title: meat rub seasoning for barbecue
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
If dry lemon powder is unavailable, use unsweetened lemonade powder mix.

title: tropical fruit punch
directions: Combine all ingredients except orange slices in large mixing bowl; mix well. Serve over ice and garnish with orange slices, if desired. Yield: 11 servings, 1/2 cup each.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except Ritz.
Top with crumbled Ritz crackers.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Heat all ingredients in pan until it starts to boil.
Fill quart jars and seal.
Turn upside down until sealed.

title: baked beans
directions: Cook bacon in saucepan.
Add other ingredients except beans and bring to a boil. Stir.
Add beans.
Pour into casserole and bake at 350 degrees until it bubbles.

title: brown rice
directions: Melt oleo in casserole dish.
Add onion, rice, consomme, water and salt.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Blend cream cheese (room temperature), peanut butter, milk and powdered sugar thoroughly.
Add Cool Whip and stir until smooth.
Pour into a crumb crust or a bakes pie shell.
Chill and serve with a dollop of whipped cream.

title: seafood salad
directions: Mix together crab, rotoni, carrots, red onion and cucumber. Arrange salad greens on 4 salad plates.
Mound seafood mixture on the plates and garnish with carrot curl and a fresh herb.
Serve with vinaigrette dressing.
Serves 4.

title: oven-roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Wash potatoes thoroughly; do not peel. Cut potatoes into chunks, 1-inch or 1 1/2-inches.
Place in a gallon-size Ziploc plastic bag along with olive oil and soup mix. Close bag and shake to thoroughly coat potatoes.
Place in shallow baking dish or pan (9 x 10 x 2-inch).
Bake about 40 to 45 minutes, stirring occasionally, until potatoes are tender and golden brown. Garnish with chopped fresh parsley, if desired.
Makes 8 servings.

title: taco sundaes
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Add taco seasoning, water and beans. Cook for 15 minutes.
Let guests build their own sundae in the following order:
steamed rice, meat-bean mixture, corn, lettuce, tomatoes, olives, cheese and salsa.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: rutabaga casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Place in a sprayed or buttered dish.
Cook at 350° about 30 minutes or until center is done.

title: italian tomato salad
directions: Mix all the ingredients except the oil.
Add enough oil to stir in to your taste.

title: stuffed zucchini
directions: Wash squash; cut off ends.
Cook in boiling water 5 minutes. Halve lengthwise; remove pulp with spoon.
Combine bread crumbs and other ingredients with pulp.
Fill zucchini shells; dot with butter and additional cheese if desired.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese.
Gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolk, beating well.
Add flour and vanilla.
Mix until blended.
Chill dough at least 1 hour.

title: rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in casserole dish and bake at 350 degrees for 45 - 60 minutes. Stir occasionally.

title: perfect pecans
directions: Beat egg white and water until frothy.
Add nuts and toss until coated.
Add all other ingredients and pour into a greased (use margarine) cookie sheet.
Bake 1 hour at 250°.
Toss every 15 minutes during baking time.

title: vermont green tomato pie
directions: Prepare pastry as directed below.
Place a layer of tomato slices on the pastry shell.
Combine the sugar, spices and cornstarch and sprinkle some of this mixture on top of the tomatoes; repeat layers until tomatoes and spices are used up. Sprinkle vinegar over top and dot with butter.
Roll out remaining pastry, fit on top of pie; flute edges together and make a vent slit.
Bake in a preheated oven at 425° for 20 minutes and then reduce temperature to 375° and bake for 40 minutes more.
Serve lukewarm with a slice of Cheddar cheese, if desired.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Drain salmon; drain and mash.
Add broken up bread that you soaked.
Beat up eggs and add other seasonings and mix well.
If too soft to roll, put cracker crumbs in a plate and take enough of mixture to make a ball and roll in crumbs to be firm.
Fry in enough grease, turning it twice so it will be golden brown.
Drain on brown paper.
Makes 5 croquettes.
Can be made into patty.

title: old-fashioned macaroni and cheese
directions: Boil macaroni until done; drain.
Heat oven to 350°.
Place cooked macaroni, cheese, salt and pepper in alternate layers in buttered oblong baking dish (11 1/2 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch), ending with a layer of cheese on top.
Pour milk over all.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until golden brown on top. Serve hot from baking dish.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: mexican dip
directions: In a large pie plate spread the cream cheese on the bottom. Next spread the beans over the cream cheese and then slice the cheese over the beans. Cover with wax paper.
Heat in microwave oven for 4 minutes. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: corn and oyster casserole
directions: Reserve liquid.
Keep separate.
Make cream sauce using Pet or Carnation milk and all liquid from oysters.
If more liquid is needed, use some from corn.
Mix with corn and oysters.
Top with buttered Ritz crackers, crumbled.
Brown lightly.

title: vegetable medley
directions: In a 9 x 12-inch baking dish sprayed with food release, layer 4 to 5 tomatoes (that have been quartered), layer the zucchini (sliced), layer the yellow squash (sliced), layer the onion (thinly sliced) and layer the fresh mushrooms (sliced).
Sprinkle on top of each the seasonings.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes uncovered.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese.
In medium bowl, beat cream cheese with a fork until smooth.
Gradually stir in pineapple, half of the nuts, green pepper, onion and seasoning salt.
Shape into a ball and roll in remaining nuts.
Wrap in plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight to let flavors blend.
Serve with party crackers, etc.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Line 9 x 13-inch pan with foil.
Roll dressing into fine crumbs.
Put in plastic bag.
Dip chicken in buttermilk, then in bag with crumbs and shake until covered.
Place in pan.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 1 hour in 350° oven or until done.
Yields 4 servings.

title: christmas wassail
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Turn down and simmer 30 minutes.
Keep warm to serve.
Serving size 1/2 cup; 79 calories, 0 fat, 0 cholesterol, 119 mg. sodium.

title: unbaked date balls
directions: Boil margarine, sugar, egg and dates 4 minutes on low heat, stirring all the time.
Add Rice Krispies and chopped nuts.
Roll in marble size balls and roll in coconut or powdered sugar.
Very good; large recipe.

title: spinach dip
directions: One teaspoon of chopped onions can be substituted.

title: tuna and noodles
directions: Boil noodles until done.
Drain and mix all the ingredients in a large bow.
It can be served hot or cold.
Use grated cheese if desired.

title: stuffed pork chops
directions: Note:
Use beer instead of water in Stove Top.

title: mexican dip
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet.
Melt Velveeta cheese in microwave oven.
Mix cheese and beef together in bowl and add picante or salsa sauce to your taste.
Dip Tostitos or tortilla chips.

title: nita's easy apple crisp
directions: Place peeled and diced apples in baking dish topped with sugar.
Combine other ingredients; mixture should look crumbly. Pour on top of apples. Bake at 375° for 35 minutes. Cool. Serve with Cool Whip.

title: mom, clara best's oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: seafood fancy
directions: Combine seafood, vegetables, mayo, Worcestershire, salt and 3/4 cup bread crumbs.
Put into a large casserole dish.
Mix remaining crumbs with melted butter and sprinkle on top of seafood mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until crumbs are browned.

title: cookie press butter cookies
directions: Soften or melt butter.
Mix all ingredients well.
Press onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 325° until firm, with bottoms lightly golden.
Cool cookies on a wire rack.
When cool, decorate with confectioners sugar and water and colored sugars.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix in order given, then pour into 9-inch pie shell and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Use frozen shell or a raw shell.
Either one works fine.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Boil noodles according to directions.
Drain.
Combine noodles, tuna, mayo, celery, onions, peas, green peppers and salt. Blend soup and milk and heat.
Add cheese and cook until cheese melts.
Add noodle mixture.
Pour in casserole and bake at 450° for 25 minutes.
Top with chips or French onion and brown.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Layer vegetables in order given.
Seal with mayonnaise.
Cover with cheese.
Sprinkle on sugar.
Cover and chill 24 hours.
Don't mix until ready to serve.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Put vegetables in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put diced chicken on top. Pour gravy over entire mixture.
Make stuffing mix as directed. Put on top of mixture.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: pineapple pistachio dessert
directions: Prepare pistachio pudding as directed.
Drain the liquid from the can of pineapple.
Combine the pudding and pineapple.
Let chill.
Serve with Cool Whip topping, if desired.

title: tavern spoon bread
directions: Combine water and milk; heat to simmer.
Add the cornmeal, salt, sugar and butter; stir over medium heat until mixture is thickened, about 5 minutes.
Remove from the heat.
Beat the eggs with baking powder until they are very light and fluffy, then add to cornmeal mixture, mixing well.
Pour into greased shallow baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: chess bars
directions: Mix together cake mix, egg and margarine.
Press in the bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan that has been greased.
Mix together sugar, cream cheese and eggs.
Spread on top of cake mix.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes or until browned.

title: marinated salad
directions: Cut ingredients into small pieces; mix together except for mushrooms and tomatoes.
You will add them before serving.

title: fried zucchini
directions: Mix all and drop by spoonfuls into hot grease.

title: cheesy potato casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes for 30 minutes. Mix all ingredients together. Put in a 9 x 13 baking dish coated with cooking spray. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until potatoes are tender.

title: chicken casserole
directions: In chicken broth, add bell pepper, celery, onion and spaghetti.
Cook until spaghetti is tender.
Put in long casserole dish.
Spread 1 cup cream of mushroom soup over top.
Cover top with cheese.
Bake at 375° until cheese is melted.

title: katrina's applesauce
directions: Cut and peel apples.
Put apples, sugar, cinnamon and water into pan.
Cover and cook at medium heat (simmering) for 15 to 20 minutes.
Let the apples cool, then mash them, with a fork or potato masher.
Enjoy!

title: caramel popcorn balls
directions: In the top of a double boiler, melt marshmallows and margarine.
Pour over a large pan of popcorn.
Butter your hands and shape the popcorn into balls.
Optional:
Dip popcorn ball in melted caramel candy and put peanuts on it.
Cool and eat.
Makes 20 balls or 40 small balls.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Combine together flour, nuts, melted butter and salt.
Press into the bottom of a greased 9x13-inch baking dish.

title: corned beef salad
directions: Make jello according to directions.
Add all ingredients but Miracle Whip and mix well.
Then add Miracle Whip and mix well. Pour in mold and chill.

title: apple cake squares
directions: Put apples, sugar and oil in large mixing bowl.
Let stand a few minutes.
Add everything else.
Stir so everything is glued together.

title: corn fritters
directions: Beat egg yolks and butter.
Sift first 4 ingredients.
Mix. Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into the batter mixture.
Add corn.
Bake in a greased frying pan over medium heat until golden on both sides.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Combine cake mix, egg, butter and water; mix well.
Fold in walnuts.
Spread on foil wrapped pizza pan.
Bake for about 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Spread on whipped topping.
Next, arrange fruit in circular pattern.
Heat apricot jelly and 1 to 2 tablespoons water until well blended.
Brush on fruit.
Chill at least 30 minutes.

title: meat loaf for the gang
directions: In large bowl, combine eggs, V-8 juice, onions, celery, bread crumbs, soup mix and pepper. Crumble beef over mixture, slowly mixing well. Shape into 4 loaves. Put in 4 loaf pans, setting 2 pans each into 13 x 9 baking pans. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: banana marshmallow ice cream
directions: Heat milk and marshmallows in a 3-quart saucepan, stirring constantly until marshmallows are melted.
Cool.
Combine banana puree and lemon juice.
Beat eggs until foamy in a large mixing bowl; gradually add sugar and beat until thickened.
Add cream, vanilla and salt; mix thoroughly.
Blend in marshmallow mixture, bananas and cherries.
Chill; churn-freeze.

title: zucchini snack
directions: Slice zucchini into
1/2-inch rounds.
Cover the slices with pizza sauce, sauteed
onions,
herbs,
chopped olives and cheese. Put under broiler until toppings are hot.

title: spiced raisin chews
directions: In large bowl, mix flour, cinnamon, cloves, baking powder, soda, salt and pepper until blended.
Finely chop raisins, almonds and apple.
Add to flour mixture and mix well (with hands is easiest).
In large bowl, beat eggs and brown sugar until thick and pale.
Stir into flour mixture and mix well.
Chill 1 hour.
Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease cookie sheets.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Place 2 inches apart on cookie sheets.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Let cool on sheet 1 minute before removing.

title: jalapeno corn bread
directions: Mix and bake at 400° until golden brown.

title: chicken salad
directions: Cut chicken into bite size pieces. Mix all of the ingredients and refrigerate overnight.

title: microwave divine divinity
directions: In 2-quart glass measuring cup with handle, combine sugar, syrup, water and salt.
Microwave on High 5 minutes.
Stir until sugar dissolves.
Cook on High 6 minutes.
In large mixer bowl, beat egg whites until stiff peaks form.
While beating at low speed, slowly pour hot syrup into egg whites.
Continue beating until mixture loses its gloss, about 10 to 12 minutes.
Blend in vanilla (and nuts, if desired).
Quickly press candy mixture into buttered 9-inch square dish.
Let stand until firm.
Makes 1 1/2 pounds.

title: twinkie dessert
directions: Split Twinkies and layer in a 9 x 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix Cool Whip and dry pudding mix until well blended.
Spread over Twinkies.
Pour strawberries and juice on Twinkies.
Poke holes in cake and let the juice run through.

title: turkey divan or chicken
directions: Cut turkey in thin pieces; set aside.
In medium bowl, mix soup, sour cream, vermouth and mushrooms.
Spread about 1/3 mushroom mixture in bottom of 12 x 8-inch dish.
Arrange turkey pieces, overlapping slightly.
Place broccoli on top.
Spoon remaining mushroom sauce over broccoli.
Sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 450° for 20 minutes.

title: quick and easy bread sticks
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add powdered milk, honey and salt.
Add flour, a little at a time, until mixture forms a ball. Knead.
Let rise 15 minutes.
Divide into 12 balls.
Roll each ball into bread stick.
Place on a greased pan.
Brush with melted butter and sprinkle with seasoning salt or garlic salt and Parmesan cheese, if desired.
Let rise 20 minutes.
In 400° oven, bake for 15 minutes.
Makes 12.

title: quick dessert
directions: Stir all ingredients together and freeze.
Serve frozen for a light refreshing dessert.

title: homemade spaghetti sauce
directions: Precook onion and garlic in olive oil, then add beef and pork cubes.
Add the rest of ingredients and simmer for 3 hours.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Makes 1 pie.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook noodles and rinse.
Combine other ingredients; pour over noodles and chill.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken and dice.
In a bowl, mix soup and sour cream. Pour this over chicken.
Crumble the crackers over the soup mixture.
Sprinkle this with the poppy seed.
Pour the melted margarine over the top of the crackers.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: milky way ice cream
directions: Beat sugar, eggs, flour and milk together. Heat slowly on low heat. Add "chopped" Milky Way bars; stir and cook until most of candy is melted. Add vanilla. Pour into ice cream freezer; add 1/2 gallon cold homogenized milk. Freeze and enjoy.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Brown ground beef in skillet; add onion. Add enchilada mix, tomato paste and water.
Simmer for 5 to 6 minutes.
Add beans and mix together.
Put in casserole dish and place in oven.

title: hot dill potato salad
directions: Melt butter over low heat. Stir in flour, dill, salt and pepper. Add milk all at once. Cook and stir mixture until it thickens and bubbles. Blend in mayonnaise and onion. Fold in cooked potatoes. Spoon into serving dish and sprinkle with paprika. Garnish with parsley. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown steak and onion in oleo.
Blend in flour and all other ingredients except sour cream and noodles.
Cook on low heat at least 1 hour.
Gently stir in sour cream and warm (do not boil). Serve over hot noodles.
Serves 6.

title: spinach tortellini soup
directions: Combine broth, water and bouillon. Bring to a boil. Add garlic, tomatoes and spinach and return to a boil. Add tortellini and boil for 5 to 10 more minutes.

title: johnny mossetti
directions: Chop pepper, onion and celery; saute in small amount of oil. Remove from skillet.
Add meat to skillet and cook until done. Cook noodles according to directions on package.
Drain, add soup, sauce and mushrooms to noodles.
Add meat, pepper, onions and celery to mixture.
Pour into casserole dish and top with grated cheese and sliced olives.
Heat in oven until cheese melts.
Makes a large amount.
It can be frozen.
I add picante sauce for spicy taste.

title: praline dream cookies
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt; set aside.
Cream until smooth butter and brown sugar.
Blend in and mix thoroughly egg, vanilla and dry ingredients.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 14 minutes. When cool, place pecan quarters on cookies.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: perfect meringue
directions: Beat egg whites and cold water at high speed one minute (until stiff
but	not dry).
Add cream of tartar and salt and beat one minute
at high speed.
Add sugar gradually and beat one more minute
at	high
speed.
Spread
on pie and bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine margarine, sugar, milk and cocoa in saucepan.
Boil for 1 minute while stirring.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter; stir.
Add oats; stir.
Drop by spoonfuls quickly onto waxed paper.
Cool.
Yield:
3 dozen.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Combine sugar, water and oleo in 2 cup glass cup.
Microwave on High 1 1/2 to 2 minutes until sugar is dissolved and oleo melts.
Place milk in blender; add microwaved ingredients and process until smooth.
Refrigerate until needed.
Makes 1 cup.

title: french onion soup
directions: Put water in large pot.
Add sliced onions.
Cook until onions are translucent.
Add beef broth, wine, pepper and bay leaf. Simmer until hot.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Blend sugar and oil.
Add eggs.
In separate bowl sift dry ingredients together.
Add half of mixture at a time and blend. Add pumpkin and nuts.
Bake in loaf pans (yields 2) at 350° for 1 hour.

title: onion potatoes
directions: Fill a 9 x 12-inch pan with sliced potatoes.
Take soup and water and pour over potatoes.
Cook at 350° until done (covered).

title: broccoli and corn scallop
directions: Saute onion in 1 tablespoon margarine.
Blend in flour. Gradually add milk; cook, stirring constantly, until thickened. Add cheese, stirring until melted.
Stir in corn and 1/4 cup crumbs.
Arrange broccoli in 12 x 7 1/2-inch baking dish.
Pour cheese sauce over broccoli.
Toss remaining crumbs and margarine. Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes. To make ahead, cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Place macaroni in pan and cover with water.
Add a little salt to water.
Cook until tender.
Drain off all of the water.
Place a layer in a baking dish; sprinkle with cheese, a dash of salt, pepper, another layer of macaroni, then cheese, salt and pepper. Beat 2 eggs; add a cup of milk and pour over macaroni.
Put a few pieces of butter on top; bake until thick and brown, for 20 to 30 minutes, at 350°.

title: beef 'n bean chimichangas
directions: In a skillet, brown ground beef; drain off excess fat.
Stir in tomatoes and jalapeno peppers and taco seasoning mix.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Using pastry brush, lightly coat both sides of each tortilla with oil.
Stack tortillas; wrap in aluminum foil.
Place wrapped tortillas in oven; heat for 10 minutes.
Remove tortillas, but leave oven set at 350°.

title: no sugar carrot cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: italian green beans
directions: Saute
chopped	onion
in
the	2 tablespoons olive oil until soft and lightly browned.
Salt and pepper to taste.
In large bowl,
place
green
beans, cooked onion, bread crumbs, cheese and
cup olive oil.
Mix well.
Place in greased, shallow baking
dish
or cookie sheet.
Spread out over large area, making 1-inch thick over the area.	Bake for 45 minutes in 350° oven.
Serves about 10 people.

title: raisin pie
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, salt and spices.
Mix well.
Stir in sour cream and raisins.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake in hot oven at 425° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 30 minutes longer or until knife inserted near center comes out clean.
Serve warm or chilled.

title: mexican stew
directions: Brown beef.
Saute chopped onion and green pepper.
Add beef mixture to undiluted soups.
Bring to a boil and simmer 10 minutes.

title: springerle
directions: Mix eggs
with	oil
and beat for 10 minutes.
Add powdered sugar,
1 cup flour and baking powder and mix well.
Add anise seed
and
rest
of
flour.
Mix
dough
in
morning and refrigerate until evening.	Roll out dough 1/4-inch thick (you may use special rolling pin to roll out dough, rolling pin has designs that
are	imprinted
on
dough).	Cut
into squares. Place on greased cookie sheets, liberally sprinkled with anise seed.
Let cookies set overnight.
Bake in morning at 325° for 5 to 10 minutes.
Cookies are done when bottoms are brown.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: The American Heart Association advises that you keep your fat intake to less than 30 percent of your total calorie intake.
But how can you tell?

title: salmon ball
directions: Mix all ingredients well, except nuts and parsley.
Roll mixed ingredients into a ball.
Chill overnight.
Roll in chopped pecans and finely chopped parsley.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix together with enough buttermilk to mix.
Bake in hot skillet at 500° until brown.

title: crunchy mixed vegetable bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine soup, mayonnaise, garlic and pepper in bowl and mix well. Stir in Cheddar cheese. Place frozen vegetables in 9 x 13-inch baking dish. spoon soup mixture over vegetables. Mix to coat vegetables evenly. Bake 35 to 40 minutes. Remove from oven. Sprinkle with fried onions. Return to oven 5 minutes or until onions are golden. Serve immediately. Yield: 12 servings.

title: apple and nut cake
directions: Mix oil, sugar and eggs.
Combine apples.
Add pecans and remaining dry ingredients to mixture.
Bake for 1 hour or longer at 300°.
Bake in a Bundt pan.

title: chicken marsala
directions: Cube cutlets.
Dip in bread crumbs.
Brown in margarine.
Add 1 can chicken broth and mushrooms.
Add Marsala wine to taste. Simmer covered 30 to 40 minutes, until mixture thickens.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Arrange 2 cups rhubarb in pie shell.
Beat egg whites until stiff, then beat in egg yolks until blended.
Mix flour and sugar; add to egg mixture.
Pour over rhubarb.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
This pie does not need a mearingue.
It will be crunchy as it is.

title: fresh herb dressing
directions: In screw top jar, combine oil, wine, lemon juice, sugar, basil, salt, bottled hot pepper sauce and 1/4 teaspoon pepper. Cover and shake to mix well.
Chill.
Shake again before serving. Makes 1/2 cup.

title: war cake(world war ii)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour an 8 x 4-inch loaf pan or an 8-inch square baking pan.

title: fry bread
directions: To the flour, add enough milk so the dough is mixed well and kind of sticky. Turn on floured board and add enough flour to dough so you can handle.
Pinch off dough according to how large you want the bread.
Pat the dough in your hands until it is about 1/4 to 1/2-inch thick.
Drop in very hot skillet of cooking oil. They will turn brown and float on top.
Turn over to brown the other side.
You will be able to tell when they are ready. This makes 10 to 12 medium size fry breads.

title: seafood chowder
