directions: In a Dutch oven or large saucepan, saute the onion in margarine until tender.
Add water, potato, carrots, celery, bay leaves, thyme and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer about 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Cube cod and stir in with 1 3/4 cups of the milk.
Stir flour into remaining 1/4 cup milk. Stir into chowder.
Cook until cod is opaque and chowder is thoroughly heated.
Add salt.
Serve sprinkled with parsley and a squeeze of lemon.
Makes 4 servings.
Serving size:
1 serving. Preparation time:
1 hour.

title: best-ever fruit cake
directions: Mix crumbs, sugar and baking powder; add remaining ingredients in order given.
Bake in tube pan for 1 1/2 hours at 275°. Increase to 350° and bake 30 more minutes.
Put a pan of water under cake while baking.

title: angel hair pasta with spices and cheese
directions: Add pasta to boiling salted water and cook until al dente (firm to the bite).

title: quick cucumber pickles
directions: Mix vinegar, sugar, water and spices.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Add cucumbers and onion rings, if desired.
Boil 5 minutes.
Pack cucumber chunks in jars; cover with hot syrup and seal immediately.
Or, store in jars in refrigerator.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Put all ingredients in a bowl and beat 10 minutes.
Put into well-greased and floured angel food pan and bake for 50 minutes at 350° to 375°.
Serve with whipped cream or powdered sugar.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Combine sugar, butter, cocoa and milk.
Bring to a rolling boil.
Boil for 3 minutes.
Add peanut butter and oatmeal.
Mix well and spoon onto waxed paper.

title: jumbles
directions: Mix together lard and sugar.
Add 1 egg and beat.
Blend together with flour, soda and salt.
Add buttermilk and vanilla and blend well.
Drop by teaspoon and sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon or red hots.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 400°.
Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Shake pieces of meat in bag with flour, salt and pepper. Brown meat in butter and add stock that is mixed with water; simmer 20 to 30 minutes.
Stir in sour cream and heat thoroughly. Serve over rice or noodles.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Spray a 13 x 9-inch pan with cooking spray.
Blend baking mix and milk.
Turn out onto surface dusted with additional baking mix and knead about 20 times.
Pat or roll dough into 1/4-inch thick rectangle, approximately 8 x 14-inches. Spread with soft margarine and sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Roll as for a jelly roll.
Cut into 1-inch pieces. Place in prepared pan.
Bake 15 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: pumpkin nut bread
directions: Beat oil, sugar, eggs on high speed for 3 minutes.
Sift together dry ingredients, add and stir in remaining ingredients. Beat until batter is smooth.
Pour into 3 x 6 or 9 x 5 loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Double batch will give you 12
3 x 6 pans.

title: easy fruit salad
directions: Combine all fruits in a large bowl.
In a small bowl, combine pineapple juice and pudding mix; mix well.
Pour over fruits and gently stir until well mixed.
Chill before serving.

title: cheese ball
directions: Let cheese stand at room temperature for 15 minutes.
Then mix all of the ingredients together.
Refrigerate just long enough so that it can be rolled into a ball.
Roll in chopped nuts, your favorite.
Refrigerate until ready to use, overnight is best. Serve on a tray with Club crackers.

title: *broccoli casserole*
directions: Cook broccoli in about 1 cup of water for 5 minutes.
Drain broccoli and add cheese, mayonnaise, onion and mushroom soup.
Mix together and pour into a casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Just before casserole is to come out of the oven, sprinkle with stuffing mix.
Remove from oven when mix is brown.

title: dump cake
directions: Into ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan, add ingredients in order.
Do not stir, but spread each layer out evenly in pan.
Pour oleo over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Mix together the flour, sugar, baking powder and baking soda. Add shortening, orange juice and egg.
Fold in cranberries and nuts.
Bake in loaf pan at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix crushed pretzel sticks, 4 tablespoons sugar and oleo and spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 400° for 6 to 10 minutes. Cool thoroughly.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook the carrots in salted water until barely tender.
Drain. Mix all other ingredients and pour over warm carrots.
Cover and refrigerate overnight, turning carrots occasionally.
Drain carrots, but do not discard marinade liquid.
Serve carrots on lettuce leaf.
Leftover carrots may be stored in refrigerator 2 weeks.
Use remaining sauce on green salad.

title: oysters rockefeller
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Fill 4 (8-inch) pie pans with rock salt.
Place 6 oysters on each plate; set aside.
In heavy saucepan, heat 1/2 stick butter until foaming.
Add onion and cook until onions clear.
Stir in ingredients down to cayenne; add remaining butter.
Mix well and simmer a couple of minutes.
Spoon mixture evenly on oysters.
Top each with bacon piece and bake 8 to 10 minutes or until bacon is done.

title: czech sauerkraut
directions: Put sauerkraut and water in pot and start cooking.
Peel and shred potatoes. Add them to the sauerkraut, cooking on low. Cut the bacon in small pieces and fry until brown.
Add to sauerkraut. Put onion in skillet with bacon drippings and cook until clear. Add flour and cook a little longer.
Put onion/flour mixture into sauerkraut.
Mix well.
Continue cooking until potatoes are done.

title: lemon creme
directions: Make jello according to package.
Remove from heat, stir in milk.
Pour into mold, dessert cups or torte shells.
Sprinkle with lemon rinds.
Refrigerate until firm.
This is all the milk for 1 day and 1/2 the jello.

If you want to dress up the dessert for company, cut a lemon in thin slices and cut through the slice to the center from one side and garnish each torte or cup (you may use lime jello and fresh lime slices).

title: cheesecake squares
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients; spread in 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix together remaining ingredients; spread on top of first mixture. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: cranberry cream cheese pie
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine Jell-O and sugar; set aside.
In a saucepan, bring cranberry juice to a boil.
Remove from heat and pour over Jell-O mixture, stirring to dissolve.
Stir in the cranberry sauce.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Meanwhile, in another mixing bowl, beat cream cheese, sugar, milk and vanilla until fluffy.
Fold in the whipped topping.
Spread evenly into pie shell.
Beat cranberry topping until frothy; pour over filling. Chill overnight.

title: hot rolls
directions: Mix dissolved yeast, sugar, eggs and warm water.
Add oil, salt and flour.
Let stand 8 hours or overnight.
Divide into 3 parts; roll out as if you were making pie crust.
Cut into eight sections the shape of pie wedges.
Roll wide edge into the point (like crescent rolls) and place on a greased cookie sheet.
Let rise six hours.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
Perfect for Sunday dinner.

title: spinach strawberry salad
directions: Toss spinach and strawberries together. Add dressing just before serving.

title: french fried apple rings
directions: Core and peel apples and slice into rings.
Preheat cooking oil 1/2-inch deep in frying pan.
Dip apple rings in batter and fry until golden brown, each side turning once.
Remove and drain on paper towel.
Immediately sprinkle lavishly with sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Serve hot.

title: mostaccioli
directions: Fry meat until brown. Drain.
Add all other ingredients except noodles.
Simmer 2 hours.
Cook noodles according to package directions.
Toss noodles with sauce and simmer 10 minutes. Serves 30.

title: oven-roasted snapper with vegetables
directions: Soak saffron in wine, mixed with bread crumbs.
Rinse fish inside and out and pat dry with paper towels.
With a sharp knife, make 3 deep vertical slashes, almost to the bone, on both sides of fish.
Sprinkle a little salt over each lemon slice and press a slice into each of the slashes.
Tuck remaining lemon slices into the belly cavity.

title: aunt coleen's delicious cornbread
directions: Put butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan in a 375° oven to melt while oven is preheating.
Mix together dry ingredients.
Add eggs and milk.
Turn pan to coat with melted butter as you pour butter into batter.
Stir just to mix thoroughly.
Pour into pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cranberry-apple sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in a small saucepan; bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat and simmer, stirring occasionally, 6 minutes or until chopped apples are tender.
Serve warm over pancakes or cold over ice cream.
Store sauce in refrigerator.
Yields 2 1/2 cups.

title: creamy peach pie
directions: Drain peaches and save the juice.
Add enough water to juice to make 2 cups.
Add the jello and jello pudding mix in saucepan and bring to full boil for 1 minute.
Put in refrigerator to thicken and set.
Add whipped topping and peaches.
Put in graham cracker crust and chill 2 hours or overnight.

title: zucchini quiche
directions: In a large skillet, cook zucchini, onion, butter, parsley and seasonings over medium heat about 10 minutes; set aside. In a large bowl, blend eggs and cheese. Stir in vegetable mixture. Separate dough into triangles and place over bottom and up sides of ungreased 10-inch pie pan or quiche plate to form crust. Spread mustard over crust. Pour in vegetable mixture. Bake at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes. Let stand 10 minutes before serving. Serves 6.

title: oreo cookie freeze
directions: Combine melted margarine and cookies; mix and spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Freeze.
Allow ice cream to soften; spread on cookies.
Refreeze.

title: deep south baked chicken
directions: Rinse chicken pieces; drain and pat dry.
Combine Bisquick, salt, paprika and poultry seasoning.
Dip chicken in evaporated milk.
Coat well with Bisquick mixture.
Arrange in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pour melted butter over top.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 1 hour.

title: deluxe chicken casserole
directions: Place broccoli in 9 x 13-inch pan (greased).
Lay large pieces of chicken on broccoli.
Cover whole pan with cheese sliced 1/8-inch thick over chicken.
Mix soup with mayonnaise and spread on cheese.
Lay on sliced water chestnuts.
Cover and bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Remove cover and add onion rings.
Bake, uncovered, 15 minutes more.

title: savory pork chops
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Wash meat in cold water and pat dry. In small bowl, mix mustard, catsup and vinegar.
Season chops with salt, pepper and onion salt.
Place in shallow baking pan.
Spread the mustard mixture over the chops.
Cover the chops with onion rings.
Bake, uncovered, in oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: chicken breasts diane
directions: Pound chicken breasts until even.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Heat 1 tablespoon each of oil and butter.
Brown chicken 4 minutes each side.
Remove to warming platter.
Add scallions to skillet with lime juice and brandy.
Whisk and add mustard and parsley; cook 15 seconds.
Whisk in broth until smooth, then remaining butter and oil.
Pour over chicken and serve.
Serves 4.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer in order:
lettuce, red onions, celery, green pepper, bacon bits and peas.
Spread mayonnaise across top.
Sprinkle grated Cheddar cheese across top.

title: real mincemeat
directions: In a large pan over medium high heat, heat to boiling all ingredients except grape juice and pastry; stir occasionally. Reduce heat to low and simmer for 30 minutes.
You may substitute apple pie spice or pumpkin pie spice for all spices listed.
If you think the mixture will be too thin, mix apple and grape juice to make 1/2 cup, if too thick, add 1/4 cup of the two juices mixed.
Makes 1 pie.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Beat oil and sugar together. Add eggs and bananas, beat well. Sift flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Add to first mixture with milk and vanilla.
Beat well, and stir in nuts.
Bake in 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan, lined on the bottom with waxed paper at 350° for about 1 hour.
Cool well and store airtight.
A good keeper, the vegetable oil and bananas keep it moist.

title: banana smoothie
directions: Peel bananas.
Wash and cut strawberry tops.
Put in blender with milk and yogurt and blend.

title: toasted cheese delights
directions: Place each muffin half, cut side up, on a baking sheet.
Top each with a tomato slice, cheese slice and crumbled bacon.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: whole chicken in a bag
directions: Prepare dressing of oil, garlic, thyme and lemon juice.
Rub the chicken with the dressing and add a bit of salt and pepper. Place chicken in cooking bag (Reynolds bag).
Poke hole in bag to allow steam to escape.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Serves 3 to 4 people.

title: mexican style stuffed peppers
directions: Remove cores from green peppers.
Boil in salt water for 5 minutes.
Saute onion in butter until golden brown.
Add meat and cook until well done.
Add flour and chili powder.
Stir.
Add tomatoes and simmer over low heat 20 minutes.
Stuff peppers with mixture.
Pour some liquid from peppers in baking pan.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Mix apples, cinnamon and sugar together and set aside. Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a cake pan.
Either loaf pan or tube pan may be used.

title: quebec meat pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Line pie plate with pastry.
Roll out top crust and set aside.
In a large frypan or Dutch oven, heat oil.
Saute onion until tender.
Remove and set aside.

title: my cinnastix
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Separate the dough into 8 portions. Fold over two of the corners of the triangular dough pieces so that it forms a rectangle. Roll the dough to make a tube, then twist the tube a couple of times, and stretch it a little longer. Repeat for all the dough triangles. Combine the butter, 2 1/2 teaspoons of sugar, 1/4 teaspoons of cinnamon and 1/4 teaspoon of vanilla. Combine 1/2 cup of sugar and 1 tablespoon of cinnamon for the coating in another bowl. Brush the melted butter mixture over the dough sticks. Toss the dough into the sugar and cinnamon mixture. coat the dough evenly. Then place them on a greased cookie sheet, spray the top of the sticks with cooking spray. Bake for 8 minutes or until golden brown.

title: easy sausage quiche(serves 8)
directions: Trim crust from bread to fit bottom of greased pan.
Brown sausage in pan and drain.
Stir in mustard.
Spoon mixture over bread.
Sprinkle on the cheese.
Combine all remaining ingredients and pour over bread and sausage.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until puffed and stiff.
Can be made ahead and refrigerated until ready to cook.

title: dietetic apple cake
directions: Place bread in blender; crumb.
Add milk, cinnamon and baking soda together.
Beat eggs until very thick and add rest of ingredients.
Add crumbs and apples last.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: salmon pie
directions: Cook potatoes, discard water and mash.
Cook celery in salted water until transparent.
Discard water.
Cook onions in butter until transparent.
Add onions, celery, celery seed, butter, salt, pepper, seasoning and milk, add to potatoes and mix.
Salmon (remove all skin and bones) break into small pieces.
Add to potatoes. Make crust from Bisquick.
Line deep dish pie plate with 1/2 crust.
Put potato mixture into pie plate, pile high. Cover with remaining crust.
Make several small fish out of pie trimmings.
Put fish on top with egg wash and brush top with milk and egg yolk.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: pudding cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shape into small balls.
Place balls on greased cookie sheet and poke with fork (flatten).
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: risotto
directions: Cook raw rice and onion in oleo and olive oil until onion starts to color.
Add chicken broth to which saffron has been added.
Cook, covered, over low heat, stirring often, until broth is absorbed and rice is tender.
Stir in cheese and serve.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Line bottom with bread.
Sprinkle with cheese, then sausage.
Mix together remaining ingredients; pour evenly over pan.
Chill overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: date bars
directions: Sift flour with baking powder, salt and sugar.	Combine dates and
nuts
with
flour
and
mix
well.
Beat eggs until light. Add butter, milk and vanilla, combine egg mixture with dry ingredients and mix
well.	Bake in greased 9 x 9-inch pan for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: saucy italian meatballs
directions: Soak bread in 1/2 cup water for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add eggs; mix well with ground meat, cheese, parsley, salt, oregano and soaked bread.
Mix together well.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Fry evenly. Simmer meatballs in favorite spaghetti sauce.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix sausage and cheese, then add Bisquick.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: chicken salad sandwiches(i remember a plate of these piled a foot high.)
directions: Note:
Amounts of ingredients may have to be adjusted to taste and consistency.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream butter.
Set aside.
Mix together sugar and cookies.
Add butter, eggs pecans and vanilla.
Blend well.
Pour into a Bundt pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Do not cut for several hours.

title: chocolate turtles
directions: Melt caramels, butter, and 1 Tablespoon of water over boiling water. (Keep warm over hot water.)
Melt chocolate, light corn syrup, and 1 Tablespoon water over hot water (not boiling). Remove from water.

title: lemon cake squares
directions: Mix together the dry cake mix, 1 egg, pecans and margarine. Spread mixture in bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread evenly.

title: mexican rice
directions: Fry rice in oil and brown.
Add garlic, onion, bell pepper and tomatoes. Simmer over low heat. Add salt and pepper.
Add water. Let it boil for about 25 minutes with the lid on over low heat.

title: green pea casserole
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients until tender. Add the remaining ingredients and pour into a baking dish. Top with crushed Ritz crackers and bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: chicken soup
directions: Place chicken, onions and water in a 12-quart pot.
Bring to a boil; lower heat and simmer for 2 to 3 hours, skimming off top as necessary.
Add remaining ingredients, except for dill and parsley; cover and simmer for 1 or 2 more hours.
If desired, soup can be strained at this point.
Add dill and parsley and cook for 15 minutes more.
Refrigerate overnight.
Skim off fat before reheating the next day.
Serve with Knaidlach.
Makes approximately 8 servings.

title: low-fat ranch dip
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Chill for about 4 hours.
Tastes better if made and chilled overnight.

title: top dressing for meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour over meatloaf and bake.

title: st. nick's salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Add partially defrosted berries, also the juice.
Pour into an 8-inch pan (or star mold). Chill in refrigerator until firm.
Combine the marshmallows and cream cheese; mix.
Add whipping cream; beat with beater until stiff.
Spread over gelatin mixture.
Chill thoroughly.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: lime marinated swordfish
directions: Place fish in a shallow pan.
In a small bowl, combine lime juice, zest, garlic, olive oil and cilantro.
Pour over fish and turn to coat thoroughly.
Cover and refrigerate for 2 to 3 hours. Drain fish and broil or grill until fish flakes easily with a fork, about 8 to 10 minutes per inch of thickness.
Serve garnished with cilantro.
This zesty marinade compliments any fish.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Cook tomatoes, onions and garlic bulbs until soft.
Put through a food mill and let stand overnight.
Drain water.
Add oil, honey, salt, seasonings and tomato paste.
Simmer until thick (about 6 hours).
Pour hot mixture into hot, sterilized pint jars. Seal and process in boiling water bath for 30 minutes.

title: deviled crab
directions: Preheat the oven to 400°.
Rinse the crabmeat under cold running water and drain, making sure to remove any filament or shell.
Spray the vegetable oil over the baking sheet 3 times to coat.
In a large bowl, combine all remaining ingredients, except 1/2 cup of the bread crumbs, and stir in the crabmeat.
Using 1/4 cup for each crabcake, form the mixture into 8 cakes.
Roll each in the reserved bread crumbs and place on the prepared baking sheet.
Coat the crabcakes lightly with the cooking spray.
Place the baking sheet on the bottom shelf of the oven and bake the crabcakes for about 5 minutes per side, until brown.

title: twenty-two minute cake
directions: In saucepan add butter, cocoa, water and Crisco; bring to a boil and pour over flour and sugar.
Beat well; add buttermilk, eggs, baking soda, vanilla, and cinnamon.
Beat until smooth. Pour into greased and floured jelly roll pan (11-1/2x16x1 inch). Bake at 375 degrees for 20 minutes.

title: low country boil
directions: Boil potatoes 30 minutes.
Add corn and 1 onion cut in half. Cook 15 additional minutes.
Add shrimp and cook until shrimp turns red.
Serves 50 people.

title: english butter toffee
directions: Butter a 10 x 15-inch baking sheet.
Combine sugar, butter and salt in a saucepan.
Place over medium heat and bring to a boil, stirring, until sugar dissolves.
Continue boiling, shaking pan occasionally until thermometer reads 305°.
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla.
Pour onto sheet.
Let stand until cool and hard.

title: pepperoni hot dish
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Add spaghetti sauce.
Stir in 1 cup cooked macaroni and 1 can mushrooms.
Add sliced pepperoni to the casserole mixture.
Heat thoroughly.
Place in casserole dish. Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Cover and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: sugar cookies(good in the summer)
directions: Cream together white sugar, powdered sugar, butter or margarine and oil.
Add remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight.
Form into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Dip in sugar.
Press with bottom of a tumbler.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 14 minutes.

title: nut pound cake
directions: Cream the butter and Crisco. Add sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time. Add flour alternately with milk, then flavorings.
Toss nuts in small amount of flour and add last.
Bake in tube pan about 1 1/2 hours at 275°.

title: minestrone soup
directions: Place raw meat in bottom of slow cooker, or in heavy kettle on stove top.
Add remaining ingredients, except cheese.
Stir to blend.
Cover.
Cook on low setting 10 to 13 hours, or 4 to 5 hours on High setting.
Garnish each serving with Parmesan cheese.
Makes 2 1/2 quarts.

title: cheese krispies
directions: Cut oleo into flour and cheese; add Rice Krispies.
Dough will be very stiff!
Make into small balls and press with a fork.
Put on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° but watch!
They brown quickly.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: On low heat in saucepan, melt the margarine and chocolate. Add sugar, Pet milk and vanilla. Cook and stir until thickened. Serve warm over ice cream.

title: grape salad
directions: Cream the cheese with pineapple.
Stir in all other ingredients; chill.

title: baptist pot roast
directions: Brown roast in a skillet with fat, turning once.
Put in a large roaster pan with potatoes (peeled and quartered), cabbage (quartered) and carrots (peeled and cut in halves).
Add other ingredients except Kitchen Bouquet and water.
Mix Kitchen Bouquet with water and pour over roast.
Cover roaster pan tightly.
Bake at 275° for 3 hours or until preacher's sermon is over.
(Forget about your dinner and listen to what he has to say.)
It smells so good when you walk into the house after church.

title: 3 bean hot dish
directions: Fry bacon, onion and hamburg; drain.
Add the rest of the ingredients and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: hershey's vanilla chip fruit tart
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Beat butter and confectioners sugar until light and fluffy.
Blend in flour.
Press mixture onto bottom and up side of 12-inch round pizza pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool completely.
Prepare Vanilla Filling. Spread on cooled crust.
Cover and chill.
Prepare Fruit Topping.
Cover and chill assembled tart.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: pineapple sheet cake
directions: Mix. Combine all ingredients.
Pour into pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until done.
Cool.

title: shrimp batter
directions: Beat egg and water with oil, then add dry ingredients.
Makes a delicious light batter.

title: broccoli with cheese sauce
directions: Trim off large leaves of broccoli and remove tough ends of lower stalks.
Wash broccoli thoroughly and separate into spears. Cook broccoli covered in a small amount of boiling salt water for 10 minutes or until crisp and tender.
Drain well and keep warm. Melt margarine in a heavy saucepan over low heat.
Add flour, stirring until smooth.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly. Gradually add milk and cook over medium heat, stirring with a wire whisk until thick and bubbly.
Add cheese, salt and pepper.
Stir until cheese melts.
Serve sauce over broccoli.
About 24 calories per serving plus 20 calories per tablespoon of sauce.

title: country potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes until tender.
Cool; peel and dice.
Saute onion and bell pepper in margarine.
Mix all and put into a 9 x 12 x 13-inch casserole.
Cover and bake for 30 minutes at 400°.
Remove cover and let brown 10 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Cook beef, onion and garlic until all pan juice evaporates and meat is browned.
Stir in chili powder.
Cook 1 minute.
Add beans, taco sauce and green chilies.

Place half of lettuce in center of large platter, then meat mixture on top of lettuce. Arrange tortilla chips around meat mixture, then cheese, tomato and remaining lettuce in separate piles on chips.
Top meat mixture with sour cream.

title: blueberry cake muffins
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, shortening and vanilla. Add milk. Slowly mix well. Add dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Mix blueberries in by hand. Batter will be thick. Fill paper lined cupcake muffin cups 1/2 to 3/4 full. Bake at 375° until light brown on top and toothpick is clean, about 25 minutes.
Makes 15 to 20 muffins.

title: spicy chicken breast
directions: Sprinkle chicken lightly with salt on both sides.
Place in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Pour melted margarine with lemon juice over chicken.
Sprinkle salad dressing on top of chicken.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tender.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, soda, salt and cinnamon together. Blend beaten eggs and sugar.
Add pumpkin and oil; blend well. Add flour mixture and nuts.
Make 1 large cake (tube or Bundt pan) or 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° about 60 minutes for large cake; about 50 minutes for loaf pans.
Frost if desired or pour glaze over top of warm cake.

title: melt-in-your-mouth blueberry cake
directions: Beat egg whites until soft peaks form.
With same beaters, cream shortening with sugar, beat in egg yolks.
Beat well.
Sift dry ingredients together; add alternately with milk.
Add vanilla. Fold in beaten egg whites.
Dust blueberries with about a tablespoon of flour; stir into batter.
Spread in 8 or 9-inch square cake pan.
Sprinkle with a little sugar or cinnamon-sugar. Bake 35 to 40 minutes in preheated 350° oven, until toothpick inserted into cake will come out clean.

title: triple cheese bread(bread machine bread)
directions: Be sure the yeast does not come in contact with the water or cottage cheese.
Cook on regular cycle (no time delayed).

title: no cook marshmallow frosting
directions: Beat egg whites and salt with mixer until foamy.
Gradually add sugar, beating until mixture is smooth and glossy.
Beat in Karo syrup, a little at a time.
Beat until frosting holds firm peaks when beaters are raised.
Fold in vanilla and food coloring, if desired. Will frost two 9-inch layer cakes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Simply mix!
Heavenly on chicken and spareribs.

title: grandma quinn's jumbles
directions: Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for about 12 minutes.

title: watergate salad
directions: In a bowl, mix packages of pudding (dry) with the pineapple syrup only.
Add pineapple and marshmallows.
Fold in the Cool Whip.
Chill for 2 hours.

title: chewy butterscotch bars
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add sugar and heat until dissolved. Add the eggs, one at a time and mix well.
Add vanilla and sifted dry ingredients.
Mix well and add nuts.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cut in bars when cool.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
If too juicy, add oatmeal, about 2 tablespoons.
It's best if you let it sit about 1 hour before you eat it.

title: mother's never fail cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add flour to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: carnival cake
directions: Position a rack in the center of the oven and preheat to 350°. Lightly grease the bottoms of 2 (8-inch) round cake pans; line each with a round of waxed paper trimmed to fit and then grease the paper and the sides of the pan.
Lightly flour, tapping out the excess.
In a large bowl, stir together the flour, brown sugar, granulated sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt.

Add the butter, vegetable shortening, milk, eggs and vanilla; beat with an electric mixer on medium speed for 3 minutes, scraping the sides of the bowl occasionally to make a thick, fluffy batter. Stir in the chopped (large
pieces) chocolate.
Divide the batter between the pans, smoothing the tops.
Drop each cake pan onto your work surface to level batter and remove air bubbles.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes until the top springs back when lightly touched. Cool in the pans on racks.
Run a knife around the edges and invert the layers peeling off the waxed paper.

title: wacky cake
directions: Add liquid ingredients to dry ingredients and mix.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pastrami dip
directions: Chop green onions; add to pastrami.
Mix cream cheese and meat together.
Mold into shape of your choice.
Serve with crackers.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients to dissolve yeast and sugar, about 30 minutes.
Cream together 1/2 cup sugar, shortening and salt until fluffy.
Add egg, then the yeast water and 2 cups more lukewarm water.
Beat flour in gradually; knead on floured board for 10 minutes.
Place in large mixing bowl and let rise until doubled in bulk.
Mix down well and put in refrigerator with cover. For hot rolls, make balls about the size of golf balls and put in greased pan.
Let rise about 4 hours.
Bake 20 minutes at 375° to 400°.
Dough will keep in refrigerator for 4 or 5 days and can be used for cinnamon rolls, etc.

title: ozark pudding
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and vanilla until light.
Stir together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Fold in apples and nuts.
Turn into a 9 x 9-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake in a 325° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: cabbage wedges(with veggie cheese sauce)
directions: Cut cabbage into 4 wedges.
Cook cabbage in lightly salted boiling water until crisp-tender; drain well.
Meanwhile, in small saucepan, melt margarine.
Add carrots and celery; cook until tender.
Remove from heat; stir in flour.
Gradually add milk. Cook until mixture boils and thickens slightly, stirring constantly.
Add remaining ingredients; stir until cheese is melted.
Place hot cabbage wedges on serving platter or in serving bowl.
Pour sauce over cabbage.

title: cherry pie
directions: Spray a 9x13 pan with cooking spray. Put 1 can of crescent rolls on the bottom of pan. Mix cream cheese with confectioners sugar. You can add a little milk to make the mixture creamy. Pour cream mixture on the rolls then pour the can of cherries on top of the mixture. Place the other can of crescent rolls on top with 1/2 c melted butter poured on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
In separate bowl, combine soup, mayonnaise, egg and cheese.
Place broccoli and cheese mixture in casserole.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and drizzle with melted butter.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted and top is browned (about 40 minutes).
One can of French fried onions may be added.

title: lemon-dill pollock
directions: Place fish in casserole dish.
Cover with layer of lemon slices.
Top with pats of butter.
Bake fish at 375°, uncovered, for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cover fish with cream of mushroom soup and sprinkle dill over soup.
Bake until fish flakes and is done, approximately 10 to 15 minutes.

title: cheese tortilla roll-ups
directions: Spread 1 tablespoon cream cheese on each tortilla.
Top with 2 slices of cheese and 2 slices of ham.
Roll up tightly in plastic wrap.
Refrigerate 15 minutes.
Cut each roll into 6 pieces. Secure ends with toothpicks.
Serve with salsa or picante sauce. Makes 24.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Serve with chips.
I use Old Bay seafood seasoning.

title: blacksmith chicken
directions: Arrange chicken,
meat
side
down,
in a well buttered casserole
dish
or
Dutch
oven.
Cover
with
carrots,
then potatoes.
Sprinkle
with salt and pepper.
Pour dressing over all.
Cover and bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Remove and turn chicken.
Add
broccoli and cauliflower;
cover again and bake 30 to 35 minutes more, adding green pepper, mushrooms and zucchini during the last 10 minutes.

title: diabetic fruit cookies
directions: Boil together for 3 minutes the raisins, dates and water. Cool.
Cream butter.
Add 2 eggs, sweetener and vanilla.
Add alternately with fruit mixture the flour, soda and cinnamon.
Mix all together.
Chill dough.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: red cabbage and apple salad
directions: Combine cabbage, apples and onion in a salad bowl.
Toss lightly.
Combine oil, vinegar, sugar, celery seed, salt, pepper and sour cream in a small bowl.
Stir until well blended. Toss dressing with salad until well coated.
Just before serving, toss salad again.

title: rum cream pie
directions: Beat egg yolks until light; add sugar.
Soak gelatin in cold water; put over low heat until dissolved.
Pour over sugar and egg mixture, stirring briskly.
Whip cream until stiff; fold into the egg mixture and flavor with rum.
Cool until the mixture begins to set, then pour into pie shell.
Chill until firm.
Sprinkle top generously with shaved bittersweet chocolate curls.
Garnish with whipped cream, if desired.
Serve cold.
Yields 1 pie.

title: sausage and egg souffle
directions: Cut 3 slices of white bread in 1/4-inch cubes (if using French bread, remove crust).
Grate cheese. Brown crumbled sausage and drain well.
Mix beaten eggs, milk, mustard and salt.
Stir in bread, sausage and cheese.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Refrigerate, covered, overnight.
Bake next day, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 10.

title: dirt
directions: Cream the cream cheese, butter and sugar; set aside.
In large bowl, mix milk, pudding and Cool Whip.
Add cheese mixture.
Layer with crushed Oreos.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Put sugar, milk, butter and cocoa into saucepan.
Bring to a boil and cook one minute.
Remove from heat and quickly add oatmeal, peanut butter, vanilla and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.
Let stand one-half hour until day.

title: pretty punch
directions: Mix drink mix in 1 gallon water in large bowl.
Add sugar and juices, mixing well.
Pour over sherbet in punch bowl.
Add ginger ale just before serving.
Yields approximately 40 servings.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream butter, peanut butter and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla. Beat well.
Add dry ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Form in small balls on cookie sheet and flatten with fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen.

title: sweet pepper burritos with guacamole
directions: In a medium bowl, mix the peppers, lemon juice, cilantro, cumin, chili powder and black pepper.
Let stand for 30 minutes. Meanwhile, in another medium bowl, mix the tomatoes, avocado, onions, lime peel and juice.
Cover and refrigerate the guacamole until needed.
Place the tortillas on individual plates.
Divide the pepper mixture evenly with the lettuce and jicama and roll up the tortilla to enclose the filling.
Serve with the guacamole. Serves 4.

title: easy blackberry cobbler
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Mix the rest of the ingredients together except the pie filling.
Pour over the melted butter.
Do not stir.
Spoon the pie filling onto mixture. Do not stir.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: lasagna
directions: Mix Ricotta, Mozzarella, egg, parsley and grated cheese.
In a 9 x 13 pan, spoon about 2 tablespoons sauce in bottom of pan. Layer uncooked lasagna sheets in pan.
Spoon the Ricotta mix on top, then sprinkle some chopped meatballs on top.
Spoon some sauce on top.
Then start again with the lasagna sheets, Ricotta mix, chopped meat and sauce.
Do a third layer of lasagna sheets, Ricotta mix, chopped meat and sauce.
Now place lasagna sheets on top and top with sauce.
Sprinkle with shredded Mozzarella and grated cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 30 to 40 minutes. Remove from oven and let rest about 10 minutes before serving.

title: heath bar ice cream
directions: Freeze candy.
Beat eggs by hand until fluffy.
Beat in sugar. Add creams and vanilla and mix well.
Pour mixture in ice cream maker and freeze.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Crush 1/2 of the strawberries with a fork.
Stir in cornstarch, sugar and lemon juice.
Cook over medium heat, stirring until mixture is clear and thickened.
Cool.
Cut the remaining strawberries in half.
Fold in cooked mixture.
Pour into pie crust.
Refrigerate until well chilled.
Garnish with whipped cream and serve.

title: corn bread for two
directions: Mix dry ingredients well. Add milk and egg(s).
Blend well. Add melted shortening and blend. Bake at 350° in whatever you choose, pan or skillet.
Let rise on bottom rack.
Place on top to brown.

title: date muffins
directions: Sift together the flour, salt, baking soda and sugar.
Add dates; combine well with dry ingredients.
Combine egg, vinegar and milk; stir in shortening.
Add to dry mixture all at once. Stir until dry ingredients are just dampened, not smooth.
Spoon batter into greased muffin pans, filling 2/3 full.
Bake in a 425° oven for about 20 minutes.

title: green beans and potatoes with swiss cheese
directions: Melt butter and blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Cook until bubbly.
Blend in milk.
Remove from heat.
Stir in onion and sour cream until mixed.
Mix sauce, drained green beans, potatoes and the Swiss cheese and turn into a buttered casserole.
Combine cornflake crumbs, bacon and butter and spread on top.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: patty's baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients except bacon together in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Lay the bacon strips on top of the beans.
Cover with foil and bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Remove foil
and cook at 350° for another 30 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: sauerkraut casserole
directions: Brown hamburger.
Throw in a bowl and don't drain.
Add uncooked rice, cream of mushroom soup, water, onion soup mix and sauerkraut; mix.
Bake in casserole dish at 350° for 1 hour without a lid.

title: cornmeal biscuits
directions: Cut shortening into flour, 1/2 cup cornmeal, baking powder and salt until resembles crumbs.
Stir in enough milk so dough cleans sides of bowl and makes a ball.
Knead dough on lightly floured surface for 10 minutes.
Roll to 1/2-inch thick.
Cut out biscuits. Sprinkle extra cornmeal on cookie sheet.
Place biscuits on cookie sheet; sprinkle more cornmeal on top.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Measure milk in saucepan. Separate eggs, yolks from whites. Beat yolks; save whites for meringue. Combine flour and sugar (1 cup). Heat milk until warm. Add egg yolks; stir. Add sugar and flour mixture to milk and eggs. Cook until mixture thickens. Remove from heat. Add vanilla, butter and brown sugar. I put 2 tablespoons instead of 1 1/2. Stir well. Pour into baked pie shell. Top with meringue of your choice.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Mix all together, adding broccoli last.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: crunchy salad
directions: Toast almonds and noodles until brown. Toss together. Can be prepared and kept separate, adding dressing to
mix as late as possible to preserve crispness.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream sugar and cream cheese.
Add peanut butter.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Cool in refrigerator.

title: strawberry pie recipe
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and water in a saucepan; bring to boil and thicken.
It will turn clear.
Remove from heat and add jello.
Let mixture cool 15 to 30 minutes.
Add strawberries and pour into pie shell.
Put in refrigerator to chill.
Serve with Dream Whip or Cool Whip.

title: prune cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Stir in oil, eggs, buttermilk and prunes.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cut into squares while hot.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Thin the
soup with a little white wine, a little thyme and onion powder.
Cook
vegetables
according	to directions. Drain; add cubed cheese, soup
and croutons.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chili sauce
directions: Burn a lighted candle nearby when preparing onions.
The candle burns away the onion smell gases and you can complete the job without tears.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Place container over low heat and keep turning pickles over until mixture reaches the scalding point.
Do not boil.
Place in jars while hot (first heating the jars).
Let stand 48 hours before eating.
Yield:
8 pints.

title: butter balls
directions: Add all ingredients in order as listed.
Mix until dough forms a ball.
Form into one inch balls.
Bake in oven at 400° for 14 to 17 minutes.
While hot, roll in confectioner sugar.
Cool and roll in sugar again.

title: cranberry-pineapple punch
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill. Serve with ice.

title: salsa dip with vegetables
directions: Soften cream cheese and mix with salsa until smooth.
Add to sour cream and soup mix.
Chill for at least 2 hours or overnight. Serve with sliced vegetables.
Yield:
2 cups.

title: mexican meat loaf
directions: Combine ingredients, reserving 1 cup tomato sauce.
Spoon mixture into pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Heat reserved sauce and pour over meat.

title: libby's famous pumpkin pie
directions: *For cinnamon, ginger and cloves, can substitute 1 1/2 teaspoons pumpkin pie spice.

title: black drum creole
directions: Clean fish well.
Score on each side at 1-inch intervals. Season fish well, using salt and pepper.
Squeeze lemon juice. Place in heavy casserole dish and set aside.
In a heavy pot, heat oil over medium heat.
Add flour and make roux.
Add seasonings. Saute until done.
Add tomato paste, tomatoes and water.
Blend well.
Cook over medium heat for 10 minutes.
Add rest of seasonings. Season to taste.
Cook approximately 20 minutes.
Pour gravy over fish.
Cook, uncovered, in oven for approximately 1 hour at 350°.
Add water as necessary to retain volume.

title: tastee franks
directions: Mix both ingredients in slow cooker and heat.
Very tasty.

title: italian chicken
directions: Marinate chicken (skinned or with skin) overnight in Italian dressing.
Roll in bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° (covered baking dish) 45 to 60 minutes or until done (depends on pieces used).

title: apple crisp
directions: Prepare apples in an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Mix dry ingredients and egg.
Makes crumb effect.
Sprinkle on apples.
Pour melted butter over top.
Bake at 375° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Peel eggs; cut in half and take out yolks.
Mix yolks, salt, pepper and mayo together.
Stuff eggs and sprinkle tops with paprika.

title: french onion soup for four
directions: Heat the butter in a large, heavy saucepan.
Add the onions; cover and cook over very low heat for 20 minutes.
Remove cover and stir in brown sugar.
Stir until onions are browned.
Stir in paprika and flour.
Add broth, thyme, salt and pepper; simmer, uncovered, over gentle heat for 30 minutes.
Preheat boiler; ladle soup into four soup crocks.
Place on a baking sheet.
Put a round of French bread in each and sprinkle with cheeses.
Place 4 inches from broiler and cook 4 minutes until cheese is bubbly and lightly browned.

title: snowballs
directions: Cook sugar, butter, dates and eggs.
Add 2 teaspoons vanilla, 3 cups Rice Krispies, 3/4 cup nuts (finely chopped) and 1/2 cup coconut.
Cool until you can handle.
Roll in balls and then roll in confectioners sugar.

title: company meat balls
directions: Mix beef, sour cream, soup mix, egg and crumbs.
Press mixture into a rectangle about 8 x 12 inches.
Cut into 48 pieces; form into balls.
Mix flour and paprika; roll balls in mixture.
Brown slowly on all sides in butter.
Blend soup and water; pour over meat balls.
Cover pan; simmer for about 20 minutes.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and freeze in a 9 x 13-inch dish.

title: kentucky pound cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, Crisco, oil, egg yolks and hot water; mix well.
Beat egg whites stiff.
Add to mixture.
Add pineapple, nuts and coconut.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Start in cold oven.

title: chili sauce
directions: Peel and mash tomatoes.
Add all ingredients except sugar and cook until half done.
Add sugar and cook a little more.

title: cheesy chicken casserole
directions: Layer in a 9 x 13-inch dish with slightly cooked broccoli. Next, add chicken.
Sprinkle with garlic salt.
Mix cream cheese and milk together.
Pour over chicken-broccoli mixture.
Sprinkle generously with Parmesan cheese.
Cover and bake at 350° for 15 minutes, then uncover and bake 15 to 30 minutes.

title: divinity swirls
directions: Blend sugar, syrup, salt and water.
Cook to softball stage.
Blend egg whites, add 1/3 cup boiled syrup.
Cook remaining syrup until it forms a hard ball, 280°.
Cook 1 minute.
Pour over egg mixture. Add vanilla and nuts.
Beat.
Put on waxed paper by teaspoons.
Cool.

title: italian zucchini pie
directions: Prepare pastry for a deep 9-inch pie pan.
Roll out, line pan and flute edges.
Spread horseradish mustard over the bottom of crust.

title: mushroom rice
directions: Saute onion and mushroom stems and pieces in oleo.
Add 1 1/2 cups rice and brown the rice, stirring often over medium heat.
Add the beef consomme and cook on low until all liquid is cooked out, about 30 minutes.
If cooked on top of stove, cover to cook.
(I use a nonstick electric skillet.)
Also, an iron skillet may be used.
You can also put the iron skillet, uncovered, in the oven at 350° and cook until liquid is gone, about 30 minutes.

title: mushroom stew
directions: Cut pork into 3/4-inch cubes.
Cut onion and peppers into bite size pieces.
Put all ingredients into a saucepan or crock-pot (including liquid from mushrooms).
I cut celery into 4 pieces so that it can be removed after cooking.
If you prefer, you can cut it into bite size pieces also.
If cooked in a saucepan, simmer for about 2 hours.
Serve with Italian bread and a salad.

title: ambrosia
directions: Combine all the ingredients and chill for three hours before serving.

title: chicken breast casserole
directions: Place chicken in bottom of dish.
Mix sour cream, cream of chicken soup and milk together.
Pour over chicken.
Melt margarine and mix with crushed Ritz crackers.
Sprinkle over top and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mexican fajitas
directions: Marinate
beef overnight in the refrigerator.
Stir-fry beef, onion
and	green pepper in skillet with a little of the marinade until done.
Warm fajitas in microwave for 1 minute. Serve with 1 tablespoon of meat mixture with toppings.

title: shrimp, chicken gumbo
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
Use
the
broth to start your gumbo. Put chicken back
into
broth
and
then add tomatoes, celery, onion,
green onions and bell peppers.
(Cook celery, onions
and bell
peppers in a little butter before adding to chicken
broth until
tender.)
Add okra, bay leaves, parsley flakes,
thyme, red pepper, garlic salt and flour.
(Put flour in
skillet and brown until real dark, almost black.) Salt and pepper to taste.
Cook until almost done, then add the shrimp. Serve over cooked rice.

title: monster cookies
directions: Cream together the butter and sugars.
Add the eggs, honey, vanilla and peanut butter and mix well.
Add the baking soda and oatmeal, stir well.
Then add the M & M's, chocolate chips, raisins and nuts.
To make large cookies for monster size cookies, use 1/4 c. dough per cookie, make sure to leave room for the cookies to expand during baking.
Or use a teaspoonful to make regular size cookies.
Bake at 350° for 9-12 minutes.
Since this is a large recipe, it is a good one to use to bake and freeze for later.
Or you can bake a few dozen and freeze the dough to bake at a later time.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Brown sausage; drain.
Separate rolls into 8 triangles.
Place on ungreased 14-inch pizza pan with points to center.
Press over bottom and up sides to form crust; seal perforations.
Spoon sausage over crust.
Sprinkle with potatoes.
Top with Cheddar. In a bowl beat together eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour into crust.
Sprinkle Parmesan over all.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Sprinkle 2 tablespoons sugar over berries.
Cool 7-Up, cornstarch and sugar over low heat until thick.
Add coloring. Cool before adding berries.
Pour in cooled pie shell and add whipping cream on top.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Add in order given, from flour to applesauce.
Mix well.
Then add beaten eggs.
Mix in nuts and raisins.
Bake in angel food pan at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: terri's chocolate-caramel cake
directions: While cake is hot from oven punch holes with wooden spoon handle and pour caramel sauce and Eagle Brand evenly over top. Allow to cool and top with whipped topping.
Keep cool until ready to serve.

title: lemon pudding cake
directions: Mix eggs, oil, water, pudding and cake mix together.
Pour in cake pan.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: chilled strawberry cake dessert
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 1/2 cups boiling water.
Stir in strawberries, sugar and salt.
Cool until it begins to thicken, then fold in Cool Whip.
Break up half of angel food cake into chunks.
Cover bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour half of mixture over top.
Break up other half of cake, form another layer.
Cover with other half of mixture.
Refrigerate 4 to 5 hours.
Cut into squares.

title: three flour braided bread
directions: In large bowl thoroughly mix 2 1/4 cups white flour, sugar, salt and undissolved yeast.
Add margarine.
Gradually add warm water to ingredients and beat 2 minutes at medium speed, scraping bowl occasionally.
Add 1 cup white flour.
Beat at high speed 2 minutes, scraping occasionally.
Portion equal amounts of batter into 3 bowls.
To the first add 2 tablespoons molasses and whole wheat flour, to make a soft dough.
Turn out onto lightly floured board and knead until smooth and elastic, about 5 minutes.
Cover and set aside.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Halve eggs; scoop out yolks into a bowl.
Use fork to crumble yolks.
Combine with all other ingredients.
Fill whites with yolk mixture.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
In a large bowl combine tuna, noodles, soup, then milk.
Mix well.
Put ingredients in a 9 X 13-inch pan or casserole dish sprayed with Pam.
Level.
Crumble crushed Pringles on top.
Bake at 375° until chips are golden brown.

title: french fried onion rings
directions: Soak onion rings in ice water for 30 minutes to 1 hour. Combine all remaining ingredients as batter.
Drain onion rings; dip in batter and fry in deep, hot oil.
When done, place on paper towels to absorb excess oil and serve.

title: pork chops ala easy
directions: Salt and pepper pork chops.
Brown them in the butter. Put chops in ovenproof casserole.
Cover with chopped peppers, onions, minced garlic and Italian seasoning.
Add stewed tomatoes.
Cover and bake in 350° oven for 50 minutes.
Uncover and continue baking 40 minutes.
Add cheese 10 minutes before taking out of oven. Excellent with linguine and garlic oil.

title: banana bread
directions: Beat sugar, Crisco and eggs until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into 2 greased and floured bread loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: favorite flapjacks
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add sour cream, flour, salt, sugar and baking soda.
Blend until smooth.
Cook on hot, lightly greased griddle until bubbly on top.
Turn and cook until brown.
Serve at once. Makes 4 servings.

title: shoe peg corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except margarine and cracker crumbs. Add salt and pepper to taste.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole. Melt margarine and stir in cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: molasses crinkles
directions: Mix together thoroughly shortening, brown sugar, egg and molasses.
Sift together and stir in remaining ingredients. Chill dough.
Roll into balls the size of a walnut.
Dip tops of balls in granulated sugar.
Place sugared-side up, 3-inches apart on greased baking sheet.
Bake until set but not hard, about 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.

title: baby zucchini and portabella mushrooms
directions: Heat oil in a pan until it begins to crackle.
Add garlic, salt, hot pepper and basil.
Add zucchini, mushrooms and tomato chopped into 1/4-inch pieces.
Cook for 4 to 5 minutes.
Splash with red wine or brandy.
Serve as an appetizer or main dish over pasta.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Cook and debone chicken. Chop chicken. Save 1 cup broth. Combine soups, chilies, Tabasco and broth. Cover bottom of 3-quart casserole with 2 cups Fritos. Spread half of chicken, half of liquid and half of cheese. Repeat layers. Cook at 350°, uncovered, for 30 minutes.

title: chinese chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese and noodles.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with cheese.
(Can be frozen at this point.)

title: hamburger soup
directions: Brown hamburger.
Pour in large Dutch oven pot.
Add tomatoes, 57 sauce, 2 cups water, cabbage and onion.
Cook for 1 hour and add remaining ingredients.
Cook for 2 more hours.
Any vegetables may be added. (I like to add macaroni to mine.)

title: pumpkin cheesecake
directions: Mix graham cracker and gingersnap crumbs, 3 packets Equal| and melted margarine in bottom of 8 or 9-inch spring-form pan; reserve 2 tablespoons crumb mixture.
Pat remaining mixture evenly on bottom and 1/2-inch up side of pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven until crust is lightly browned, about 8 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.
Reduce oven temperature to 300°.

title: snicker cake
directions: Put half the batter in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Melt caramels, butter and milk.
Spread over cake.
Sprinkle chips and nuts over cake.
Pour the rest of the batter on top.
Bake another 20 minutes at 250°, then 10 more minutes at 350°.

title: pot roast
directions: Combine all ingredients except potatoes, carrots and cream of mushroom soup.
Put the ingredients into a crock-pot with water and cook for several hours until meat is done.
Add potatoes, carrots and cream of mushroom soup.
Make sure there is liquid covering potatoes and carrots.
Add water if necessary.
Cook until potatoes and carrots are tender and serve.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: spicy sausage cheese dip
directions: Brown sausage and sprinkle seasoning on top.
Let it sit for 2 hours.
Add remaining ingredients to sausage in a micro-safe dish. Melt on High.

title: two corn casserole
directions: Butter a 2-quart casserole.
Put, in layers, 1/3 hominy and 1/3 corn.
Add pepper, salt and 3 tablespoons green chiles.
Dot with butter.
Add 4 tablespoons sour cream and 1/2 cup cheese. Repeat the layers of hominy, corn, seasonings, sour cream and cheese, ending with final third of hominy and corn.
Top with butter, pepper and grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: cheese potato soup
directions: Put first four ingredients and 1 teaspoon salt in Dutch oven or heavy kettle.
Bring to boil and simmer for about 15 minutes.

title: poor man's caviar
directions: Bake whole eggplant in 400° oven for one hour until it looks collapsed.
Then skin eggplant and mash with fork.
Lightly saute onion, celery, green pepper and tomatoes.
Add this to eggplant pulp and chill for two or three hours.
Yields about 2 1/2 cups.

title: chicken poppy seed
directions: Line bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan with chicken pieces.
Mix sour cream and soup.
Spoon over top of meat.
Combine melted butter, crumbs and poppy seed. Sprinkle over cream mixture.
Pour broth over all. Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: hockenberry casserole
directions: Dice onion and cook with ground meat until all meat is brown. Remove grease.
Into casserole dish, slice very thinly the potato. Add meat and onion mixture.
Sprinkle with uncooked rice.
Add tomatoes (partially chopped).
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes and onion; drain off half the water.
Add oleo, milk, ham, salt and pepper to taste.
Thicken with instant potatoes.

title: pig pickin cake
directions: Beat together the first 4 ingredients.
Pour into three (8-inch) cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Drain the can of pineapple.
Pour the pineapple juice over the cooked cakes to make them soggy.
Allow them to cool.
Then mix pudding, pineapple and Cool Whip.
Beat.
Ice and refrigerate cake.

title: buttermilk potatoes(so creamy!)
directions: Cook potatoes, covered, in boiling water, until tender, about 20 minutes.
Drain.
Preheat oven to 400°.
In a medium bowl, mash potatoes.
Add onion flakes, garlic powder, mushrooms, salt, pepper, thyme and buttermilk.
Mix well.
Place mixture in a 1-quart baking dish that has been sprayed with a nonstick cooking spray.
Sprinkle with wheat germ.
Dot with margarine.
Bake, uncovered, 15 minutes, until hot and lightly browned.
Makes 4 servings.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and let set overnight.

title: marshmallow heaven
directions: Drain cocktail and mix with pudding and other ingredients.
Let set in refrigerator for 4 to 5 hours.

title: italian spaghetti sauce
directions: Saut meat, onions, pepper, celery and garlic in oil. Add tomato paste, bay leaves, salt and pepper.
Cook slowly for about 4 hours.
Add hot water as needed.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix and store in jar.
Use 2 tablespoons of mix for each cup of tea.
Pour boiling water over mix.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Grease 4-quart baking dish.
Arrange bread, buttered side down in dish.
Beat eggs and other ingredients and pour over bread, along with sausage, ham or bacon.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.
(Let casserole get room temperature before putting into oven.)
Serves 8.

title: hawaiian burgers
directions: Grill your burgers to perfection.
Top with cheese, avocado, pineapple ring, onion and other desired toppings.
Aloha!

title: squash patties
directions: Mix all ingredients and fry in patties.

title: rice pudding
directions: In pan, mix the cornstarch with milk and stir until smooth. Mix in all the other ingredients, stirring constantly.
Cook until moderately thickened.
Remove from heat and cool, covered. Pudding will continue to thicken as it cools.

title: orange angel mold
directions: Day Before Serving:
Break angel food cake into small pieces. In saucepan combine gelatin, sugar and salt until well mixed; stir in 1/2 cup water.
Cook over low heat until gelatin is dissolved. Stir in orange juice.
Refrigerate until mixture mounds when dropped from a spoon.
Beat cream until soft peaks form.
Gently fold in orange juice mixture and food color to tint orange.
Oil mold.
Spoon 1/4 mixture, top with 1/3 cake pieces; repeat, ending with orange mixture.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Unmold; garnish with orange sections.

title: dirt pie
directions: Pour milk into bowl.
Add pudding and stir until blended.
Add Cool Whip.
Stir in crushed cookies and chocolate chips.
Pour into 1 medium flower pot, put gummy worms in at will and set a plastic flower (any kind you wish) in the middle.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
In another bowl mix butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Then add dry ingredients alternating with applesauce.
Add raisins and pecans.
Bake in a tube pan.
Bake about 1 hour in a 350° oven (little less to start with).

title: chocolate chip bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, mix flour and sugar.
Cut in margarine until crumbly.
Stir in 1/2 cup chocolate chips; press on bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes.
Combine milk, egg and vanilla.
Stir in remaining chocolate chips and nuts.
Spread evenly over crust.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes until light brown.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Press out crescent rolls on cookie sheet to completely cover pan.
Pinch edges together.
Bake at 375° for 11 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool.

title: key lime grilled chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients, except chicken, in blender. Mix well. Pour over chicken; marinate overnight (covered). Grill until done. Garnish with cilantro and lime slices.

title: applesauce cinnamon cake
directions: Mix sugar and cinnamon together.
Set aside.
Mix together cake mix, applesauce and eggs.
Put about 1 tablespoon sugar and 1 tablespoon cinnamon mixture in bottom of a greased pan.
Pour 1/2 the batter in pan.
Sprinkle on sugar and cinnamon mix, saving some for top.
Pour in remaining batter.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 375°.

title: pecan cookies
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add eggs.
Stir flour and baking soda together and gradually add to cream mixture.
Add vanilla. Stir in nuts.
Make dough into rolls in wax paper and chill thoroughly.
Slice 1/8-inch thick and bake at 350° for approximately 10 minutes.

title: mediterranean six layer dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, 1 cup Feta cheese and milk with electric mixer on medium speed until well blended.
Spread into 9 inch pie plate.
Top with remaining ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: flank steak pinwheels
directions: You will need toothpicks.

title: pecan tassies
directions: Cream together.
Wrap in plastic wrap and chill.
Shape into walnut-sized balls.
Press each onto sides and bottom of 1 3/4-inch muffin cups.
Fill with Pecan filling.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Cool.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: graham cracker pralines
directions: Separate crackers; arrange on cookie sheet.
Melt butter; add sugar and pecans.
Bring to boil and cook for 3 minutes; spread mixture over crackers.
Bake at 300° for 12 minutes.

title: fried catfish
directions: Cut fish into serving size pieces.
Combine cornmeal, flour, salt and pepper.
Beat eggs and water until blended.
Dip fish in egg mixture and then coat in cornmeal mixture.
Heat vegetable oil in skillet until hot.
Fry fish in hot oil until brown on both sides.

title: ham loaf
directions: Combine.
Bake 1 1/2 hours in a 350° oven.

title: artichoke cheese dip
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Place in baking dish; sprinkle top with garlic powder and parsley.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: spiced tongue
directions: Wash
tongue,
cover
with hot water and add seasoning. Simmer about 3 hours.
Let cool in liquid.
Trim excess tissue from the tongue and remove the skin.
Slice and serve.
It's a very good dish.

title: coconut custard dessert
directions: Combine pudding mix and milk.
Add ice cream.
Refrigerate 1 hour.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: Place salt pork and onions in large saucepan.
Saute until onions are golden brown.
Add 3 cups boiling water, potatoes and pepper.
Boil for 15 minutes or until potatoes are soft.
Bring fresh clams and clam liquor to boiling point.
Add milk.
Combine clams with potato mixture.
Bring to boiling point.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: chicken waikiki beach
directions: Wash chicken; pat dry with paper towels.
Coat chicken with flour.
Heat oil in large skillet.
Add chicken, a few pieces at a time and brown on all sides.
Remove as browned to shallow roasting pan, arranging pieces skin side up.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Meanwhile, preheat oven to 350°.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Press dough into a large 12 x 18-inch cookie pan, ungreased. Bake at 350° until golden, 10 to 15 minutes.
Cool.
Mix rest of ingredients together and spread on top of cooled dough.
Press chopped veggies into cheese layer.
Cool in refrigerator about 4 hours, but do not store overnight.
Crust could get soggy.
Cut into squares.

title: cherry fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.
Best if made the day before serving.

title: potato casserole
directions: Boil the potatoes.
Cool and grate.
Mix soup, sour cream, onion flakes, cheese, salt and pepper and potatoes together well. Put in casserole dish.
Top with corn flakes and butter.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: delicious cookies
directions: Note:
May use plain flour.
If so, add 3 1/2 teaspoons baking powder and 1 teaspoon baking soda.

title: choco-scotch clusters
directions: Melt chocolate morsels, butterscotch morsels and peanut butter in large pan over low heat, stirring constantly until smooth. Remove from heat.
Add Rice Krispies and peanuts.
Stir until well coated.
Drop by level measuring tablespoon on waxed paper or buttered baking sheet.
Refrigerate until firm or press in 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan and cut out.
Makes 4 dozen drop cookies.

title: vegetable enchiladas
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch baking dish with vegetable cooking spray.
Heat the vegetable oil in a frying pan. Then saute the onion and green pepper until tender.
Add cilantro and corn; heat for 5 minutes.
Add the refried beans (or mashed kidney beans) to the mixture and stir.
Fill the tortillas (or burritos) with the mixture.
Roll out and fold each one at the ends.
Place them side-by-side in the baking dish.
Cover the tortillas/burritos with the salsa, then the 2 cheeses.
Bake until the sauce bubbles and the cheese melts (about 20 minutes).
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: rice side dish
directions: Brown rice in oleo.
Stir often to keep from burning.
Add onion, chives, celery or green pepper and saute lightly.
Add about 2 cups water soup base and any other ingredients you choose. Simmer until water is gone about 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve with beef or chicken instead of potatoes.

title: shrimp vegetable dip
directions: Drain and mash shrimp.
Blend cream cheese and sour cream. Add ketchup, onion, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce and salt. Serve with fresh vegetables.

title: mama wiand's peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar and milk, bring to a boil.
Cook 5 minutes (no longer).
Immediately add marshmallow cream and stir thoroughly. Add peanut butter and stir thoroughly.
Pour into greased (or Pam it) 8-inch square pan.
Cool and cut.

title: reese bars
directions: Melt 1 1/2 sticks margarine with peanut butter.
Stir in cracker crumbs and powdered sugar.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan; press smooth.
Melt chocolate chips and 1 stick margarine together; pour over mixture.
Refrigerate.
Have bars at room temperature before cutting.

title: helen's crackers
directions: Mix all dry ingredients with oil and stir until completely dissolved.
Alternate crackers and mixture in a large plastic bag. Mix well and let set overnight.
Turn frequently until all oil is absorbed.
Serve with wine/cheese and dip.

title: graham crackers
directions: Mix together well.
Roll out and cut into 3 inch squares. Place on cookie sheet and bake at 350° until slightly brown.

title: sponge cookies
directions: Beat the eggs until very light; add the sugar and beat again. Fold in gently the flour, salt and baking powder sifted together. Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased pans, some distance apart.
Bake in 350° oven until set.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream together butter or margarine and sugar; add eggs.
Mix well.
Add 1 cup flour and 1/2 cup milk.
Put baking powder in remaining 1/2 cup milk.
Let bubble and settle, then add flavoring.
Add remaining 2 cups flour and milk with baking powder and flavoring.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours in greased and floured tube pan.
Do not open door during cooking.

title: olive cheese snacks
directions: Blend cheese and butter together until light and fluffy.
Add pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Stir in flour to form dough. Shape around olives, forming 1-inch balls.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet in a 400° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: ham and noodles
directions: Place green pepper, celery, onion and butter in a 2-quart glass casserole dish.
Cover and microwave 3 to 4 minutes.
Stir in remaining ingredients except cheese.
Cover and microwave 7 to 10 minutes, stirring once during cooking.
Stir in cheese.
Cover and let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: johnny m. casserole
directions: Cook ground beef until done and it loses its red color.
Stir in seasoning mix, tomato paste and water.
Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally. Cook macaroni as directed on package; drain.
Stir into the meat mixture the macaroni, corn and 1 cup of the grated Cheddar cheese. Turn into a casserole dish and sprinkle with the remaining 1 cup of cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until bubbly.

title: five flavor cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar until light and fluffy. Add eggs, which have been beaten until lemon colored.
Combine flour and baking powder; add to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Stir in flavorings.
Spoon mixture into prepared 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours, or until cake tests done. Cool in pan for about 10 minutes before turning out.

title: hot snappy snacks
directions: Put cheese, green pepper, onion and bacon through food chopper.
Add Worcestershire sauce and enough mayonnaise to bring mixture to spreading consistency, mixing well.
(Makes enough spread to serve 12 to 15 people.)

Lay bread slices close together on jelly roll pan or cookie sheet and spread with cheese mixture. At serving time, place in broiler (about 3 inches from heat source) until topping is bubbling and golden brown.
Serve immediately and be prepared to keep serving.
Pickles, any type, are good accompaniment.

title: beer battered fish
directions: Partially defrost fillets so they can be separated.
Cut into pieces about 3 x 1 1/2-inch.
Place on paper towels to dry.
Beat egg yolks until thick and light. Blend in beer, milk, flour and seasonings.
Mix until smooth.
Beat egg whites stiff but not dry; fold in.
Pat fillets dry.
Dip into batter, a few pieces at a time; lift out and drain slightly with fork or slotted spoon. Deep fry in cooking oil for 2 to 3 minutes until golden brown.

title: peg's marshmallow creme fudge
directions: Mix together the sugar, butter and milk; bring to a boil. Boil good for 9 minutes, stirring as it cooks.
Add chocolate chips, Marshmallow Creme and vanilla; mix well.
Add chopped pecans and mix.
Pour into a buttered 13 x 9-inch pan or drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.

title: karen's macaroni and cheese
directions: Have husband prepare per package directions.
Best when served to wife as she sits in easy chair.

title: my mothers caramel icing
directions: Melt butter in saucepan. Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Cook over low heat for 2 minutes, stirring constantly, until mixture boils. Remove from heat and cool 10 minutes. Gradually beat in confectioners sugar until icing reaches spreading consistency. Spread on cool cake.

title: seafood delight
directions: Cook rolls in jelly roll pan for 5 minutes.
Sprinkle partially baked crust with cheeses, shrimp and crabmeat.
Mix other ingredients and pour over; bake 25 to 35 minutes more.

title: beef louise
directions: Do not brown beef.
Mix all together.
Put in covered 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 325° for about 2 hours.
Leave lid on.
Serve on buttered noodles or rice.
The meat in this recipe is very tender.

title: cranberry sauce
directions: If possible, let cranberries and sugar stand overnight in refrigerator.
Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water, then add other ingredients.
Refrigerate.

title: chili
directions: Brown the ground chuck in a large skillet or saucepan.
Drain fat.
Put in the tomato sauce and water.
Add large spice packet; add salt and cayenne pepper.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Drain sausage and ground beef.
Mix ingredients together. Shape into 1/2-inch balls.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: cran-apple mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in cranberry sauce until melted.
Mix in applesauce.
Pour into oiled 5 cup mold. Chill until firm.

title: chocolate-apricot upside-down cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Heat 1/2 cup margarine in round pan (9 x 1 1/2-inches) or square pan (9 x 9 x 2-inches) in oven until melted. Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Arrange apricot and pecan halves on top.
Add enough water to apricot syrup to measure 1 1/4 cups. Beat mix (dry), syrup mixture, 1/2 cup margarine and the eggs in large bowl on low speed 30 seconds.
Beat on medium speed 2 minutes.
Pour 2 1/2 cups batter into pan.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until cake springs back when touched lightly in center. Immediately invert cake onto heatproof serving plate.
Leave pan over cake a few minutes.
Serve warm.

title: frozen cuke rounds
directions: Place cukes, onion and salt in a large bowl; cover with cold water.
Let stand 2 hours and drain.
Mix sugar with vinegar; pour over cukes.
Mix thoroughly.
Put into pint freezer containers and leave 1/4-inch space at top.
Freeze.

title: no shell coconut pie
directions: Mix well.
Pour into pie pan that you have sprayed with Pam. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chili cheese puff
directions: In a large
mixing
bowl, beat eggs well.
Stir in next five ingredients.
Add
green
chilies.	Pour
into
a greased 8-inch square baking
pan.
Bake
at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until a knife inserted near center comes out clean.
Serve immediately. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: french fried okra
directions: Slice okra, about like pickle chips.
Salt lightly.
Beat 1 egg well with 3/4 cup milk.
Dip okra in breading mix, then in milk mixture, then back in breading mix.
Fry in deep fryer at 350° until golden brown.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix everything together.
Put in buttered 9x13 pan.
Top with crushed potato chips.
Bake 1 hour at 375° or 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: fudgy brownies
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
In large saucepan, melt butter and chocolate over low heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add sugar.
Cool slightly.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating until well blended after each addition.
Stir in flour, vanilla and salt; add nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, or until inserted toothpick comes out clean.

title: lean pork sausage
directions: Combine dry seasonings, then mix into water.
Combine the mixture with the coarsely ground meat.
Please use the salt and water which produces a paste.
The meat mixture will be sticky. Wet hands with water for easier handling.
Be sure to follow this recipe exactly because cooking sausage causes 25% to 29% loss in weight which is mostly moisture.
Shape patties or create links with 31 to 34 mm pork casings.
Pork casings are found in most meat markets and supermarkets that make their own sausage.
Your supermarket can order casings for you.
(Fat and calories reduced about 33% compared to some commercial sausages.)

title: hamburger skillet dinner
directions: In medium skillet, combine meat and gravy mix; cook over low heat until meat is done.
Drain off fat.
Make mashed potatoes by combining water, milk and salt.
Add potato flakes and stir with fork.
Pat meat along bottom and sides of skillet, like a crust. Spoon peas and carrots over crust.
Spread mashed potatoes over the top.
Cover and heat 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in Corning 30 to 40 minutes until golden brown.

title: spiced pretzels
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Bake all together on a cookie sheet for 10 minutes, then stir.
Bake another 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: dark chocolate fudge
directions: In heavy saucepan, over low heat, melt chips, sweetened condensed milk and salt.
Remove from heat and stir in nuts and vanilla.
Spread evenly into 8-inch square, waxed paper lined pan. Chill 2 hours.
Turn onto cutting board, peel off paper and cut into squares.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Partly brown hamburger meat and onion in skillet.
Pour off excess fat.
Add margarine and mushrooms and finish browning.
Then add salt, garlic salt, pepper and flour.
Mix well for about 5 minutes.
Add can cream of chicken soup; stir for 2 or 3 minutes, until completely mixed.
Reduce heat and let simmer for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Then add sour cream and stir until completely mixed and warmed through.
Great over noodles or rice.

title: chicken crunch
directions: Blend broth or milk with soup.
Mix remaining ingredients except for almonds.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.
Sprinkle with almonds before serving.
A good choice for leftover chicken!

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Ground wafers into meal like mixture.
Cut cherries into small pieces.
Chop pecans.
Mix raisins, pecans, coconut, cherries, milk and wafers.
Knead with hands.
Put in greased mold or Pyrex dish.
Set 24 hours in refrigerator.
When ready to serve slice thin.
This will keep for several months in the refrigerator.

title: cracker jacks
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients for five minutes.
Pour over 20 cups of popcorn.
Stir; spread into two large pans.
Bake at 225° for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Cool and store.

title: granny's biscuits
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add buttermilk and cooking oil.
Pour onto floured board and knead until dough is smooth but soft.
Pinch or cut biscuits and place in oiled pan.
Brush with butter or oil and bake until golden brown (350°).

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix meat, eggs, bread crumbs, ketchup, Accent, water and soup mix.
Put in loaf pan.
Cover with 2 strips bacon.
Pour tomato sauce over and bake 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: millionaires
directions: Melt caramel candy with milk over low heat.
Remove and stir in pecans.
Drop by teaspoon on buttered wax paper.
Chill.
Melt Crisco or wax and morsels on low heat; remove from heat.
Dip candy in chocolate and return to wax paper.

title: zucchini-artichoke salad
directions: Combine Italian dressing and the Ranch Style dressing mix; stir in remaining ingredients except lettuce.
Cover and chill
8 hours.
When serving, spoon into a lettuce-lined bowl using a slotted spoon.
Makes 12 to 14 servings.

title: christmas fudge
directions: Cream sugar, syrup and salt; cook in large pan.
