Cook until sugar dissolves (boil 1 minute covered).
Uncover; cook to soft ball stage.
Add vanilla; beat on high speed mixer until creamy. Add all other ingredients.
Pour into square pan.
Chill.

title: meatballs in mushroom sauce
directions: Mix meat, eggs, cheese and oregano.
Shape into about 30 (1/2-inch) balls; brown slightly on all sides in a little hot fat. Drain off excess fat.
Pour in soup.
Add water slowly, stirring to blend.
Simmer, uncovered, for 20 to 25 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Put pickling spices in cloth bag.
Put vinegar, salt and garlic with pickling spices in saucepan.
Simmer, but do not boil.

title: alfredo sauce
directions: Heat butter in saucepan over medium heat. Whisk in flour to form a roux. Add cream and stir until it begins to thicken. Add cheese and nutmeg and continue to stir until desired consistency is achieved. Salt and pepper to taste.

title: cereal candy
directions: Mix the Cornflakes, Rice Krispies, coconut and peanuts in a large mixing bowl.
Boil the sugar, half & half and corn syrup to a soft boil.
Pour over the cereal mixture.
Mix well and pack in shallow buttered 9x13-inch pan.
Cut in squares.

title: chicken cheese ball
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Refrigerate until hard enough to shape.
Roll in chopped walnuts.

title: punch
directions: Cut up oranges and lemons and let stand in part of the sugar. Add all of ingredients, except ginger ale.
Add frozen or fresh strawberries, if desired.
Add ginger ale just before serving. Makes 2 1/2 gallons.
Serves 75.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix together the 2 corns, the package of Jiffy corn mix, 2 eggs and 1 cup milk.
Spread in greased pan.
Spread over above the 1 small diced onion, 1/2 diced green pepper, 2 tablespoons pimento and 1 stick melted oleo (mix the 4 ingredients together and pour over above corn mixture).
Spread 1 1/2 cups grated cheese over above.
Bake in 400° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: steak baked in sour cream
directions: Wipe meat with a wet cloth.
Season on both sides and brown in fat.
Mix tomatoes with A.1. sauce and mustard.
Pour over meat; cover.
Bake at 375° until tender, about 30 minutes.
Add sour cream; cook, uncovered, 10 more minutes.
Thin sour cream with light cream, if too thick.

title: lyle's chili con carne
directions: Stir and brown off meat in skillet or open saucepan; drain off any fat or water that renders out.
Add onions and celery to the meat and stir.
Cook until the vegetables are clear.
In a pot, add all the ingredients together; cover and cook over low heat, the slower, the better (1 to 1 1/2 hours).
Perhaps it would be better for guests to add cayenne pepper to their taste when served. Serves about 8.

title: date sticks
directions: Beat eggs, add sugar, flour, baking powder, salt and vanilla. Add dates and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes in a large greased loaf pan, 10 x 15 x 2-inches.
Cut and roll in powdered sugar while still warm.
Do not overbake.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix all the ingredients together in order: butter, margarine, peaches and the cake mix. Bake 1 hour at 375°.

title: super fudge brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and 1 stick butter in double boiler.
Cream 1 stick butter with 2 cups of sugar.
Beat until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time and mix well, then add vanilla and chocolate mixture. Sift and fold in flour.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Spread evenly, then bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Do not overcook.

title: peach open face pie
directions: Slice peaches; put into unbaked pie shell.
Mix flour, sugar, eggs and pour over peaches.
Add a couple dots of butter.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.
Cool completely before cutting.

title: peach smoothie
directions: Blend at high speed until smooth.
Serves 3.

title: texas soup
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Add rest of ingredients.
Mix together in slow cooker.
Simmer all day on low.

title: pecan balls
directions: Add brown sugars to melted margarine; stir until dissolved. Add the dates and 1 1/2 tablespoons water to sugar, margarine and date mixture.
Cook for 6 minutes, stirring all the time.
Take off stove; add coconut, pecans and vanilla.
Let cool until you can handle it.
Add Rice Krispies.
Mix well and roll in small balls.
Drop in a plastic bag with 1/2 cup confectioners sugar. Lay them on foil until cool.
Store in plastic bowl until ready to serve.
(Very good to serve at Christmas.)

title: crab delight
directions: Mix the mayonnaise and Old Bay seasoning together.
Fold into crabmeat and put in shallow casserole.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.

title: treasure bars
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and press in cake pan.
Bake for 12 minutes in 350° oven.
Next mix the remaining ingredients together.
Pour on top of baked crust and bake 25 minutes or more. Cut in bars.

title: date log
directions: Mix well, roll in crushed nuts and roll in wax paper.
Add coconut and pineapple if desired.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 1 hour, or microwave until done, stirring once during cooking time.

title: shaughn's pineapple drop cookies
directions: Mix shortening and sugar together; cream well.
Add egg and vanilla.
In a separate bowl, mix all dry ingredients together. Add alternately to shortening/sugar with the pineapple.
(You may wish to add a little more pineapple and flour to make the mixture stiffer.)
Add nuts and raisins.
Drop onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes or until light brown.
Yields 48 cookies.

title: baked macaroni zucchini
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Pat zucchini dry and saute over medium heat until browned on both sides.
Drain on paper towel and set aside.
Place tomato sauce in saucepan.
Add wine, celery, parsley and oregano.
Simmer for 5 minutes and set aside.
Preheat oven to 375°.

title: broccoli-cheese dip
directions: Cook broccoli per package instructions.
Dice the celery, mushrooms and onion; saute in butter.
Add Velveeta cheese and cook slowly until all the cheese is melted.
Add garlic powder to taste. Add Tabasco, Worcestershire and seasoning salt to taste.
Serve with corn chips.

title: pretzel candy
directions: Break pretzel sticks into 3 pieces (or bite-size pieces). Place in a bowl. Pour peanuts on top.
Mix together.

Melt white chocolate in either double boiler (covered) on stove top, or in microwave bowl (covered with air vent) in microwave on High for 2 minutes, or until melted (stir after 1 minute, then check every 15 seconds).
Stir and pour over pretzels and peanuts.
Take a cookie sheet and line it with wax paper.
Spread candy mixture across to fill 1 cookie sheet.
Place in refrigerator for 15 minutes to harden.
Take out and break apart like peanut brittle into uneven sized pieces.
Store in cool place or in fridge. Enjoy!

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Thaw broccoli if frozen or cook until tender if fresh.
Put broccoli into a 2 1/2-quart casserole, preferably flat.
Slice cheese over the broccoli.
Sprinkle with the crackers.
Pour butter (melted) over top.
Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes at 350°.

title: shrimp sauce piquante - shrimp creole
directions: In a heavy 6 to 8-quart pot, heat the oil and gradually add the flour, stirring constantly.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until a medium brown roux, the color of rich peanut butter, is formed.
Remove from the heat and add the fresh vegetables and parsley.
Mix well with the roux, then return to low heat and cook, stirring constantly, until the vegetables begin to brown.
Mix in the canned tomatoes and tomato sauce, then add the chives, wine, seasonings and lemon juice and mix again.
Raise the heat under the pan and bring to a low boil.
Add the water and mix thoroughly.
When the mixture boils up again, reduce the heat and simmer for 45 minutes.
Add the shrimp and allow to come to a low boil again, then cover, reduce the heat slightly and simmer for 20 minutes.
Remove the pot from the burner and allow to stand, covered, at room temperature for about 10 minutes before serving.
Serve over boiled rice.
Serves 4.
This takes time to prepare, but it is worth the effort.
When you try it, you will be transported to the Crescent City, New Orleans.

title: raisin puffs
directions: Cook raisins in water over moderate heat until all water is absorbed, set aside and cool.
Cream shortening, sugar and eggs until fluffy.
Sift flour with soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture with cooled raisins and vanilla, mix well.
Shape dough into small balls (walnut size).
Put on greased baking sheet.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool on wire rack.
Yields 6 to 8 dozen.

title: deviled crab casserole
directions: Heat milk and butter together until milk begins to simmer. Do not let it come to a boil.
Crush saltines finely.
Blend saltines with milk and butter.
Add crab meat and seasonings. Save some cracker crumbs to sprinkle on top.
Top with a few pats of butter.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until crab is golden brown.

title: strawberry pudding
directions: In a bowl, put some wafers.
Add strawberries.
Then add a layer of pudding.
Do pudding as on box.
Then repeat the layers.

title: aunt nancy's quiche
directions: Grease 10 x 6-inch or 9 x 9-inch Pyrex pan.
Layer croutons on bottom, cheese over that.
Add egg and milk mixture, meat or mushrooms on top.
Bake at 325° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Great with ham and beans.
Enjoy!

title: chicken balls
directions: Bone chicken breasts and put through food grinder with onion, water chestnuts and mushrooms. Add cornstarch, salt, soy sauce, sherry and beaten egg whites.
Form into small balls and fry in deep hot oil.
Drain and serve with toothpicks.
Yields about 50 small balls.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Cook and drain noodles; combine noodles, tuna, salad dressing, celery, onion, green pepper and salt.
Blend in soup and milk; heat through.
Add cheese; heat and stir until cheese melts.
Turn into 2-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 20 minutes. Makes 6 servings.

title: homemade french dressing
directions: Place sugar, oil, catsup and vinegar in a quart jar.
Shake until all blended well.
Peel and grate a medium-size onion and place in the jar.
Peel two pieces of garlic and place in jar to marinate.
Dressing must set 24 hours before using.
Keep refrigerated.

title: breakfast casserole(from my sister-in-law, linda evans)
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish (9 x 12-inch cake dish).
Refrigerate for 12 hours.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: orientation brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Use 11 1/2 x 17-inch baking pan.

title: oneida or lime pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers lengthwise, then scoop seeds out with spoon. Cut in 1/2-inch thick slices.
Cover with 2 gallons water in which 2 cups lime has been dissolved.
Cover; let stand 24 hours.
Drain and rinse at least 3 times in cold water.
Cover with ice water and let stand 3 hours.
Drain well and dry with towel.
Make a syrup of vinegar, sugar, salt and spices.
Stir well and heat. Pour syrup over cukes and let stand overnight.
The next morning, boil for about 35 minutes or until transparent.
Put in sterilized jars and seal.
Save leftover syrup.
Cover and refrigerate until next making.

title: shrimp fried rice
directions: Heat 1 tablespoon of oil and fry eggs on both sides.
Remove egg and shred.
Heat rest of oil and brown garlic and onion. Once garlic is browned, add rice.
Add shrimp, stirring while cooking, until they turn pink.
Add rest of ingredients and stir until thoroughly heated, about 5 to 8 minutes.
Serve topped with shredded eggs.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix together and place in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: picante chicken with peppers
directions: You will need one large (14 x 20-inch) cooking bag for oven.

title: chicken horseradish salad
directions: Stir all ingredients together. Chill at least 2 hours.

title: dian's s---
directions: Mix flour, butter and nuts together.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan. Cook in 350° oven for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: peanut butter cup candy
directions: Mix 1/2 cup peanut butter with chocolate and melt in heavy saucepan.
In a separate saucepan, melt the remaining 1 cup of peanut butter.
Keep warm over hot water or very low heat on stove.
Cut cupcake liners down to 1-inch deep.
Place in muffin tins.

title: forgotten short ribs
directions: Sprinkle salt and pepper on all sides of meat and put in a 3-quart casserole.
In a small pan, combine tomato sauce with molasses, vinegar, liquid smoke and onion; bring to a boil and simmer 5 minutes.
Pour over ribs.
Cover and bake in slow oven at 275° for 3 to 4 hours or until very tender.
Spoon off excess fat.

title: eggplant szechuan style
directions: Choose firm purple eggplant.
Remove stalk and, without peeling, cut into thumb-size pieces.

title: shipwreck
directions: Spread 2 tablespoons cooking oil in bottom of casserole. Arrange all ingredients in layers.
After potato layer, add salt to taste.
Spread kidney beans over potatoes.
Cover with soup and water.
Cover and bake in a 350° oven for 2 hours.

title: kraut salad
directions: Heat vinegar and sugar to boil; pour over mixture of other ingredients. Store in refrigerator.

title: cranberry-orange relish
directions: Remove seeds from orange.
Core apple.
Grind cranberries, orange, apple and nuts.
Add 3 cups sugar.
Simmer in a saucepan until all sugar is dissolved.
Refrigerate overnight.
Excellent with turkey.

title: unbelievable lasagna
directions: Brown the turkey with onion and garlic clove.
Drain fat from heat.
Mix together the next 7 ingredients.
Mix the cheeses together.

title: peach delight
directions: Dissolve the Jell-O in boiling water. Add cold water.
Stir in pineapple, pie filling and nuts.
Mix well. Let congeal.
Mix cream cheese, sour cream and sugar.
Spread over top of congealed mixture.
Yields 12 to 15 servings.

title: hot spicy tea
directions: If using unsweetened tea and lemonade, add 2 1/2 cups sugar. Add 2 1/2 teaspoons to a cup of hot water.

title: bat food(alabama caviar)
directions: Pour first 4 ingredients in colander to rinse and drain.
Put in a bowl.
Add Italian salad dressing.
Stir well.
Refrigerate. Best if allowed to marinate over night.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in a 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes, then uncover and bake 30 minutes more.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: hershey cake
directions: Mix together all ingredients and pour into two 9-inch greased pans.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: coconut cake
directions: Make yellow cake mix as directed on package and bake in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Upon removal from oven, poke holes in warm cake at 2-inch intervals with knife or chopstick.
Mix together condensed milk and coconut milk.
Pour over cake allowing to soak into holes and along sides.
Chill at least 2 hours.
Cover cake with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Cool until ready to cut and serve. Serves 12 to 16.

title: veg'ol casserole
directions: Add in onions.
Mix together.
Crumble up crackers on top and bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: schnitzel
directions: Pound chops with meat pounder.
Take each chop and dip in milk, then flour and next in beaten eggs and lastly in bread crumbs.
Deep fry (400° to 475°), turning once, then drain.
Put in warm oven on cookie sheet until all are done.
Serve with lemon juice.

title: banana split cake
directions: Using directions on box, make a graham cracker crust in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cream together the cream cheese, powdered sugar and margarine.
Pour mixture on top of crust.
Layer all other ingredients on top of this.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: copper penny carrots
directions: Cook carrots in salted water until medium done (10 to 15 minutes).
Rinse in ice water.
Arrange layers of carrots, pepper and onion in container.
Combine all remaining ingredients in saucepan and bring to boil, stirring until blended.
Pour marinade over carrot mixture and refrigerate until flavor is absorbed. Picnic serve on skewers.

title: hard cinnamon candy
directions: Heat corn syrup, sugar and 1 cup water in saucepan until sugar dissolves, stirring constantly. Boil until mixture reaches hard crack stage or 310° on candy thermometer.
Do not stir.
Stir in cinnamon and food coloring.
Pour into 12 x 24-inch foil lined pan.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Break into pieces when cool.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Serve with fresh vegetables.

title: colorful white cake
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar until light.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beating after each addition.
Gently fold in whites.
Put into 2 greased and lightly floured 9-inch round pans.
Sprinkle with assorted food colors. Use a toothpick to swirl colors.
Bake at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Cool completely. Use your favorite icing.

title: salsa shrimp dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and salsa with electric mixer on medium speed until well blended.
Stir in shrimp.
Serve with tortilla chips or vegetables.
Makes 2 cups.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Add all ingredients to chicken broth, except chicken, noodles and parsley.
Cook until vegetables are tender.
Add chicken, noodles and parsley and cook until noodles are done.
Remove bay leaves.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding with 3 cups of milk; add more for desired thickness.
Line a 13 x 9-inch container with bananas and vanilla wafers.
Pour pudding over bananas and wafers.

title: mary's cherry pie]
directions: Cook all except Jell-O, bananas and nuts until thick.
Remove and cool a few minutes.
Stir in Jell-O.
Add bananas and nuts. Pour into graham cracker crust.
Makes 2 pies, using 8-inch crusts.

title: apple squares
directions: Mix flour, salt, shortening.
Add 1 egg yolk in cup with enough milk to make 2/3 cup.
Roll 1/2 of mixture and put in cookie sheet. Spread with 1 cup cornflakes.
Add apples with sugar and cinnamon. Roll out other 1/2 of dough cover as you do pie crust.
Beat the egg white to soft peaks and spread over crust.
Bake until golden brown.

title: summer salad
directions: Drain pineapple and oranges.
Combine fruit with coconut. Blend in sour cream.
Chill at least 24 hours.
Add marshmallows just before serving.
Serves 10.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour and milk alternately, beginning and ending with flour.
Makes 6 layers.

title: broccoli bake
directions: Mix all ingredients, pour into 13X9 pan and bake at 250 degrees for 50 minutes.

title: english yorkshire pudding
directions: Mix and stand for couple of hours (in blender).
Heat small amount shortening in bottom of pans.
Pour enough batter to cover bottom of pans (use cupcake pans or larger baking pan).
Bake in 400° oven for approximately 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve with roast beef and gravy.

title: cherry pie
directions: Drain cherries.
Set cherries aside.
Heat juice; add 1/2 cup water.
Add sugar to hot liquid.
Add cornstarch, cinnamon and margarine.
When liquid clears, add cherries.
Pour into crust and cook at 300° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: mint tea
directions: Stir together and store in airtight container; makes 1 1/2 cups.
Use one rounded teaspoon per cup.
Recipe from Hills and Pines Garden Club, Raleigh, North Carolina.

title: sweet griddle cakes
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Add egg, milk and butter together.
Then mix into dry ingredients gradually and stir until smooth.
Cook.
Makes 11 (4-inch) cakes.

title: pork chops
directions: Spread pork chops
with
mustard; roll in flour.
Brown slowly.
Place in
baking
dish
and cover with chicken noodle soup.
Place in 350° oven and bake for 1 hour.

title: tamale pie
directions: Brown meat; drain fat.
Add can tomatoes and taco mix.
Simmer 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add corn; mix well.
Pour mixture in baking dish square, approximately 9 x 9-inch.
Prepare cornbread mix per instructions on box, then spread mix on top of mixture evenly.
Bake as directed on cornbread box.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: lemon lush
directions: Blend together flour, pecans and margarine.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350° and cool.

title: hamburger rice soup
directions: Brown meat in medium saucepan.
Add water, bouillon cubes, tomatoes, vegetables, onion and garlic powders.
Bring to boil and simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in rice, simmer 5 minutes longer.

title: egg nog
directions: Beat 3 whole eggs and 1 yolk until very thick and light in color.
Add 3 1/2 tablespoons sugar, beating in thoroughly.
Stir in milk, vanilla and salt.
Pour the mixture into glasses.

title: corn casserole
directions: Skin desired amount of tomatoes. Place in quart jars with 1 teaspoon salt and 1 teaspoon sugar. Seal jars. Place jars on cookie sheet. Set oven to 250°, do not preheat oven. Turn oven off in 1 hour. Do not open oven door; leave tomatoes overnight.

title: ice cream
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and mix well.
Add milk, half and half, salt and vanilla.
Stir until well mixed.
You may add 2 cups of mashed fresh fruit if you want.
Pour into ice cream container or mix everything right in the container.
Follow directions for your ice cream maker.

title: jalapeno cheese
directions: Prepare and chill for a couple of hours.
Delicious with any crackers.

title: sausage balls
directions: Grate cheese.
Mix everything together (use hands).
Roll into small balls.
Bake at 425° for 12 minutes.
Serve with catsup or cocktail sauce.

title: mexican bread
directions: Place 2 tablespoons of butter in round ovenproof casserole. Put in oven and preheat to about 400° or until butter is melted and hot.
Pour in the batter and sprinkle with grated cheese. Bake about 40 minutes or until done.

title: rice and spinach casserole
directions: In a buttered casserole, put first of all the rice, then a layer of the cheese, then the spinach.
Add the mushroom soup and milk.
Then sprinkle with the rest of the cheese.
Bake for 1 hour at 300°.

title: fruity cookies(sugar-free)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease cookie sheet.
Mash bananas. Add dates and oil, mix with fork.
Add remaining ingredients and let stand a few minutes for oats to absorb moisture.
Drop by teaspoonful on cookie sheet.
Bake 25 minutes or until nicely browned.
Cool before removing from cookie sheet.

title: old time tea cakes
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Pour a little at a time into flour and work up like biscuit dough.
Roll out and cut.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Makes 60 or more.

title: corn and chicken soup
directions: Cook corn, celery and chicken in stock.
Bring to a boil and simmer, covered, 15 minutes.
Gradually stir hot milk into egg yolks.
Add to soup mixture and cook 2 minutes, stirring constantly. Add butter and season to taste with salt and pepper. Serve with croutons. Serves 8.

title: different baked potatoes
directions: Melt oleo in flat baking dish.
Use just enough to cover bottom.
Sprinkle pan with salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Slice potatoes in half and place, cut side down, in dish.
Lightly butter potato skin.
Bake at 425° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Serve with sour cream and chives.
Nutmeg is a must.

title: refrigerator sweet pickles
directions: Mix mustard seed, celery seed, turmeric, vinegar, sugar and salt.
Put cucumbers and onions
into glass or plastic gallon jar.
Pour this liquid over slices and stir lightly and stir every day for 2 weeks.
Store in refrigerator.
Do not can.
May be used next day and will keep indefinitely in refrigerator.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach using package directions; drain.
Combine spinach, stuffing mix, Parmesan cheese, eggs, margarine, salt and pepper in bowl; mix well.
Shape into balls; place on baking sheet.
Freeze until firm; store in airtight bag in freezer. Place frozen spinach balls on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes, or until light brown.
Yield: 60 servings.

title: tyrrhenian roast
directions: Combine all
ingredients
except
meat.
Place	a small amount of this sauce
in
the
bottom of a 12-inch Dutch oven. Put in meat and pour
the	rest of the sauce over it.
Roast 2 hours with 9 coals below and
on
top.
Replenish coals as needed.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel eggplant and slice 1/4 to 1/2-inch thick. Dip in beaten eggs, then breadcrumbs. Brown in oil. Put a thin layer of tomato sauce in bottom of a baking dish. Then layer eggplant, Mozzarella, Parmesan and oregano. Two layers are best. Top with tomato sauce and cheese. Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: biscuits supreme
directions: Sift dry ingredients; cut in shortening until it resembles corn meal.
Add milk all at once and stir just until dough follows fork around bowl.
Roll or press 1/2-inch thick on a lightly floured surface and cut out.
Bake on ungreased baking sheet or in a hot 425° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: orange sherbet
directions: Mix ingredients until both become one.
Pour into ice cream freezer and freeze.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Add sherbet to hot jello. Let cool.
Add other ingredients. Refrigerate.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix about half the cake mix to the vegetable oil, vanilla and eggs.
Stir in remaining cake mix, nuts and butterscotch chips.
Drop dough by teaspoon about 2-inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes. Centers will be soft.
Cool slightly.
Remove from cookie sheet with spatula.

title: pepperoni bread
directions: Mix egg, oregano, sugar, parsley flakes and dash of salt together.
Unroll the loaf.
Spread egg mixture on bottom 1/3 of loaf.
(Leave some mixture for the top.)
Put pepperoni on next 1/3 of loaf.
Add Mozzarella cheese to next 1/3 of loaf.
Fold over; slits go on top.
Add remaining egg mixture.
Sprinkle with sesame seed.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: frosted grapes
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff and dip small bunches of grapes into the egg whites.
Let grapes stand until nearly dry on wax paper.
Sprinkle with granulated sugar.
Refrigerate until dry in closed container.

title: baked pineapple(not a dessert)
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and beat.
Add other ingredients.
Mixture will look curdled.
Place in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 50 minutes and serve with ham or turkey.

title: party perfect eggnog
directions: In medium bowl, blend egg yolks, syrup, ginger, cloves, cinnamon and nutmeg until spices have dissolved.
In another bowl, beat egg whites until a little stiff.
Add sugar and continue beating until stiff.
Pour lemon and orange juice in punch bowl. Add egg yolk mixture, then fold in stiff egg whites.
Add ice cream (in chunks).
Pour ginger ale over eggnog mixture.
Stir and serve.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: In 9 x 13-inch baking dish, spread layer of stuffing (dry). Slice and cook zucchini and onion in boiling water until tender. Drain, mix in stewed tomatoes.
Pour over bread stuffing mix.
Top with cheese and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: herb cheese dip
directions: Blend cottage cheese in blender or food processor until smooth.
Add cream cheese and blend.
Stir herbs into mixture. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Garnish with parsley.
Serve with crackers.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix these 2 together and make crust.

title: spinach quiche
directions: Layer 1/2 spinach, 1/2 cheese, 1/2 onion and repeat.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over spinach.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes; reduce to 325° for 20 to 25 minutes longer.
Sprinkle with extra Parmesan and nutmeg.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
In a saucepan, bring oleo, cocoa and water to a boil.
Pour over flour and sugar mixture.
Add buttermilk, vanilla, eggs, cinnamon and soda.
Mix well.
Pour into a greased oblong pan and bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: shaikh's strawberry shortcake
directions: Slice strawberries and sprinkle brown sugar on top.
Let stand for 1 hour.
Heat oven to 450°.

title: better every cake
directions: Bake a yellow pudding cake. Use a 13x9 in pan. Five minutes before cake is done, beat a large can of pineapple (not drained) and 1 cup of sugar together and boil 5 minutes. Remove cake and pour hot pineapple mixture over the top. Mix 1 pkg. instant butter pecan pudding mix according to directions and spread over cake. Spread a large container of cool whip over pudding. Sprinkle with coconut and nuts, Be generous. Chill and serve.

title: sheri's quick taters 'n beef combo
directions: Brown hamburger and onion in a skillet.
Chop hamburger into small chunks.
Drain grease.
Add soups, salt and pepper; mix well.
Fold in taters and vegetables.
Pour into a greased pan or casserole dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: navy bean and potato soup
directions: Soak beans overnight; drain. Add 7 1/4 cups of water and cook 1 hour. Add potatoes, onion, carrot, catsup, salt, pepper and ham. Simmer 30 minutes or until beans and vegetables are tender.

title: seafood gumbo
directions: Saute shrimp in cooking oil (about 6 tablespoons).
In another pot saute okra in about 6 tablespoons of cooking oil, then add onions, sweet peppers, garlic and parsley flakes.
After shrimp are tender, add all ingredients together in one large pot.
When mixture comes to boil, add crab meat and cook on low heat until done (about 1 1/2 hours).

title: baked cabbage
directions: Cut the cabbage coarsely.
Cook in a small amount of salted water until tender.
Drain.
Grease a large baking dish. Alternate a layer of cabbage, then a layer of the cheese, and then a layer of the white sauce.
Top all of the casserole with the mixed cheese and the crumbs.
Bake at 350° until the ingredients are heated through and the cheese is golden brown.

title: apple crumble pie
directions: Combine 1/2 cup of the sugar, the 2 tablespoons flour and the lemon peel.
Sprinkle apple slices with lemon juice.
Add sugar mixture and toss to coat.
Fill a pastry-lined 9-inch pie plate with apple mixture.

title: salmon and cucumber
directions: Remove the skin and bones from the salmon; mix together with mayonnaise to taste.
Slice the cucumber into 3/4-inch slices and with a sharp paring knife make a shallow indentation in each slice.
Top each slice with salmon.

title: shortbread
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly and pour on a cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: teriyaki chicken kebabs
directions: You will need wooden skewers.

title: whipped dry skim milk
directions: Put water in quart mixing bowl.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla.
Sprinkle dry milk over top of liquid.
Beat with rotary beater until mixture is stiff.
Sprinkle sugar or honey on surface.
Beat again until blended and stiff enough to stand in peaks.
Serve mock whipping cream over most any recipe
calling for whipped cream.
Low calorie count and high in protein.

title: savory crescent chicken squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, beat cream cheese and 1 tablespoon softened margarine until smooth.
Add chicken, chives, salt, pepper, milk and pimento; mix well.
Separate crescent dough into 4 rectangles.
Firmly press perforations to seal.
Spoon 1/2 cup of chicken mixture onto center of each rectangle.
Pull 4 corners of dough to center of chicken mixture; twist firmly. Pinch edges to seal.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Brush tops of sandwiches with 1 tablespoon melted margarine; sprinkle with crushed croutons.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: wedding cookies
directions: Soften butter and add all other ingredients.
Mix well.
Roll into small balls; place on cookie sheet that has been lightly sprayed.
Press each cookie slightly.
Bake at 350° for about 20 to 25 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar while still warm.

title: good dressing
directions: Mix all together and bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chili
directions: Mix chili powder, garlic, pepper and salt.
Brown with beef. Add beans, water and oatmeal.
Simmer about 1 hour.
Mash occasionally with potato masher.

title: sausage quiche
directions: Baking Temperature: 350°.
Baking Time: 25 to 30 minutes.

title: coney island casserole(makes 6 servings)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine rice, franks, chili and onion. Pour into a 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle cheese over the top. Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until cheese is melted and bubbly.

title: fiesta bites
directions: Layer tortilla and mixture ending up with tortilla on top. Refrigerate before serving and cut on a diagonal.

title: million dollar fudge
directions: Handed down 29 years ago to me from Sister Watson.
As near a grandmother as I ever had.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli into bite-size pieces.
(May peel the larger stalk and cut up also.)
Saute bacon until crisp.
In large bowl combine broccoli, onion, bacon and raisins.
In another bowl mix together mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Combine dressing with veggies and refrigerate for at least 2 hours before serving.
May add sunflower seeds at this time.

title: pineapple banana shake
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Mix the ingredients well.
Put flour on your hands and take a small piece of the dough.
Make it into a shape, make sure to keep it thin.
Put the biscuits on a greased cookie sheet.
Place them in the oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
After baking, let the biscuits cool for 30 minutes.

title: fried spinach balls
directions: Combine spinach with water, 1 egg, crumbs, onion, cheese and allspice.
Mix thoroughly.
Let stand 10 minutes. Shape balls. Combine remaining egg and water; blend well. Roll balls in crumbs, dip in egg mixture and again in crumbs.
Fry in hot fat (375°) until brown. Drain on absorbent paper before serving.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream together the shortening, sugars and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat after each addition. Sift together flour, salt and soda; add to creamed mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop by spoon onto an ungreased cookie sheet. Bake for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Combine dry ingredients and stir into creamed mixture alternately with mashed bananas.
Fold in nuts (and chips if desired).
Pour into buttered loaf pan and let stand at room temperature for 20 minutes.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: plain cake
directions: Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until brown.
